79 static CGCXXABI *createCXXABI(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
80  switch (CGM.getContext().getCXXABIKind()) {
81  case TargetCXXABI::AppleARM64:
82  case TargetCXXABI::Fuchsia:
83  case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
84  case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
85  case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
86  case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
87  case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
88  case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
89  case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
90  case TargetCXXABI::XL:
91  return CreateItaniumCXXABI(CGM);
92  case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
93  return CreateMicrosoftCXXABI(CGM);
94  }
95 
96  llvm_unreachable("invalid C++ ABI kind");
97 }

99 CodeGenModule::CodeGenModule(ASTContext &C, const HeaderSearchOptions &HSO,
100  const PreprocessorOptions &PPO,
101  const CodeGenOptions &CGO, llvm::Module &M,
102  DiagnosticsEngine &diags,
103  CoverageSourceInfo *CoverageInfo)
104  : Context(C), LangOpts(C.getLangOpts()), HeaderSearchOpts(HSO),
105  PreprocessorOpts(PPO), CodeGenOpts(CGO), TheModule(M), Diags(diags),
106  Target(C.getTargetInfo()), ABI(createCXXABI(*this)),
107  VMContext(M.getContext()), Types(*this), VTables(*this),
108  SanitizerMD(new SanitizerMetadata(*this)) {
109 
110  // Initialize the type cache.
111  llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = M.getContext();
112  VoidTy = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(LLVMContext);
113  Int8Ty = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(LLVMContext);
114  Int16Ty = llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(LLVMContext);
115  Int32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
116  Int64Ty = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(LLVMContext);
117  HalfTy = llvm::Type::getHalfTy(LLVMContext);
118  BFloatTy = llvm::Type::getBFloatTy(LLVMContext);
119  FloatTy = llvm::Type::getFloatTy(LLVMContext);
120  DoubleTy = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(LLVMContext);
121  PointerWidthInBits = C.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0);
122  PointerAlignInBytes =
123  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getTargetInfo().getPointerAlign(0)).getQuantity();
124  SizeSizeInBytes =
125  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getTargetInfo().getMaxPointerWidth()).getQuantity();
126  IntAlignInBytes =
127  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getTargetInfo().getIntAlign()).getQuantity();
128  CharTy =
129  llvm::IntegerType::get(LLVMContext, C.getTargetInfo().getCharWidth());
130  IntTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(LLVMContext, C.getTargetInfo().getIntWidth());
131  IntPtrTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(LLVMContext,
132  C.getTargetInfo().getMaxPointerWidth());
133  Int8PtrTy = Int8Ty->getPointerTo(0);
134  Int8PtrPtrTy = Int8PtrTy->getPointerTo(0);
135  const llvm::DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
136  AllocaInt8PtrTy = Int8Ty->getPointerTo(DL.getAllocaAddrSpace());
137  GlobalsInt8PtrTy = Int8Ty->getPointerTo(DL.getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace());
138  ASTAllocaAddressSpace = getTargetCodeGenInfo().getASTAllocaAddressSpace();
139 
140  RuntimeCC = getTargetCodeGenInfo().getABIInfo().getRuntimeCC();
141 
142  if (LangOpts.ObjC)
143  createObjCRuntime();
144  if (LangOpts.OpenCL || LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
145  createOpenCLRuntime();
146  if (LangOpts.OpenMP)
147  createOpenMPRuntime();
148  if (LangOpts.CUDA)
149  createCUDARuntime();
150  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
151  createSYCLRuntime();
152 
153  // Enable TBAA unless it's suppressed. ThreadSanitizer needs TBAA even at O0.
154  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Thread) ||
155  (!CodeGenOpts.RelaxedAliasing && CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel > 0))
156  TBAA.reset(new CodeGenTBAA(Context, TheModule, CodeGenOpts, getLangOpts(),
157  getCXXABI().getMangleContext()));
158 
159  // If debug info or coverage generation is enabled, create the CGDebugInfo
160  // object.
161  if (CodeGenOpts.getDebugInfo() != codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo ||
162  CodeGenOpts.EmitGcovArcs || CodeGenOpts.EmitGcovNotes)
163  DebugInfo.reset(new CGDebugInfo(*this));
164 
165  Block.GlobalUniqueCount = 0;
166 
167  if (C.getLangOpts().ObjC)
168  ObjCData.reset(new ObjCEntrypoints());
169 
170  if (CodeGenOpts.hasProfileClangUse()) {
171  auto ReaderOrErr = llvm::IndexedInstrProfReader::create(
172  CodeGenOpts.ProfileInstrumentUsePath, CodeGenOpts.ProfileRemappingFile);
173  if (auto E = ReaderOrErr.takeError()) {
174  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
175  "Could not read profile %0: %1");
176  llvm::handleAllErrors(std::move(E), [&](const llvm::ErrorInfoBase &EI) {
177  getDiags().Report(DiagID) << CodeGenOpts.ProfileInstrumentUsePath
178  << EI.message();
179  });
180  } else
181  PGOReader = std::move(ReaderOrErr.get());
182  }
183 
184  // If coverage mapping generation is enabled, create the
185  // CoverageMappingModuleGen object.
186  if (CodeGenOpts.CoverageMapping)
187  CoverageMapping.reset(new CoverageMappingModuleGen(*this, *CoverageInfo));
188 
189  // Generate the module name hash here if needed.
190  if (CodeGenOpts.UniqueInternalLinkageNames &&
191  !getModule().getSourceFileName().empty()) {
192  std::string Path = getModule().getSourceFileName();
193  // Check if a path substitution is needed from the MacroPrefixMap.
194  for (const auto &Entry : LangOpts.MacroPrefixMap)
195  if (Path.rfind(Entry.first, 0) != std::string::npos) {
196  Path = Entry.second + Path.substr(Entry.first.size());
197  break;
198  }
199  llvm::MD5 Md5;
200  Md5.update(Path);
201  llvm::MD5::MD5Result R;
202  Md5.final(R);
203  SmallString<32> Str;
204  llvm::MD5::stringifyResult(R, Str);
205  // Convert MD5hash to Decimal. Demangler suffixes can either contain
206  // numbers or characters but not both.
207  llvm::APInt IntHash(128, Str.str(), 16);
208  // Prepend "__uniq" before the hash for tools like profilers to understand
209  // that this symbol is of internal linkage type. The "__uniq" is the
210  // pre-determined prefix that is used to tell tools that this symbol was
211  // created with -funique-internal-linakge-symbols and the tools can strip or
212  // keep the prefix as needed.
213  ModuleNameHash = (Twine(".__uniq.") +
214  Twine(toString(IntHash, /* Radix = */ 10, /* Signed = */false))).str();
215  }
216 }
217 
218 CodeGenModule::~CodeGenModule() {}

220 void CodeGenModule::createObjCRuntime() {
221  // This is just isGNUFamily(), but we want to force implementors of
222  // new ABIs to decide how best to do this.
223  switch (LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.getKind()) {
224  case ObjCRuntime::GNUstep:
225  case ObjCRuntime::GCC:
226  case ObjCRuntime::ObjFW:
227  ObjCRuntime.reset(CreateGNUObjCRuntime(*this));
228  return;
229 
230  case ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX:
231  case ObjCRuntime::MacOSX:
232  case ObjCRuntime::iOS:
233  case ObjCRuntime::WatchOS:
234  ObjCRuntime.reset(CreateMacObjCRuntime(*this));
235  return;
236  }
237  llvm_unreachable("bad runtime kind");
238 }
239 
240 void CodeGenModule::createOpenCLRuntime() {
241  OpenCLRuntime.reset(new CGOpenCLRuntime(*this));
242 }
243 
244 void CodeGenModule::createOpenMPRuntime() {
245  // Select a specialized code generation class based on the target, if any.
246  // If it does not exist use the default implementation.
247  switch (getTriple().getArch()) {
248  case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
249  case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
250  case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
251  assert(getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
252  "OpenMP AMDGPU/NVPTX is only prepared to deal with device code.");
253  OpenMPRuntime.reset(new CGOpenMPRuntimeGPU(*this));
254  break;
255  default:
256  if (LangOpts.OpenMPSimd)
257  OpenMPRuntime.reset(new CGOpenMPSIMDRuntime(*this));
258  else
259  OpenMPRuntime.reset(new CGOpenMPRuntime(*this));
260  break;
261  }
262 }
263 
264 void CodeGenModule::createCUDARuntime() {
265  CUDARuntime.reset(CreateNVCUDARuntime(*this));
266 }

268 void CodeGenModule::createSYCLRuntime() {
269  SYCLRuntime.reset(new CGSYCLRuntime(*this));
270 }

272 void CodeGenModule::addReplacement(StringRef Name, llvm::Constant *C) {
273  Replacements[Name] = C;
274 }
275 
276 void CodeGenModule::applyReplacements() {
277  for (auto &I : Replacements) {
278  StringRef MangledName = I.first();
279  llvm::Constant *Replacement = I.second;
280  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
281  if (!Entry)
282  continue;
283  auto *OldF = cast<llvm::Function>(Entry);
284  auto *NewF = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Replacement);
285  if (!NewF) {
286  if (auto *Alias = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Replacement)) {
287  NewF = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Alias->getAliasee());
288  } else {
289  auto *CE = cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Replacement);
290  assert(CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast ||
291  CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::GetElementPtr);
292  NewF = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(CE->getOperand(0));
293  }
294  }
295 
296  // Replace old with new, but keep the old order.
297  OldF->replaceAllUsesWith(Replacement);
298  if (NewF) {
299  NewF->removeFromParent();
300  OldF->getParent()->getFunctionList().insertAfter(OldF->getIterator(),
301  NewF);
302  }
303  OldF->eraseFromParent();
304  }
305 }
306 
307 void CodeGenModule::addGlobalValReplacement(llvm::GlobalValue *GV, llvm::Constant *C) {
308  GlobalValReplacements.push_back(std::make_pair(GV, C));
309 }
310 
311 void CodeGenModule::applyGlobalValReplacements() {
312  for (auto &I : GlobalValReplacements) {
313  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = I.first;
314  llvm::Constant *C = I.second;
315 
316  GV->replaceAllUsesWith(C);
317  GV->eraseFromParent();
318  }
319 }

321 // This is only used in aliases that we created and we know they have a
322 // linear structure.
323 static const llvm::GlobalValue *getAliasedGlobal(const llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
324  const llvm::Constant *C;
325  if (auto *GA = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(GV))
326  C = GA->getAliasee();
327  else if (auto *GI = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(GV))
328  C = GI->getResolver();
329  else
330  return GV;
331 
332  const auto *AliaseeGV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(C->stripPointerCasts());
333  if (!AliaseeGV)
334  return nullptr;
335 
336  const llvm::GlobalValue *FinalGV = AliaseeGV->getAliaseeObject();
337  if (FinalGV == GV)
338  return nullptr;
339 
340  return FinalGV;
341 }
342 
343 static bool checkAliasedGlobal(DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
344  SourceLocation Location, bool IsIFunc,
345  const llvm::GlobalValue *Alias,
346  const llvm::GlobalValue *&GV) {
347  GV = getAliasedGlobal(Alias);
348  if (!GV) {
349  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_cyclic_alias) << IsIFunc;
350  return false;
351  }
352 
353  if (GV->isDeclaration()) {
354  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_alias_to_undefined) << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
355  return false;
356  }
357 
358  if (IsIFunc) {
359  // Check resolver function type.
360  const auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
361  if (!F) {
362  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_alias_to_undefined)
363  << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
364  return false;
365  }
366 
367  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = F->getFunctionType();
368  if (!FTy->getReturnType()->isPointerTy()) {
369  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_ifunc_resolver_return);
370  return false;
371  }
372  }
373 
374  return true;
375 }
376 
377 void CodeGenModule::checkAliases() {
378  // Check if the constructed aliases are well formed. It is really unfortunate
379  // that we have to do this in CodeGen, but we only construct mangled names
380  // and aliases during codegen.
381  bool Error = false;
382  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = getDiags();
383  for (const GlobalDecl &GD : Aliases) {
384  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
385  SourceLocation Location;
386  bool IsIFunc = D->hasAttr<IFuncAttr>();
387  if (const Attr *A = D->getDefiningAttr())
388  Location = A->getLocation();
389  else
390  llvm_unreachable("Not an alias or ifunc?");
391 
392  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
393  llvm::GlobalValue *Alias = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
394  const llvm::GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
395  if (!checkAliasedGlobal(Diags, Location, IsIFunc, Alias, GV)) {
396  Error = true;
397  continue;
398  }
399 
400  llvm::Constant *Aliasee =
401  IsIFunc ? cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(Alias)->getResolver()
402  : cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Alias)->getAliasee();
403 
404  llvm::GlobalValue *AliaseeGV;
405  if (auto CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Aliasee))
406  AliaseeGV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CE->getOperand(0));
407  else
408  AliaseeGV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Aliasee);
409 
410  if (const SectionAttr *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>()) {
411  StringRef AliasSection = SA->getName();
412  if (AliasSection != AliaseeGV->getSection())
413  Diags.Report(SA->getLocation(), diag::warn_alias_with_section)
414  << AliasSection << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
415  }
416 
417  // We have to handle alias to weak aliases in here. LLVM itself disallows
418  // this since the object semantics would not match the IL one. For
419  // compatibility with gcc we implement it by just pointing the alias
420  // to its aliasee's aliasee. We also warn, since the user is probably
421  // expecting the link to be weak.
422  if (auto *GA = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(AliaseeGV)) {
423  if (GA->isInterposable()) {
424  Diags.Report(Location, diag::warn_alias_to_weak_alias)
425  << GV->getName() << GA->getName() << IsIFunc;
426  Aliasee = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
427  GA->getAliasee(), Alias->getType());
428 
429  if (IsIFunc)
430  cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(Alias)->setResolver(Aliasee);
431  else
432  cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Alias)->setAliasee(Aliasee);
433  }
434  }
435  }
436  if (!Error)
437  return;
438 
439  for (const GlobalDecl &GD : Aliases) {
440  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
441  llvm::GlobalValue *Alias = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
442  Alias->replaceAllUsesWith(llvm::UndefValue::get(Alias->getType()));
443  Alias->eraseFromParent();
444  }
445 }

447 void CodeGenModule::clear() {
448  DeferredDeclsToEmit.clear();
449  if (OpenMPRuntime)
450  OpenMPRuntime->clear();
451 }

453 void InstrProfStats::reportDiagnostics(DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
454  StringRef MainFile) {
455  if (!hasDiagnostics())
456  return;
457  if (VisitedInMainFile > 0 && VisitedInMainFile == MissingInMainFile) {
458  if (MainFile.empty())
459  MainFile = "<stdin>";
460  Diags.Report(diag::warn_profile_data_unprofiled) << MainFile;
461  } else {
462  if (Mismatched > 0)
463  Diags.Report(diag::warn_profile_data_out_of_date) << Visited << Mismatched;
464 
465  if (Missing > 0)
466  Diags.Report(diag::warn_profile_data_missing) << Visited << Missing;
467  }
468 }
469 
470 static void setVisibilityFromDLLStorageClass(const clang::LangOptions &LO,
471  llvm::Module &M) {
472  if (!LO.VisibilityFromDLLStorageClass)
473  return;
474 
475  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes DLLExportVisibility =
476  CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(LO.getDLLExportVisibility());
477  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes NoDLLStorageClassVisibility =
478  CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(LO.getNoDLLStorageClassVisibility());
479  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes ExternDeclDLLImportVisibility =
480  CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(LO.getExternDeclDLLImportVisibility());
481  llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes ExternDeclNoDLLStorageClassVisibility =
482  CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(
483  LO.getExternDeclNoDLLStorageClassVisibility());
484 
485  for (llvm::GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) {
486  if (GV.hasAppendingLinkage() || GV.hasLocalLinkage())
487  continue;
488 
489  // Reset DSO locality before setting the visibility. This removes
490  // any effects that visibility options and annotations may have
491  // had on the DSO locality. Setting the visibility will implicitly set
492  // appropriate globals to DSO Local; however, this will be pessimistic
493  // w.r.t. to the normal compiler IRGen.
494  GV.setDSOLocal(false);
495 
496  if (GV.isDeclarationForLinker()) {
497  GV.setVisibility(GV.getDLLStorageClass() ==
498  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass
499  ? ExternDeclDLLImportVisibility
500  : ExternDeclNoDLLStorageClassVisibility);
501  } else {
502  GV.setVisibility(GV.getDLLStorageClass() ==
503  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass
504  ? DLLExportVisibility
505  : NoDLLStorageClassVisibility);
506  }
507 
508  GV.setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
509  }
510 }
511 
512 static llvm::MDNode *getAspectsMD(ASTContext &ASTContext,
513  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx, StringRef Name,
514  const SYCLUsesAspectsAttr *A) {
515  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 4> AspectsMD;
516  AspectsMD.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, Name));
517  for (auto *Aspect : A->aspects()) {
518  llvm::APSInt AspectInt = Aspect->EvaluateKnownConstInt(ASTContext);
519  AspectsMD.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
520  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), AspectInt.getZExtValue())));
521  }
522  return llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, AspectsMD);
523 }
524 
525 void CodeGenModule::Release() {
526  EmitDeferred();
527  EmitVTablesOpportunistically();
528  applyGlobalValReplacements();
529  applyReplacements();
530  checkAliases();
531  emitMultiVersionFunctions();
532  EmitCXXGlobalInitFunc();
533  EmitCXXGlobalCleanUpFunc();
534  registerGlobalDtorsWithAtExit();
535  EmitCXXThreadLocalInitFunc();
536  if (ObjCRuntime)
537  if (llvm::Function *ObjCInitFunction = ObjCRuntime->ModuleInitFunction())
538  AddGlobalCtor(ObjCInitFunction);
539  if (Context.getLangOpts().CUDA && CUDARuntime) {
540  if (llvm::Function *CudaCtorFunction = CUDARuntime->finalizeModule())
541  AddGlobalCtor(CudaCtorFunction);
542  }
543  if (OpenMPRuntime) {
544  if (llvm::Function *OpenMPRequiresDirectiveRegFun =
545  OpenMPRuntime->emitRequiresDirectiveRegFun()) {
546  AddGlobalCtor(OpenMPRequiresDirectiveRegFun, 0);
547  }
548  OpenMPRuntime->createOffloadEntriesAndInfoMetadata();
549  OpenMPRuntime->clear();
550  }
551  if (PGOReader) {
552  getModule().setProfileSummary(
553  PGOReader->getSummary(/* UseCS */ false).getMD(VMContext),
554  llvm::ProfileSummary::PSK_Instr);
555  if (PGOStats.hasDiagnostics())
556  PGOStats.reportDiagnostics(getDiags(), getCodeGenOpts().MainFileName);
557  }
558  EmitCtorList(GlobalCtors, "llvm.global_ctors");
559  EmitCtorList(GlobalDtors, "llvm.global_dtors");
560  EmitGlobalAnnotations();
561  EmitStaticExternCAliases();
562  EmitDeferredUnusedCoverageMappings();
563  CodeGenPGO(*this).setValueProfilingFlag(getModule());
564  if (CoverageMapping)
565  CoverageMapping->emit();
566  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso) {
567  CodeGenFunction(*this).EmitCfiCheckFail();
568  CodeGenFunction(*this).EmitCfiCheckStub();
569  }
570  emitAtAvailableLinkGuard();
571  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isWasm() &&
572  !Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSEmscripten()) {
573  EmitMainVoidAlias();
574  }
575 
576  if (getTriple().isAMDGPU()) {
577  // Emit reference of __amdgpu_device_library_preserve_asan_functions to
578  // preserve ASAN functions in bitcode libraries.
579  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address)) {
580  auto *FT = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {});
581  auto *F = llvm::Function::Create(
582  FT, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
583  "__amdgpu_device_library_preserve_asan_functions", &getModule());
584  auto *Var = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
585  getModule(), FT->getPointerTo(),
586  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, F,
587  "__amdgpu_device_library_preserve_asan_functions_ptr", nullptr,
588  llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal);
589  addCompilerUsedGlobal(Var);
590  }
591  // Emit amdgpu_code_object_version module flag, which is code object version
592  // times 100.
593  // ToDo: Enable module flag for all code object version when ROCm device
594  // library is ready.
595  if (getTarget().getTargetOpts().CodeObjectVersion == TargetOptions::COV_5) {
596  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error,
597  "amdgpu_code_object_version",
598  getTarget().getTargetOpts().CodeObjectVersion);
599  }
600  }
601 
602  emitLLVMUsed();
603  if (SanStats)
604  SanStats->finish();
605 
606  if (CodeGenOpts.Autolink &&
607  (Context.getLangOpts().Modules || !LinkerOptionsMetadata.empty())) {
608  EmitModuleLinkOptions();
609  }
610 
611  // On ELF we pass the dependent library specifiers directly to the linker
612  // without manipulating them. This is in contrast to other platforms where
613  // they are mapped to a specific linker option by the compiler. This
614  // difference is a result of the greater variety of ELF linkers and the fact
615  // that ELF linkers tend to handle libraries in a more complicated fashion
616  // than on other platforms. This forces us to defer handling the dependent
617  // libs to the linker.
618  //
619  // CUDA/HIP device and host libraries are different. Currently there is no
620  // way to differentiate dependent libraries for host or device. Existing
621  // usage of #pragma comment(lib, *) is intended for host libraries on
622  // Windows. Therefore emit llvm.dependent-libraries only for host.
623  if (!ELFDependentLibraries.empty() && !Context.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
624  auto *NMD = getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.dependent-libraries");
625  for (auto *MD : ELFDependentLibraries)
626  NMD->addOperand(MD);
627  }
628 
629  // Record mregparm value now so it is visible through rest of codegen.
630  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86)
631  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "NumRegisterParameters",
632  CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters);
633 
634  if (CodeGenOpts.DwarfVersion) {
635  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "Dwarf Version",
636  CodeGenOpts.DwarfVersion);
637  }
638 
639  if (CodeGenOpts.Dwarf64)
640  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "DWARF64", 1);
641 
642  if (Context.getLangOpts().SemanticInterposition)
643  // Require various optimization to respect semantic interposition.
644  getModule().setSemanticInterposition(true);
645 
646  if (CodeGenOpts.EmitCodeView) {
647  // Indicate that we want CodeView in the metadata.
648  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "CodeView", 1);
649  }
650  if (CodeGenOpts.CodeViewGHash) {
651  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "CodeViewGHash", 1);
652  }
653  if (CodeGenOpts.ControlFlowGuard) {
654  // Function ID tables and checks for Control Flow Guard (cfguard=2).
655  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "cfguard", 2);
656  } else if (CodeGenOpts.ControlFlowGuardNoChecks) {
657  // Function ID tables for Control Flow Guard (cfguard=1).
658  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "cfguard", 1);
659  }
660  if (CodeGenOpts.EHContGuard) {
661  // Function ID tables for EH Continuation Guard.
662  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "ehcontguard", 1);
663  }
664  if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel > 0 && CodeGenOpts.StrictVTablePointers) {
665  // We don't support LTO with 2 with different StrictVTablePointers
666  // FIXME: we could support it by stripping all the information introduced
667  // by StrictVTablePointers.
668 
669  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "StrictVTablePointers",1);
670 
671  llvm::Metadata *Ops[2] = {
672  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "StrictVTablePointers"),
673  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
674  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(VMContext), 1))};
675 
676  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Require,
677  "StrictVTablePointersRequirement",
678  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, Ops));
679  }
680  if (getModuleDebugInfo())
681  // We support a single version in the linked module. The LLVM
682  // parser will drop debug info with a different version number
683  // (and warn about it, too).
684  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "Debug Info Version",
685  llvm::DEBUG_METADATA_VERSION);
686 
687  // We need to record the widths of enums and wchar_t, so that we can generate
688  // the correct build attributes in the ARM backend. wchar_size is also used by
689  // TargetLibraryInfo.
690  uint64_t WCharWidth =
691  Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Context.getWideCharType()).getQuantity();
692  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "wchar_size", WCharWidth);
693 
694  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch();
695  if ( Arch == llvm::Triple::arm
696  || Arch == llvm::Triple::armeb
697  || Arch == llvm::Triple::thumb
698  || Arch == llvm::Triple::thumbeb) {
699  // The minimum width of an enum in bytes
700  uint64_t EnumWidth = Context.getLangOpts().ShortEnums ? 1 : 4;
701  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "min_enum_size", EnumWidth);
702  }
703 
704  if (Arch == llvm::Triple::riscv32 || Arch == llvm::Triple::riscv64) {
705  StringRef ABIStr = Target.getABI();
706  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
707  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "target-abi",
708  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, ABIStr));
709  }
710 
711  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso) {
712  // Indicate that we want cross-DSO control flow integrity checks.
713  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "Cross-DSO CFI", 1);
714  }
715 
716  if (CodeGenOpts.WholeProgramVTables) {
717  // Indicate whether VFE was enabled for this module, so that the
718  // vcall_visibility metadata added under whole program vtables is handled
719  // appropriately in the optimizer.
720  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Virtual Function Elim",
721  CodeGenOpts.VirtualFunctionElimination);
722  }
723 
724  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall)) {
725  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
726  "CFI Canonical Jump Tables",
727  CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCanonicalJumpTables);
728  }
729 
730  if (CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn &&
731  Target.checkCFProtectionReturnSupported(getDiags())) {
732  // Indicate that we want to instrument return control flow protection.
733  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "cf-protection-return",
734  1);
735  }
736 
737  if (CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch &&
738  Target.checkCFProtectionBranchSupported(getDiags())) {
739  // Indicate that we want to instrument branch control flow protection.
740  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "cf-protection-branch",
741  1);
742  }
743 
744  if (CodeGenOpts.IBTSeal)
745  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "ibt-seal", 1);
746 
747  // Add module metadata for return address signing (ignoring
748  // non-leaf/all) and stack tagging. These are actually turned on by function
749  // attributes, but we use module metadata to emit build attributes. This is
750  // needed for LTO, where the function attributes are inside bitcode
751  // serialised into a global variable by the time build attributes are
752  // emitted, so we can't access them.
753  if (Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature("ptrauth") &&
754  LangOpts.getSignReturnAddressScope() !=
755  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::None)
756  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
757  "sign-return-address-buildattr", 1);
758  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::MemTag))
759  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
760  "tag-stack-memory-buildattr", 1);
761 
762  if (Arch == llvm::Triple::thumb || Arch == llvm::Triple::thumbeb ||
763  Arch == llvm::Triple::arm || Arch == llvm::Triple::armeb ||
764  Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64 || Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_32 ||
765  Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_be) {
766  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "branch-target-enforcement",
767  LangOpts.BranchTargetEnforcement);
768 
769  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "sign-return-address",
770  LangOpts.hasSignReturnAddress());
771 
772  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "sign-return-address-all",
773  LangOpts.isSignReturnAddressScopeAll());
774 
775  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error,
776  "sign-return-address-with-bkey",
777  !LangOpts.isSignReturnAddressWithAKey());
778  }
779 
780  if (!CodeGenOpts.MemoryProfileOutput.empty()) {
781  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
782  getModule().addModuleFlag(
783  llvm::Module::Error, "MemProfProfileFilename",
784  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, CodeGenOpts.MemoryProfileOutput));
785  }
786 
787  if ((LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice || LangOpts.isSYCL()) && getTriple().isNVPTX()) {
788  // Indicate whether __nvvm_reflect should be configured to flush denormal
789  // floating point values to 0. (This corresponds to its "__CUDA_FTZ"
790  // property.)
791  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "nvvm-reflect-ftz",
792  CodeGenOpts.FP32DenormalMode.Output !=
793  llvm::DenormalMode::IEEE);
794  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "nvvm-reflect-prec-sqrt",
795  getTarget().getTargetOpts().NVVMCudaPrecSqrt);
796  }
797 
798  if (LangOpts.EHAsynch)
799  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "eh-asynch", 1);
800 
801  // Indicate whether this Module was compiled with -fopenmp
802  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd)
803  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "openmp", LangOpts.OpenMP);
804  if (getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice)
805  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "openmp-device",
806  LangOpts.OpenMP);
807 
808  // Emit OpenCL specific module metadata: OpenCL/SPIR version.
809  if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
810  EmitOpenCLMetadata();
811  // Emit SPIR version.
812  if (getTriple().isSPIR()) {
813  // SPIR v2.0 s2.12 - The SPIR version used by the module is stored in the
814  // opencl.spir.version named metadata.
815  // C++ for OpenCL has a distinct mapping for version compatibility with
816  // OpenCL.
817  auto Version = LangOpts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion();
818  llvm::Metadata *SPIRVerElts[] = {
819  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
820  Int32Ty, Version / 100)),
821  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
822  Int32Ty, (Version / 100 > 1) ? 0 : 2))};
823  llvm::NamedMDNode *SPIRVerMD =
824  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("opencl.spir.version");
825  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
826  SPIRVerMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, SPIRVerElts));
827  }
828  }
829 
830  // Emit SYCL specific module metadata: OpenCL/SPIR version, OpenCL language,
831  // metadata for optional features (device aspects).
832  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
833  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
834  llvm::Metadata *SPIRVerElts[] = {
835  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 1)),
836  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 2))};
837  llvm::NamedMDNode *SPIRVerMD =
838  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("opencl.spir.version");
839  SPIRVerMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, SPIRVerElts));
840  // We are trying to look like OpenCL C++ for SPIR-V translator.
841  // 4 - OpenCL_CPP, 100000 - OpenCL C++ version 1.0
842  // 0 - ESIMD, if any kernel or function is an explicit SIMD one
843  int Lang = llvm::any_of(TheModule,
844  [](const auto &F) {
845  return F.getMetadata("sycl_explicit_simd");
846  })
847  ? 0
848  : 4;
849 
850  llvm::Metadata *SPIRVSourceElts[] = {
851  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Lang)),
852  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 100000))};
853  llvm::NamedMDNode *SPIRVSourceMD =
854  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("spirv.Source");
855  SPIRVSourceMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, SPIRVSourceElts));
856 
857  // Emit type name with list of associated device aspects.
858  if (TypesWithAspects.size() > 0) {
859  llvm::NamedMDNode *AspectsMD =
860  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("intel_types_that_use_aspects");
861  for (const auto &Type : TypesWithAspects) {
862  StringRef Name = Type.first;
863  const RecordDecl *RD = Type.second;
864  AspectsMD->addOperand(getAspectsMD(Context, TheModule.getContext(),
865  Name,
866  RD->getAttr<SYCLUsesAspectsAttr>()));
867  }
868  }
869  }
870 
871  if (uint32_t PLevel = Context.getLangOpts().PICLevel) {
872  assert(PLevel < 3 && "Invalid PIC Level");
873  getModule().setPICLevel(static_cast<llvm::PICLevel::Level>(PLevel));
874  if (Context.getLangOpts().PIE)
875  getModule().setPIELevel(static_cast<llvm::PIELevel::Level>(PLevel));
876  }
877 
878  if (getCodeGenOpts().CodeModel.size() > 0) {
879  unsigned CM = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(getCodeGenOpts().CodeModel)
880  .Case("tiny", llvm::CodeModel::Tiny)
881  .Case("small", llvm::CodeModel::Small)
882  .Case("kernel", llvm::CodeModel::Kernel)
883  .Case("medium", llvm::CodeModel::Medium)
884  .Case("large", llvm::CodeModel::Large)
885  .Default(~0u);
886  if (CM != ~0u) {
887  llvm::CodeModel::Model codeModel = static_cast<llvm::CodeModel::Model>(CM);
888  getModule().setCodeModel(codeModel);
889  }
890  }
891 
892  if (CodeGenOpts.NoPLT)
893  getModule().setRtLibUseGOT();
894  if (CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables)
895  getModule().setUwtable(llvm::UWTableKind(CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables));
896 
897  switch (CodeGenOpts.getFramePointer()) {
898  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::None:
899  // 0 ("none") is the default.
900  break;
901  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::NonLeaf:
902  getModule().setFramePointer(llvm::FramePointerKind::NonLeaf);
903  break;
904  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::All:
905  getModule().setFramePointer(llvm::FramePointerKind::All);
906  break;
907  }
908 
909  SimplifyPersonality();
910 
911  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitDeclMetadata)
912  EmitDeclMetadata();
913 
914  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitGcovArcs || getCodeGenOpts().EmitGcovNotes)
915  EmitCoverageFile();
916 
917  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
918  DI->finalize();
919 
920  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitVersionIdentMetadata)
921  EmitVersionIdentMetadata();
922 
923  if (!getCodeGenOpts().RecordCommandLine.empty())
924  EmitCommandLineMetadata();
925 
926  if (!getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuard.empty())
927  getModule().setStackProtectorGuard(getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuard);
928  if (!getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardReg.empty())
929  getModule().setStackProtectorGuardReg(
930  getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardReg);
931  if (getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardOffset != INT_MAX)
932  getModule().setStackProtectorGuardOffset(
933  getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardOffset);
934  if (getCodeGenOpts().StackAlignment)
935  getModule().setOverrideStackAlignment(getCodeGenOpts().StackAlignment);
936  if (getCodeGenOpts().SkipRaxSetup)
937  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "SkipRaxSetup", 1);
938 
939  getTargetCodeGenInfo().emitTargetMetadata(*this, MangledDeclNames);
940 
941  EmitBackendOptionsMetadata(getCodeGenOpts());
942 
943  // If there is device offloading code embed it in the host now.
944  EmbedObject(&getModule(), CodeGenOpts, getDiags());
945 
946  // Set visibility from DLL storage class
947  // We do this at the end of LLVM IR generation; after any operation
948  // that might affect the DLL storage class or the visibility, and
949  // before anything that might act on these.
950  setVisibilityFromDLLStorageClass(LangOpts, getModule());
951 }
952 
953 void CodeGenModule::EmitOpenCLMetadata() {
954  // SPIR v2.0 s2.13 - The OpenCL version used by the module is stored in the
955  // opencl.ocl.version named metadata node.
956  // C++ for OpenCL has a distinct mapping for versions compatibile with OpenCL.
957  auto Version = LangOpts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion();
958  llvm::Metadata *OCLVerElts[] = {
959  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
960  Int32Ty, Version / 100)),
961  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
962  Int32Ty, (Version % 100) / 10))};
963  llvm::NamedMDNode *OCLVerMD =
964  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("opencl.ocl.version");
965  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
966  OCLVerMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, OCLVerElts));
967 }
968 
969 void CodeGenModule::EmitBackendOptionsMetadata(
970  const CodeGenOptions CodeGenOpts) {
971  switch (getTriple().getArch()) {
972  default:
973  break;
974  case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
975  case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
976  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "SmallDataLimit",
977  CodeGenOpts.SmallDataLimit);
978  break;
979  }
980 }

990 }

998 TBAAAccessInfo CodeGenModule::getTBAAAccessInfo(QualType AccessType) {
999  if (!TBAA)
1000  return TBAAAccessInfo();
1001  if (getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
1002  // As CUDA builtin surface/texture types are replaced, skip generating TBAA
1003  // access info.
1004  if (AccessType->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType()) {
1005  if (getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceDeviceType() !=
1006  nullptr)
1007  return TBAAAccessInfo();
1008  } else if (AccessType->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType()) {
1009  if (getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureDeviceType() !=
1010  nullptr)
1011  return TBAAAccessInfo();
1012  }
1013  }
1014  return TBAA->getAccessInfo(AccessType);
1015 }

1077 void CodeGenModule::Error(SourceLocation loc, StringRef message) {

1079  getDiags().Report(Context.getFullLoc(loc), diagID) << message;
1080 }

1082 /// ErrorUnsupported - Print out an error that codegen doesn't support the
1083 /// specified stmt yet.
1084 void CodeGenModule::ErrorUnsupported(const Stmt *S, const char *Type) {
1085  unsigned DiagID = getDiags().getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
1086  "cannot compile this %0 yet");
1087  std::string Msg = Type;
1088  getDiags().Report(Context.getFullLoc(S->getBeginLoc()), DiagID)
1089  << Msg << S->getSourceRange();
1090 }

1092 /// ErrorUnsupported - Print out an error that codegen doesn't support the

1095  unsigned DiagID = getDiags().getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
1096  "cannot compile this %0 yet");
1097  std::string Msg = Type;
1098  getDiags().Report(Context.getFullLoc(D->getLocation()), DiagID) << Msg;
1099 }

1104 
1105 void CodeGenModule::setGlobalVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
1106  const NamedDecl *D) const {
1107  if (GV->hasDLLImportStorageClass())
1108  return;
1109  // Internal definitions always have default visibility.
1110  if (GV->hasLocalLinkage()) {
1111  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
1112  return;
1113  }
1114  if (!D)
1115  return;
1116  // Set visibility for definitions, and for declarations if requested globally
1117  // or set explicitly.
1118  LinkageInfo LV = D->getLinkageAndVisibility();
1119  if (LV.isVisibilityExplicit() || getLangOpts().SetVisibilityForExternDecls ||
1120  !GV->isDeclarationForLinker())
1121  GV->setVisibility(GetLLVMVisibility(LV.getVisibility()));
1122 }
1123 
1124 static bool shouldAssumeDSOLocal(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1125  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
1126  if (GV->hasLocalLinkage())
1127  return true;
1128 
1129  if (!GV->hasDefaultVisibility() && !GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1130  return true;
1131 
1132  // DLLImport explicitly marks the GV as external.
1133  if (GV->hasDLLImportStorageClass())
1134  return false;
1135 
1136  const llvm::Triple &TT = CGM.getTriple();
1137  if (TT.isWindowsGNUEnvironment()) {
1138  // In MinGW, variables without DLLImport can still be automatically
1139  // imported from a DLL by the linker; don't mark variables that
1140  // potentially could come from another DLL as DSO local.
1141 
1142  // With EmulatedTLS, TLS variables can be autoimported from other DLLs
1143  // (and this actually happens in the public interface of libstdc++), so
1144  // such variables can't be marked as DSO local. (Native TLS variables
1145  // can't be dllimported at all, though.)
1146  if (GV->isDeclarationForLinker() && isa<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV) &&
1147  (!GV->isThreadLocal() || CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmulatedTLS))
1148  return false;
1149  }
1150 
1151  // On COFF, don't mark 'extern_weak' symbols as DSO local. If these symbols
1152  // remain unresolved in the link, they can be resolved to zero, which is
1153  // outside the current DSO.
1154  if (TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF() && GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1155  return false;
1156 
1157  // Every other GV is local on COFF.
1158  // Make an exception for windows OS in the triple: Some firmware builds use
1159  // *-win32-macho triples. This (accidentally?) produced windows relocations
1160  // without GOT tables in older clang versions; Keep this behaviour.
1161  // FIXME: even thread local variables?
1162  if (TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF() || (TT.isOSWindows() && TT.isOSBinFormatMachO()))
1163  return true;
1164 
1165  // Only handle COFF and ELF for now.
1166  if (!TT.isOSBinFormatELF())
1167  return false;
1168 
1169  // If this is not an executable, don't assume anything is local.
1170  const auto &CGOpts = CGM.getCodeGenOpts();
1171  llvm::Reloc::Model RM = CGOpts.RelocationModel;
1172  const auto &LOpts = CGM.getLangOpts();
1173  if (RM != llvm::Reloc::Static && !LOpts.PIE) {
1174  // On ELF, if -fno-semantic-interposition is specified and the target
1175  // supports local aliases, there will be neither CC1
1176  // -fsemantic-interposition nor -fhalf-no-semantic-interposition. Set
1177  // dso_local on the function if using a local alias is preferable (can avoid
1178  // PLT indirection).
1179  if (!(isa<llvm::Function>(GV) && GV->canBenefitFromLocalAlias()))
1180  return false;
1181  return !(CGM.getLangOpts().SemanticInterposition ||
1182  CGM.getLangOpts().HalfNoSemanticInterposition);
1183  }
1184 
1185  // A definition cannot be preempted from an executable.
1186  if (!GV->isDeclarationForLinker())
1187  return true;
1188 
1189  // Most PIC code sequences that assume that a symbol is local cannot produce a
1190  // 0 if it turns out the symbol is undefined. While this is ABI and relocation
1191  // depended, it seems worth it to handle it here.
1192  if (RM == llvm::Reloc::PIC_ && GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1193  return false;
1194 
1195  // PowerPC64 prefers TOC indirection to avoid copy relocations.
1196  if (TT.isPPC64())
1197  return false;
1198 
1199  if (CGOpts.DirectAccessExternalData) {
1200  // If -fdirect-access-external-data (default for -fno-pic), set dso_local
1201  // for non-thread-local variables. If the symbol is not defined in the
1202  // executable, a copy relocation will be needed at link time. dso_local is
1203  // excluded for thread-local variables because they generally don't support
1204  // copy relocations.
1205  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV))
1206  if (!Var->isThreadLocal())
1207  return true;
1208 
1209  // -fno-pic sets dso_local on a function declaration to allow direct
1210  // accesses when taking its address (similar to a data symbol). If the
1211  // function is not defined in the executable, a canonical PLT entry will be
1212  // needed at link time. -fno-direct-access-external-data can avoid the
1213  // canonical PLT entry. We don't generalize this condition to -fpie/-fpic as
1214  // it could just cause trouble without providing perceptible benefits.
1215  if (isa<llvm::Function>(GV) && !CGOpts.NoPLT && RM == llvm::Reloc::Static)
1216  return true;
1217  }
1218 
1219  // If we can use copy relocations we can assume it is local.
1220 
1221  // Otherwise don't assume it is local.
1222  return false;
1223 }
1224 
1225 void CodeGenModule::setDSOLocal(llvm::GlobalValue *GV) const {
1226  GV->setDSOLocal(shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*this, GV));
1227 }

1233  if (const auto *Dtor = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)) {
1234  getCXXABI().setCXXDestructorDLLStorage(GV, Dtor, GD.getDtorType());
1235  return;
1236  }
1237  setDLLImportDLLExport(GV, D);
1238 }

1269 static llvm::GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode GetLLVMTLSModel(StringRef S) {
1270  return llvm::StringSwitch<llvm::GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode>(S)
1271  .Case("global-dynamic", llvm::GlobalVariable::GeneralDynamicTLSModel)
1272  .Case("local-dynamic", llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalDynamicTLSModel)
1273  .Case("initial-exec", llvm::GlobalVariable::InitialExecTLSModel)
1274  .Case("local-exec", llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalExecTLSModel);
1275 }
1276 
1277 llvm::GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode
1278 CodeGenModule::GetDefaultLLVMTLSModel() const {
1279  switch (CodeGenOpts.getDefaultTLSModel()) {
1280  case CodeGenOptions::GeneralDynamicTLSModel:
1281  return llvm::GlobalVariable::GeneralDynamicTLSModel;
1282  case CodeGenOptions::LocalDynamicTLSModel:
1283  return llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalDynamicTLSModel;
1284  case CodeGenOptions::InitialExecTLSModel:
1285  return llvm::GlobalVariable::InitialExecTLSModel;
1286  case CodeGenOptions::LocalExecTLSModel:
1287  return llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalExecTLSModel;
1288  }
1289  llvm_unreachable("Invalid TLS model!");
1290 }

1292 void CodeGenModule::setTLSMode(llvm::GlobalValue *GV, const VarDecl &D) const {
1293  assert(D.getTLSKind() && "setting TLS mode on non-TLS var!");
1294 
1295  llvm::GlobalValue::ThreadLocalMode TLM;
1296  TLM = GetDefaultLLVMTLSModel();
1297 
1298  // Override the TLS model if it is explicitly specified.
1299  if (const TLSModelAttr *Attr = D.getAttr<TLSModelAttr>()) {
1300  TLM = GetLLVMTLSModel(Attr->getModel());
1301  }
1302 
1303  GV->setThreadLocalMode(TLM);
1304 }

1306 static std::string getCPUSpecificMangling(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1307  StringRef Name) {
1308  const TargetInfo &Target = CGM.getTarget();
1309  return (Twine('.') + Twine(Target.CPUSpecificManglingCharacter(Name))).str();
1310 }
1311 
1312 static void AppendCPUSpecificCPUDispatchMangling(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1313  const CPUSpecificAttr *Attr,
1314  unsigned CPUIndex,
1315  raw_ostream &Out) {
1316  // cpu_specific gets the current name, dispatch gets the resolver if IFunc is
1317  // supported.
1318  if (Attr)
1319  Out << getCPUSpecificMangling(CGM, Attr->getCPUName(CPUIndex)->getName());
1320  else if (CGM.getTarget().supportsIFunc())
1321  Out << ".resolver";
1322 }
1323 
1324 static void AppendTargetMangling(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1325  const TargetAttr *Attr, raw_ostream &Out) {
1326  if (Attr->isDefaultVersion())
1327  return;
1328 
1329  Out << '.';
1330  const TargetInfo &Target = CGM.getTarget();
1331  ParsedTargetAttr Info =
1332  Attr->parse([&Target](StringRef LHS, StringRef RHS) {
1333  // Multiversioning doesn't allow "no-${feature}", so we can
1334  // only have "+" prefixes here.
1335  assert(LHS.startswith("+") && RHS.startswith("+") &&
1336  "Features should always have a prefix.");
1337  return Target.multiVersionSortPriority(LHS.substr(1)) >
1338  Target.multiVersionSortPriority(RHS.substr(1));
1339  });
1340 
1341  bool IsFirst = true;
1342 
1343  if (!Info.Architecture.empty()) {
1344  IsFirst = false;
1345  Out << "arch_" << Info.Architecture;
1346  }
1347 
1348  for (StringRef Feat : Info.Features) {
1349  if (!IsFirst)
1350  Out << '_';
1351  IsFirst = false;
1352  Out << Feat.substr(1);
1353  }
1354 }
1355 
1356 // Returns true if GD is a function decl with internal linkage and
1357 // needs a unique suffix after the mangled name.
1358 static bool isUniqueInternalLinkageDecl(GlobalDecl GD,
1359  CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1360  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
1361  return !CGM.getModuleNameHash().empty() && isa<FunctionDecl>(D) &&
1362  (CGM.getFunctionLinkage(GD) == llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
1363 }
1364 
1365 static void AppendTargetClonesMangling(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1366  const TargetClonesAttr *Attr,
1367  unsigned VersionIndex,
1368  raw_ostream &Out) {
1369  Out << '.';
1370  StringRef FeatureStr = Attr->getFeatureStr(VersionIndex);
1371  if (FeatureStr.startswith("arch="))
1372  Out << "arch_" << FeatureStr.substr(sizeof("arch=") - 1);
1373  else
1374  Out << FeatureStr;
1375 
1376  Out << '.' << Attr->getMangledIndex(VersionIndex);
1377 }
1378 
1379 static std::string getMangledNameImpl(CodeGenModule &CGM, GlobalDecl GD,
1380  const NamedDecl *ND,
1381  bool OmitMultiVersionMangling = false) {
1382  SmallString<256> Buffer;
1383  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
1384  MangleContext &MC = CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext();
1385  if (!CGM.getModuleNameHash().empty())
1386  MC.needsUniqueInternalLinkageNames();
1387  bool ShouldMangle = MC.shouldMangleDeclName(ND);
1388  if (ShouldMangle)
1389  MC.mangleName(GD.getWithDecl(ND), Out);
1390  else {
1391  IdentifierInfo *II = ND->getIdentifier();
1392  assert(II && "Attempt to mangle unnamed decl.");
1393  const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND);
1394 
1395  if (FD &&
1396  FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getCallConv() == CC_X86RegCall) {
1397  Out << "__regcall3__" << II->getName();
1398  } else if (FD && FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() &&
1399  GD.getKernelReferenceKind() == KernelReferenceKind::Stub) {
1400  Out << "__device_stub__" << II->getName();
1401  } else {
1402  Out << II->getName();
1403  }
1404  }
1405 
1406  // Check if the module name hash should be appended for internal linkage
1407  // symbols. This should come before multi-version target suffixes are
1408  // appended. This is to keep the name and module hash suffix of the
1409  // internal linkage function together. The unique suffix should only be
1410  // added when name mangling is done to make sure that the final name can
1411  // be properly demangled. For example, for C functions without prototypes,
1412  // name mangling is not done and the unique suffix should not be appeneded
1413  // then.
1414  if (ShouldMangle && isUniqueInternalLinkageDecl(GD, CGM)) {
1415  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().UniqueInternalLinkageNames &&
1416  "Hash computed when not explicitly requested");
1417  Out << CGM.getModuleNameHash();
1418  }
1419 
1420  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND))
1421  if (FD->isMultiVersion() && !OmitMultiVersionMangling) {
1422  switch (FD->getMultiVersionKind()) {
1423  case MultiVersionKind::CPUDispatch:
1424  case MultiVersionKind::CPUSpecific:
1425  AppendCPUSpecificCPUDispatchMangling(CGM,
1426  FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>(),
1427  GD.getMultiVersionIndex(), Out);
1428  break;
1429  case MultiVersionKind::Target:
1430  AppendTargetMangling(CGM, FD->getAttr<TargetAttr>(), Out);
1431  break;
1432  case MultiVersionKind::TargetClones:
1433  AppendTargetClonesMangling(CGM, FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>(),
1434  GD.getMultiVersionIndex(), Out);
1435  break;
1436  case MultiVersionKind::None:
1437  llvm_unreachable("None multiversion type isn't valid here");
1438  }
1439  }
1440 
1441  // Make unique name for device side static file-scope variable for HIP.
1442  if (CGM.getContext().shouldExternalizeStaticVar(ND) &&
1443  CGM.getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode &&
1444  CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && !CGM.getLangOpts().CUID.empty())
1445  CGM.printPostfixForExternalizedStaticVar(Out);
1446  return std::string(Out.str());
1447 }
1448 
1449 void CodeGenModule::UpdateMultiVersionNames(GlobalDecl GD,
1450  const FunctionDecl *FD,
1451  StringRef &CurName) {
1452  if (!FD->isMultiVersion())
1453  return;
1454 
1455  // Get the name of what this would be without the 'target' attribute. This
1456  // allows us to lookup the version that was emitted when this wasn't a
1457  // multiversion function.
1458  std::string NonTargetName =
1459  getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
1460  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
1461  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(NonTargetName, OtherGD)) {
1462  assert(OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl()
1463  .getDecl()
1464  ->getAsFunction()
1465  ->isMultiVersion() &&
1466  "Other GD should now be a multiversioned function");
1467  // OtherFD is the version of this function that was mangled BEFORE
1468  // becoming a MultiVersion function. It potentially needs to be updated.
1469  const FunctionDecl *OtherFD = OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl()
1470  .getDecl()
1471  ->getAsFunction()
1472  ->getMostRecentDecl();
1473  std::string OtherName = getMangledNameImpl(*this, OtherGD, OtherFD);
1474  // This is so that if the initial version was already the 'default'
1475  // version, we don't try to update it.
1476  if (OtherName != NonTargetName) {
1477  // Remove instead of erase, since others may have stored the StringRef
1478  // to this.
1479  const auto ExistingRecord = Manglings.find(NonTargetName);
1480  if (ExistingRecord != std::end(Manglings))
1481  Manglings.remove(&(*ExistingRecord));
1482  auto Result = Manglings.insert(std::make_pair(OtherName, OtherGD));
1483  StringRef OtherNameRef = MangledDeclNames[OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl()] =
1484  Result.first->first();
1485  // If this is the current decl is being created, make sure we update the name.
1486  if (GD.getCanonicalDecl() == OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl())
1487  CurName = OtherNameRef;
1488  if (llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(NonTargetName))
1489  Entry->setName(OtherName);
1490  }
1491  }
1492 }
1493 
1494 StringRef CodeGenModule::getMangledName(GlobalDecl GD) {
1495  GlobalDecl CanonicalGD = GD.getCanonicalDecl();
1496 
1497  // Some ABIs don't have constructor variants. Make sure that base and
1498  // complete constructors get mangled the same.
1499  if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(CanonicalGD.getDecl())) {
1500  if (!getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants()) {
1501  CXXCtorType OrigCtorType = GD.getCtorType();
1502  assert(OrigCtorType == Ctor_Base || OrigCtorType == Ctor_Complete);
1503  if (OrigCtorType == Ctor_Base)
1504  CanonicalGD = GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete);
1505  }
1506  }
1507 
1508  // In CUDA/HIP device compilation with -fgpu-rdc, the mangled name of a
1509  // static device variable depends on whether the variable is referenced by
1510  // a host or device host function. Therefore the mangled name cannot be
1511  // cached.
1512  if (!LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice ||
1513  !getContext().mayExternalizeStaticVar(GD.getDecl())) {
1514  auto FoundName = MangledDeclNames.find(CanonicalGD);
1515  if (FoundName != MangledDeclNames.end())
1516  return FoundName->second;
1517  }
1518 
1519  // Keep the first result in the case of a mangling collision.
1520  const auto *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1521  std::string MangledName = getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, ND);
1522 
1523  // Ensure either we have different ABIs between host and device compilations,
1524  // says host compilation following MSVC ABI but device compilation follows
1525  // Itanium C++ ABI or, if they follow the same ABI, kernel names after
1526  // mangling should be the same after name stubbing. The later checking is
1527  // very important as the device kernel name being mangled in host-compilation
1528  // is used to resolve the device binaries to be executed. Inconsistent naming
1529  // result in undefined behavior. Even though we cannot check that naming
1530  // directly between host- and device-compilations, the host- and
1531  // device-mangling in host compilation could help catching certain ones.
1532  assert(!isa<FunctionDecl>(ND) || !ND->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() ||
1533  getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice ||
1534  (getContext().getAuxTargetInfo() &&
1535  (getContext().getAuxTargetInfo()->getCXXABI() !=
1536  getContext().getTargetInfo().getCXXABI())) ||
1537  getCUDARuntime().getDeviceSideName(ND) ==
1538  getMangledNameImpl(
1539  *this,
1540  GD.getWithKernelReferenceKind(KernelReferenceKind::Kernel),
1541  ND));
1542 
1543  auto Result = Manglings.insert(std::make_pair(MangledName, GD));
1544  return MangledDeclNames[CanonicalGD] = Result.first->first();
1545 }
1546 
1547 StringRef CodeGenModule::getBlockMangledName(GlobalDecl GD,
1548  const BlockDecl *BD) {
1549  MangleContext &MangleCtx = getCXXABI().getMangleContext();
1550  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
1551 
1552  SmallString<256> Buffer;
1553  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
1554  if (!D)
1555  MangleCtx.mangleGlobalBlock(BD,
1556  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(initializedGlobalDecl.getDecl()), Out);
1557  else if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D))
1558  MangleCtx.mangleCtorBlock(CD, GD.getCtorType(), BD, Out);
1559  else if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D))
1560  MangleCtx.mangleDtorBlock(DD, GD.getDtorType(), BD, Out);
1561  else
1562  MangleCtx.mangleBlock(cast<DeclContext>(D), BD, Out);
1563 
1564  auto Result = Manglings.insert(std::make_pair(Out.str(), BD));
1565  return Result.first->first();
1566 }

1569  return getModule().getNamedValue(Name);
1570 }
