1580 /// AddGlobalDtor - Add a function to the list that will be called
1581 /// when the module is unloaded.
1582 void CodeGenModule::AddGlobalDtor(llvm::Function *Dtor, int Priority,
1583  bool IsDtorAttrFunc) {
1584  if (CodeGenOpts.RegisterGlobalDtorsWithAtExit &&
1585  (!getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSAIX() || IsDtorAttrFunc)) {
1586  DtorsUsingAtExit[Priority].push_back(Dtor);
1587  return;
1588  }
1589 
1590  // FIXME: Type coercion of void()* types.
1591  GlobalDtors.push_back(Structor(Priority, Dtor, nullptr));
1592 }
1593 
1594 void CodeGenModule::EmitCtorList(CtorList &Fns, const char *GlobalName) {
1595  if (Fns.empty()) return;
1596 
1597  // Ctor function type is void()*.
1598  llvm::FunctionType* CtorFTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, false);
1599  llvm::Type *CtorPFTy = llvm::PointerType::get(CtorFTy,
1600  TheModule.getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace());
1601  llvm::PointerType *TargetType = VoidPtrTy;
1602  // Get target type when templated global variables are used,
1603  // to emit them correctly in the target (default) address space and avoid
1604  // emitting them in a private address space.
1605  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
1606  TargetType = llvm::IntegerType::getInt8PtrTy(
1607  getLLVMContext(), getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default));
1608 
1609  // Get the type of a ctor entry, { i32, void ()*, i8* }.
1610  llvm::StructType *CtorStructTy =
1611  llvm::StructType::get(Int32Ty, CtorPFTy, TargetType);
1612 
1613  // Construct the constructor and destructor arrays.
1614  ConstantInitBuilder builder(*this);
1615  auto ctors = builder.beginArray(CtorStructTy);
1616  for (const auto &I : Fns) {
1617  auto ctor = ctors.beginStruct(CtorStructTy);
1618  ctor.addInt(Int32Ty, I.Priority);
1619  ctor.add(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(I.Initializer, CtorPFTy));
1620  // Emit appropriate bitcasts for pointers of different address spaces.
1621  if (I.AssociatedData)
1622  ctor.add(llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
1623  I.AssociatedData, TargetType));
1624  else
1625  ctor.addNullPointer(TargetType);
1626  ctor.finishAndAddTo(ctors);
1627  }
1628 
1629  auto list =
1630  ctors.finishAndCreateGlobal(GlobalName, getPointerAlign(),
1631  /*constant*/ false,
1632  llvm::GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage);
1633 
1634  // The LTO linker doesn't seem to like it when we set an alignment
1635  // on appending variables. Take it off as a workaround.
1636  list->setAlignment(llvm::None);
1637 
1638  Fns.clear();
1639 }
1640 
1641 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes
1642 CodeGenModule::getFunctionLinkage(GlobalDecl GD) {
1643  const auto *D = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1644 
1645  GVALinkage Linkage = getContext().GetGVALinkageForFunction(D);
1646 
1647  if (const auto *Dtor = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D))
1648  return getCXXABI().getCXXDestructorLinkage(Linkage, Dtor, GD.getDtorType());
1649 
1650  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(D) &&
1651  cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D)->isInheritingConstructor() &&
1652  Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
1653  // Our approach to inheriting constructors is fundamentally different from
1654  // that used by the MS ABI, so keep our inheriting constructor thunks
1655  // internal rather than trying to pick an unambiguous mangling for them.
1656  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
1657  }
1658 
1659  return getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(D, Linkage, /*IsConstantVariable=*/false);
1660 }
1661 
1662 llvm::ConstantInt *CodeGenModule::CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(llvm::Metadata *MD) {
1663  llvm::MDString *MDS = dyn_cast<llvm::MDString>(MD);
1664  if (!MDS) return nullptr;
1665 
1666  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, llvm::MD5Hash(MDS->getString()));
1667 }
1668 
1669 void CodeGenModule::SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
1670  const CGFunctionInfo &Info,
1671  llvm::Function *F, bool IsThunk) {
1672  unsigned CallingConv;
1673  llvm::AttributeList PAL;
1674  ConstructAttributeList(F->getName(), Info, GD, PAL, CallingConv,
1675  /*AttrOnCallSite=*/false, IsThunk);
1676  F->setAttributes(PAL);
1677  F->setCallingConv(static_cast<llvm::CallingConv::ID>(CallingConv));
1678 }
1679 
1680 static void removeImageAccessQualifier(std::string& TyName) {
1681  std::string ReadOnlyQual("__read_only");
1682  std::string::size_type ReadOnlyPos = TyName.find(ReadOnlyQual);
1683  if (ReadOnlyPos != std::string::npos)
1684  // "+ 1" for the space after access qualifier.
1685  TyName.erase(ReadOnlyPos, ReadOnlyQual.size() + 1);
1686  else {
1687  std::string WriteOnlyQual("__write_only");
1688  std::string::size_type WriteOnlyPos = TyName.find(WriteOnlyQual);
1689  if (WriteOnlyPos != std::string::npos)
1690  TyName.erase(WriteOnlyPos, WriteOnlyQual.size() + 1);
1691  else {
1692  std::string ReadWriteQual("__read_write");
1693  std::string::size_type ReadWritePos = TyName.find(ReadWriteQual);
1694  if (ReadWritePos != std::string::npos)
1695  TyName.erase(ReadWritePos, ReadWriteQual.size() + 1);
1696  }
1697  }
1698 }
1699 
1700 // Returns the address space id that should be produced to the
1701 // kernel_arg_addr_space metadata. This is always fixed to the ids
1702 // as specified in the SPIR 2.0 specification in order to differentiate
1703 // for example in clGetKernelArgInfo() implementation between the address
1704 // spaces with targets without unique mapping to the OpenCL address spaces
1705 // (basically all single AS CPUs).
1706 static unsigned ArgInfoAddressSpace(LangAS AS) {
1707  switch (AS) {
1708  case LangAS::opencl_global:
1709  case LangAS::sycl_global:
1710  return 1;
1711  case LangAS::opencl_constant:
1712  return 2;
1713  case LangAS::opencl_local:
1714  case LangAS::sycl_local:
1715  return 3;
1716  case LangAS::opencl_generic:
1717  return 4; // Not in SPIR 2.0 specs.
1718  case LangAS::opencl_global_device:
1719  case LangAS::sycl_global_device:
1720  return 5;
1721  case LangAS::opencl_global_host:
1722  case LangAS::sycl_global_host:
1723  return 6;
1724  default:
1725  return 0; // Assume private.
1726  }
1727 }
1728 
1729 void CodeGenModule::GenOpenCLArgMetadata(llvm::Function *Fn,
1730  const FunctionDecl *FD,
1731  CodeGenFunction *CGF) {
1732  assert(((FD && CGF) || (!FD && !CGF)) &&
1733  "Incorrect use - FD and CGF should either be both null or not!");
1734  // Create MDNodes that represent the kernel arg metadata.
1735  // Each MDNode is a list in the form of "key", N number of values which is
1736  // the same number of values as their are kernel arguments.
1737 
1738  const PrintingPolicy &Policy = Context.getPrintingPolicy();
1739 
1740  // MDNode for the kernel argument address space qualifiers.
1741  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> addressQuals;
1742 
1743  // MDNode for the kernel argument access qualifiers (images only).
1744  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> accessQuals;
1745 
1746  // MDNode for the kernel argument type names.
1747  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argTypeNames;
1748 
1749  // MDNode for the kernel argument base type names.
1750  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argBaseTypeNames;
1751 
1752  // MDNode for the kernel argument type qualifiers.
1753  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argTypeQuals;
1754 
1755  // MDNode for the kernel argument names.
1756  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argNames;
1757 
1758  // MDNode for the intel_buffer_location attribute.
1759  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argSYCLBufferLocationAttr;
1760 
1761  // MDNode for listing SYCL kernel pointer arguments originating from
1762  // accessors.
1763  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argSYCLKernelRuntimeAligned;
1764 
1765  // MDNode for listing ESIMD kernel pointer arguments originating from
1766  // accessors.
1767  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argESIMDAccPtrs;
1768 
1769  bool isKernelArgAnAccessor = false;
1770 
1771  if (FD && CGF)
1772  for (unsigned i = 0, e = FD->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i) {
1773  const ParmVarDecl *parm = FD->getParamDecl(i);
1774  QualType ty = parm->getType();
1775  std::string typeQuals;
1776 
1777  // Get image and pipe access qualifier:
1778  if (ty->isImageType() || ty->isPipeType()) {
1779  const Decl *PDecl = parm;
1780  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(ty))
1781  PDecl = TD->getDecl();
1782  const OpenCLAccessAttr *A = PDecl->getAttr<OpenCLAccessAttr>();
1783  if (A && A->isWriteOnly())
1784  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "write_only"));
1785  else if (A && A->isReadWrite())
1786  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "read_write"));
1787  else
1788  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "read_only"));
1789  } else
1790  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "none"));
1791 
1792  // Get argument name.
1793  argNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, parm->getName()));
1794 
1795  auto getTypeSpelling = [&](QualType Ty) {
1796  auto typeName = Ty.getUnqualifiedType().getAsString(Policy);
1797 
1798  if (Ty.isCanonical()) {
1799  StringRef typeNameRef = typeName;
1800  // Turn "unsigned type" to "utype"
1801  if (typeNameRef.consume_front("unsigned "))
1802  return std::string("u") + typeNameRef.str();
1803  if (typeNameRef.consume_front("signed "))
1804  return typeNameRef.str();
1805  }
1806 
1807  return typeName;
1808  };
1809 
1810  if (ty->isPointerType()) {
1811  QualType pointeeTy = ty->getPointeeType();
1812 
1813  // Get address qualifier.
1814  addressQuals.push_back(
1815  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(
1816  ArgInfoAddressSpace(pointeeTy.getAddressSpace()))));
1817 
1818  // Get argument type name.
1819  std::string typeName = getTypeSpelling(pointeeTy) + "*";
1820  std::string baseTypeName =
1821  getTypeSpelling(pointeeTy.getCanonicalType()) + "*";
1822  argTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, typeName));
1823  argBaseTypeNames.push_back(
1824  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, baseTypeName));
1825 
1826  // Get argument type qualifiers:
1827  if (ty.isRestrictQualified())
1828  typeQuals = "restrict";
1829  if (pointeeTy.isConstQualified() ||
1830  (pointeeTy.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_constant))
1831  typeQuals += typeQuals.empty() ? "const" : " const";
1832  if (pointeeTy.isVolatileQualified())
1833  typeQuals += typeQuals.empty() ? "volatile" : " volatile";
1834  } else {
1835  uint32_t AddrSpc = 0;
1836  bool isPipe = ty->isPipeType();
1837  if (ty->isImageType() || isPipe)
1838  AddrSpc = ArgInfoAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global);
1839 
1840  addressQuals.push_back(
1841  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(AddrSpc)));
1842 
1843  // Get argument type name.
1844  ty = isPipe ? ty->castAs<PipeType>()->getElementType() : ty;
1845  std::string typeName = getTypeSpelling(ty);
1846  std::string baseTypeName = getTypeSpelling(ty.getCanonicalType());
1847 
1848  // Remove access qualifiers on images
1849  // (as they are inseparable from type in clang implementation,
1850  // but OpenCL spec provides a special query to get access qualifier
1851  // via clGetKernelArgInfo with CL_KERNEL_ARG_ACCESS_QUALIFIER):
1852  if (ty->isImageType()) {
1853  removeImageAccessQualifier(typeName);
1854  removeImageAccessQualifier(baseTypeName);
1855  }
1856 
1857  argTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, typeName));
1858  argBaseTypeNames.push_back(
1859  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, baseTypeName));
1860 
1861  if (isPipe)
1862  typeQuals = "pipe";
1863  }
1864  argTypeQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, typeQuals));
1865 
1866  auto *SYCLBufferLocationAttr =
1867  parm->getAttr<SYCLIntelBufferLocationAttr>();
1868  argSYCLBufferLocationAttr.push_back(
1869  (SYCLBufferLocationAttr)
1870  ? llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(
1871  SYCLBufferLocationAttr->getLocationID()))
1872  : llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(-1)));
1873 
1874  // If a kernel pointer argument comes from an accessor, we generate
1875  // a new metadata(kernel_arg_runtime_aligned) to the kernel to indicate
1876  // that this pointer has runtime allocated alignment. The value of any
1877  // "kernel_arg_runtime_aligned" metadata element is 'true' for any kernel
1878  // arguments that corresponds to the base pointer of an accessor and
1879  // 'false' otherwise.
1880  if (parm->hasAttr<SYCLAccessorPtrAttr>()) {
1881  isKernelArgAnAccessor = true;
1882  argSYCLKernelRuntimeAligned.push_back(
1883  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getTrue()));
1884  } else {
1885  argSYCLKernelRuntimeAligned.push_back(
1886  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getFalse()));
1887  }
1888 
1889  if (FD->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>())
1890  argESIMDAccPtrs.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(
1891  CGF->Builder.getInt1(parm->hasAttr<SYCLAccessorPtrAttr>())));
1892  }
1893 
1894  bool IsEsimdFunction = FD && FD->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>();
1895 
1896  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && !IsEsimdFunction) {
1897  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_buffer_location",
1898  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argSYCLBufferLocationAttr));
1899  // Generate this metadata only if atleast one kernel argument is an
1900  // accessor.
1901  if (isKernelArgAnAccessor)
1902  Fn->setMetadata(
1903  "kernel_arg_runtime_aligned",
1904  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argSYCLKernelRuntimeAligned));
1905  } else {
1906  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_addr_space",
1907  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, addressQuals));
1908  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_access_qual",
1909  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, accessQuals));
1910  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type",
1911  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argTypeNames));
1912  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_base_type",
1913  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argBaseTypeNames));
1914  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type_qual",
1915  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argTypeQuals));
1916  if (IsEsimdFunction)
1917  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_accessor_ptr",
1918  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argESIMDAccPtrs));
1919  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitOpenCLArgMetadata)
1920  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_name",
1921  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argNames));
1922  }
1923 }
1924 
1925 /// Determines whether the language options require us to model
1926 /// unwind exceptions. We treat -fexceptions as mandating this
1927 /// except under the fragile ObjC ABI with only ObjC exceptions
1928 /// enabled. This means, for example, that C with -fexceptions
1929 /// enables this.
1930 static bool hasUnwindExceptions(const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
1931  // If exceptions are completely disabled, obviously this is false.
1932  if (!LangOpts.Exceptions) return false;
1933 
1934  // If C++ exceptions are enabled, this is true.
1935  if (LangOpts.CXXExceptions) return true;
1936 
1937  // If ObjC exceptions are enabled, this depends on the ABI.
1938  if (LangOpts.ObjCExceptions) {
1939  return LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.hasUnwindExceptions();
1940  }
1941 
1942  return true;
1943 }
1944 
1945 static bool requiresMemberFunctionPointerTypeMetadata(CodeGenModule &CGM,
1946  const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
1947  // Check that the type metadata can ever actually be used by a call.
1948  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().LTOUnit ||
1949  !CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(MD->getParent()))
1950  return false;
1951 
1952  // Only functions whose address can be taken with a member function pointer
1953  // need this sort of type metadata.
1954  return !MD->isStatic() && !MD->isVirtual() && !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) &&
1955  !isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD);
1956 }
1957 
1958 std::vector<const CXXRecordDecl *>
1959 CodeGenModule::getMostBaseClasses(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1960  llvm::SetVector<const CXXRecordDecl *> MostBases;
1961 
1962  std::function<void (const CXXRecordDecl *)> CollectMostBases;
1963  CollectMostBases = [&](const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1964  if (RD->getNumBases() == 0)
1965  MostBases.insert(RD);
1966  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &B : RD->bases())
1967  CollectMostBases(B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
1968  };
1969  CollectMostBases(RD);
1970  return MostBases.takeVector();
1971 }
1972 
1973 void CodeGenModule::SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(const Decl *D,
1974  llvm::Function *F) {
1975  llvm::AttrBuilder B(F->getContext());
1976 
1977  if (CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables)
1978  B.addUWTableAttr(llvm::UWTableKind(CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables));
1979 
1980  if (CodeGenOpts.StackClashProtector)
1981  B.addAttribute("probe-stack", "inline-asm");
1982 
1983  if (!hasUnwindExceptions(LangOpts))
1984  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
1985 
1986  if (!D || !D->hasAttr<NoStackProtectorAttr>()) {
1987  if (LangOpts.getStackProtector() == LangOptions::SSPOn)
1988  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtect);
1989  else if (LangOpts.getStackProtector() == LangOptions::SSPStrong)
1990  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtectStrong);
1991  else if (LangOpts.getStackProtector() == LangOptions::SSPReq)
1992  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtectReq);
1993  }
1994 
1995  if (!D) {
1996  // If we don't have a declaration to control inlining, the function isn't
1997  // explicitly marked as alwaysinline for semantic reasons, and inlining is
1998  // disabled, mark the function as noinline.
1999  if (!F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline) &&
2000  CodeGenOpts.getInlining() == CodeGenOptions::OnlyAlwaysInlining)
2001  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2002 
2003  F->addFnAttrs(B);
2004  return;
2005  }
2006 
2007  // Track whether we need to add the optnone LLVM attribute,
2008  // starting with the default for this optimization level.
2009  bool ShouldAddOptNone =
2010  !CodeGenOpts.DisableO0ImplyOptNone && CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel == 0;
2011  // We can't add optnone in the following cases, it won't pass the verifier.
2012  ShouldAddOptNone &= !D->hasAttr<MinSizeAttr>();
2013  ShouldAddOptNone &= !D->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>();
2014 
2015  // Add optnone, but do so only if the function isn't always_inline.
2016  if ((ShouldAddOptNone || D->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>()) &&
2017  !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline)) {
2018  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeNone);
2019 
2020  // OptimizeNone implies noinline; we should not be inlining such functions.
2021  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2022 
2023  // We still need to handle naked functions even though optnone subsumes
2024  // much of their semantics.
2025  if (D->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
2026  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Naked);
2027 
2028  // OptimizeNone wins over OptimizeForSize and MinSize.
2029  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
2030  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
2031  } else if (D->hasAttr<NakedAttr>()) {
2032  // Naked implies noinline: we should not be inlining such functions.
2033  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Naked);
2034  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2035  } else if (D->hasAttr<NoDuplicateAttr>()) {
2036  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoDuplicate);
2037  } else if (D->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>() && !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline)) {
2038  // Add noinline if the function isn't always_inline.
2039  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2040  } else if (D->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>() &&
2041  !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline)) {
2042  // (noinline wins over always_inline, and we can't specify both in IR)
2043  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
2044  } else if (CodeGenOpts.getInlining() == CodeGenOptions::OnlyAlwaysInlining) {
2045  // If we're not inlining, then force everything that isn't always_inline to
2046  // carry an explicit noinline attribute.
2047  if (!F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline))
2048  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2049  } else {
2050  // Otherwise, propagate the inline hint attribute and potentially use its
2051  // absence to mark things as noinline.
2052  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2053  // Search function and template pattern redeclarations for inline.
2054  auto CheckForInline = [](const FunctionDecl *FD) {
2055  auto CheckRedeclForInline = [](const FunctionDecl *Redecl) {
2056  return Redecl->isInlineSpecified();
2057  };
2058  if (any_of(FD->redecls(), CheckRedeclForInline))
2059  return true;
2060  const FunctionDecl *Pattern = FD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
2061  if (!Pattern)
2062  return false;
2063  return any_of(Pattern->redecls(), CheckRedeclForInline);
2064  };
2065  if (CheckForInline(FD)) {
2066  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InlineHint);
2067  } else if (CodeGenOpts.getInlining() ==
2068  CodeGenOptions::OnlyHintInlining &&
2069  !FD->isInlined() &&
2070  !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline)) {
2071  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2072  }
2073  }
2074  }
2075 
2076  // Add other optimization related attributes if we are optimizing this
2077  // function.
2078  if (!D->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>()) {
2079  if (D->hasAttr<ColdAttr>()) {
2080  if (!ShouldAddOptNone)
2081  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
2082  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Cold);
2083  }
2084  if (D->hasAttr<HotAttr>())
2085  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Hot);
2086  if (D->hasAttr<MinSizeAttr>())
2087  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
2088  }
2089 
2090  F->addFnAttrs(B);
2091 
2092  unsigned alignment = D->getMaxAlignment() / Context.getCharWidth();
2093  if (alignment)
2094  F->setAlignment(llvm::Align(alignment));
2095 
2096  if (!D->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>())
2097  if (LangOpts.FunctionAlignment)
2098  F->setAlignment(llvm::Align(1ull << LangOpts.FunctionAlignment));
2099 
2100  // Some C++ ABIs require 2-byte alignment for member functions, in order to
2101  // reserve a bit for differentiating between virtual and non-virtual member
2102  // functions. If the current target's C++ ABI requires this and this is a
2103  // member function, set its alignment accordingly.
2104  if (getTarget().getCXXABI().areMemberFunctionsAligned()) {
2105  if (F->getAlignment() < 2 && isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
2106  F->setAlignment(llvm::Align(2));
2107  }
2108 
2109  // In the cross-dso CFI mode with canonical jump tables, we want !type
2110  // attributes on definitions only.
2111  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso &&
2112  CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCanonicalJumpTables) {
2113  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2114  // Skip available_externally functions. They won't be codegen'ed in the
2115  // current module anyway.
2116  if (getContext().GetGVALinkageForFunction(FD) != GVA_AvailableExternally)
2117  CreateFunctionTypeMetadataForIcall(FD, F);
2118  }
2119  }
2120 
2121  // Emit type metadata on member functions for member function pointer checks.
2122  // These are only ever necessary on definitions; we're guaranteed that the
2123  // definition will be present in the LTO unit as a result of LTO visibility.
2124  auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D);
2125  if (MD && requiresMemberFunctionPointerTypeMetadata(*this, MD)) {
2126  for (const CXXRecordDecl *Base : getMostBaseClasses(MD->getParent())) {
2127  llvm::Metadata *Id =
2128  CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(Context.getMemberPointerType(
2129  MD->getType(), Context.getRecordType(Base).getTypePtr()));
2130  F->addTypeMetadata(0, Id);
2131  }
2132  }
2133 }
2134 
2135 void CodeGenModule::setLLVMFunctionFEnvAttributes(const FunctionDecl *D,
2136  llvm::Function *F) {
2137  if (D->hasAttr<StrictFPAttr>()) {
2138  llvm::AttrBuilder FuncAttrs(F->getContext());
2139  FuncAttrs.addAttribute("strictfp");
2140  F->addFnAttrs(FuncAttrs);
2141  }
2142 }
2143 
2144 void CodeGenModule::SetCommonAttributes(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
2145  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2146  if (isa_and_nonnull<NamedDecl>(D))
2147  setGVProperties(GV, GD);
2148  else
2149  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
2150 
2151  if (D && D->hasAttr<UsedAttr>())
2152  addUsedOrCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
2153 
2154  if (CodeGenOpts.KeepStaticConsts && D && isa<VarDecl>(D)) {
2155  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
2156  if (VD->getType().isConstQualified() &&
2157  VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static)
2158  addUsedOrCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
2159  }
2160 }
2161 
2162 bool CodeGenModule::GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
2163  llvm::AttrBuilder &Attrs) {
2164  // Add target-cpu and target-features attributes to functions. If
2165  // we have a decl for the function and it has a target attribute then
2166  // parse that and add it to the feature set.
2167  StringRef TargetCPU = getTarget().getTargetOpts().CPU;
2168  StringRef TuneCPU = getTarget().getTargetOpts().TuneCPU;
2169  std::vector<std::string> Features;
2170  const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2171  FD = FD ? FD->getMostRecentDecl() : FD;
2172  const auto *TD = FD ? FD->getAttr<TargetAttr>() : nullptr;
2173  const auto *SD = FD ? FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>() : nullptr;
2174  const auto *TC = FD ? FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>() : nullptr;
2175  bool AddedAttr = false;
2176  if (TD || SD || TC) {
2177  llvm::StringMap<bool> FeatureMap;
2178  getContext().getFunctionFeatureMap(FeatureMap, GD);
2179 
2180  // Produce the canonical string for this set of features.
2181  for (const llvm::StringMap<bool>::value_type &Entry : FeatureMap)
2182  Features.push_back((Entry.getValue() ? "+" : "-") + Entry.getKey().str());
2183 
2184  // Now add the target-cpu and target-features to the function.
2185  // While we populated the feature map above, we still need to
2186  // get and parse the target attribute so we can get the cpu for
2187  // the function.
2188  if (TD) {
2189  ParsedTargetAttr ParsedAttr = TD->parse();
2190  if (!ParsedAttr.Architecture.empty() &&
2191  getTarget().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttr.Architecture)) {
2192  TargetCPU = ParsedAttr.Architecture;
2193  TuneCPU = ""; // Clear the tune CPU.
2194  }
2195  if (!ParsedAttr.Tune.empty() &&
2196  getTarget().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttr.Tune))
2197  TuneCPU = ParsedAttr.Tune;
2198  }
2199 
2200  if (SD) {
2201  // Apply the given CPU name as the 'tune-cpu' so that the optimizer can
2202  // favor this processor.
2203  TuneCPU = getTarget().getCPUSpecificTuneName(
2204  SD->getCPUName(GD.getMultiVersionIndex())->getName());
2205  }
2206  } else {
2207  // Otherwise just add the existing target cpu and target features to the
2208  // function.
2209  Features = getTarget().getTargetOpts().Features;
2210  }
2211 
2212  if (!TargetCPU.empty()) {
2213  Attrs.addAttribute("target-cpu", TargetCPU);
2214  AddedAttr = true;
2215  }
2216  if (!TuneCPU.empty()) {
2217  Attrs.addAttribute("tune-cpu", TuneCPU);
2218  AddedAttr = true;
2219  }
2220  if (!Features.empty()) {
2221  llvm::sort(Features);
2222  Attrs.addAttribute("target-features", llvm::join(Features, ","));
2223  AddedAttr = true;
2224  }
2225 
2226  return AddedAttr;
2227 }
2228 
2229 void CodeGenModule::setNonAliasAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
2230  llvm::GlobalObject *GO) {
2231  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2232  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GO);
2233 
2234  if (D) {
2235  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GO)) {
2236  if (D->hasAttr<RetainAttr>())
2237  addUsedGlobal(GV);
2238  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangBSSSectionAttr>())
2239  GV->addAttribute("bss-section", SA->getName());
2240  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangDataSectionAttr>())
2241  GV->addAttribute("data-section", SA->getName());
2242  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangRodataSectionAttr>())
2243  GV->addAttribute("rodata-section", SA->getName());
2244  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangRelroSectionAttr>())
2245  GV->addAttribute("relro-section", SA->getName());
2246  }
2247 
2248  if (auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(GO)) {
2249  if (D->hasAttr<RetainAttr>())
2250  addUsedGlobal(F);
2251  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangTextSectionAttr>())
2252  if (!D->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
2253  F->addFnAttr("implicit-section-name", SA->getName());
2254 
2255  llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs(F->getContext());
2256  if (GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(GD, Attrs)) {
2257  // We know that GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes will always have the
2258  // newest set, since it has the newest possible FunctionDecl, so the
2259  // new ones should replace the old.
2260  llvm::AttributeMask RemoveAttrs;
2261  RemoveAttrs.addAttribute("target-cpu");
2262  RemoveAttrs.addAttribute("target-features");
2263  RemoveAttrs.addAttribute("tune-cpu");
2264  F->removeFnAttrs(RemoveAttrs);
2265  F->addFnAttrs(Attrs);
2266  }
2267  }
2268 
2269  if (const auto *CSA = D->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>())
2270  GO->setSection(CSA->getName());
2271  else if (const auto *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
2272  GO->setSection(SA->getName());
2273  }
2274 
2275  getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(D, GO, *this);
2276 }

2279  llvm::Function *F,
2280  const CGFunctionInfo &FI) {
2281  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2282  SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GD, FI, F, /*IsThunk=*/false);
2283  SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(D, F);
2284 
2285  F->setLinkage(llvm::Function::InternalLinkage);
2286 
2287  setNonAliasAttributes(GD, F);
2288 }

2290 static void setLinkageForGV(llvm::GlobalValue *GV, const NamedDecl *ND) {
2291  // Set linkage and visibility in case we never see a definition.
2292  LinkageInfo LV = ND->getLinkageAndVisibility();
2293  // Don't set internal linkage on declarations.
2294  // "extern_weak" is overloaded in LLVM; we probably should have
2295  // separate linkage types for this.
2296  if (isExternallyVisible(LV.getLinkage()) &&
2297  (ND->hasAttr<WeakAttr>() || ND->isWeakImported()))
2298  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage);
2299 }

2301 void CodeGenModule::CreateFunctionTypeMetadataForIcall(const FunctionDecl *FD,
2302  llvm::Function *F) {
2303  // Only if we are checking indirect calls.
2304  if (!LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall))
2305  return;
2306 
2307  // Non-static class methods are handled via vtable or member function pointer
2308  // checks elsewhere.
2309  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD) && !cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)->isStatic())
2310  return;
2311 
2312  llvm::Metadata *MD = CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(FD->getType());
2313  F->addTypeMetadata(0, MD);
2314  F->addTypeMetadata(0, CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(FD->getType()));
2315 
2316  // Emit a hash-based bit set entry for cross-DSO calls.
2317  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso)
2318  if (auto CrossDsoTypeId = CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD))
2319  F->addTypeMetadata(0, llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CrossDsoTypeId));
2320 }
2321 
2322 void CodeGenModule::SetFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::Function *F,
2323  bool IsIncompleteFunction,
2324  bool IsThunk) {
2325 
2326  if (llvm::Intrinsic::ID IID = F->getIntrinsicID()) {
2327  // If this is an intrinsic function, set the function's attributes
2328  // to the intrinsic's attributes.
2329  F->setAttributes(llvm::Intrinsic::getAttributes(getLLVMContext(), IID));
2330  return;
2331  }
2332 
2333  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2334 
2335  if (!IsIncompleteFunction)
2336  SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GD, getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD), F,
2337  IsThunk);
2338 
2339  // Add the Returned attribute for "this", except for iOS 5 and earlier
2340  // where substantial code, including the libstdc++ dylib, was compiled with
2341  // GCC and does not actually return "this".
2342  if (!IsThunk && getCXXABI().HasThisReturn(GD) &&
2343  !(getTriple().isiOS() && getTriple().isOSVersionLT(6))) {
2344  assert(!F->arg_empty() &&
2345  F->arg_begin()->getType()
2346  ->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(F->getReturnType()) &&
2347  "unexpected this return");
2348  F->addParamAttr(0, llvm::Attribute::Returned);
2349  }
2350 
2351  // Only a few attributes are set on declarations; these may later be
2352  // overridden by a definition.
2353 
2354  setLinkageForGV(F, FD);
2355  setGVProperties(F, FD);
2356 
2357  // Setup target-specific attributes.
2358  if (!IsIncompleteFunction && F->isDeclaration())
2359  getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(FD, F, *this);
2360 
2361  if (const auto *CSA = FD->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>())
2362  F->setSection(CSA->getName());
2363  else if (const auto *SA = FD->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
2364  F->setSection(SA->getName());
2365 
2366  if (const auto *EA = FD->getAttr<ErrorAttr>()) {
2367  if (EA->isError())
2368  F->addFnAttr("dontcall-error", EA->getUserDiagnostic());
2369  else if (EA->isWarning())
2370  F->addFnAttr("dontcall-warn", EA->getUserDiagnostic());
2371  }
2372 
2373  // If we plan on emitting this inline builtin, we can't treat it as a builtin.
2374  if (FD->isInlineBuiltinDeclaration()) {
2375  const FunctionDecl *FDBody;
2376  bool HasBody = FD->hasBody(FDBody);
2377  (void)HasBody;
2378  assert(HasBody && "Inline builtin declarations should always have an "
2379  "available body!");
2380  if (shouldEmitFunction(FDBody))
2381  F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
2382  }
2383 
2384  if (FD->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
2385  // A replaceable global allocation function does not act like a builtin by
2386  // default, only if it is invoked by a new-expression or delete-expression.
2387  F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
2388  }
2389 
2390  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(FD) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(FD))
2391  F->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
2392  else if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
2393  if (MD->isVirtual())
2394  F->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
2395 
2396  // Don't emit entries for function declarations in the cross-DSO mode. This
2397  // is handled with better precision by the receiving DSO. But if jump tables
2398  // are non-canonical then we need type metadata in order to produce the local
2399  // jump table.
2400  if (!CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso ||
2401  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCanonicalJumpTables)
2402  CreateFunctionTypeMetadataForIcall(FD, F);
2403 
2404  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && FD->hasAttr<OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr>())
2405  getOpenMPRuntime().emitDeclareSimdFunction(FD, F);
2406 
2407  if (const auto *CB = FD->getAttr<CallbackAttr>()) {
2408  // Annotate the callback behavior as metadata:
2409  // - The callback callee (as argument number).
2410  // - The callback payloads (as argument numbers).
2411  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = F->getContext();
2412  llvm::MDBuilder MDB(Ctx);
2413 
2414  // The payload indices are all but the first one in the encoding. The first
2415  // identifies the callback callee.
2416  int CalleeIdx = *CB->encoding_begin();
2417  ArrayRef<int> PayloadIndices(CB->encoding_begin() + 1, CB->encoding_end());
2418  F->addMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_callback,
2419  *llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, {MDB.createCallbackEncoding(
2420  CalleeIdx, PayloadIndices,
2421  /* VarArgsArePassed */ false)}));
2422  }
2423 }

2427  "Only globals with definition can force usage.");

2446 static void emitUsed(CodeGenModule &CGM, StringRef Name,
2447  std::vector<llvm::WeakTrackingVH> &List) {
2448  // Don't create llvm.used if there is no need.
2449  if (List.empty())
2450  return;
2451  // For SYCL emit pointers in the default address space which is a superset of
2452  // other address spaces, so that casts from any other address spaces will be
2453  // valid.
2454  llvm::PointerType *TargetType = CGM.Int8PtrTy;
2455  if (CGM.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
2456  TargetType = llvm::IntegerType::getInt8PtrTy(
2457  CGM.getLLVMContext(),
2458  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default));
2459 
2460  // Convert List to what ConstantArray needs.
2461  SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 8> UsedArray;
2462  UsedArray.resize(List.size());
2463  for (unsigned i = 0, e = List.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2464  UsedArray[i] = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
2465  cast<llvm::Constant>(&*List[i]), TargetType);
2466  }
2467 
2468  if (UsedArray.empty())
2469  return;
2470  llvm::ArrayType *ATy = llvm::ArrayType::get(TargetType, UsedArray.size());
2471 
2472  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
2473  CGM.getModule(), ATy, false, llvm::GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage,
2474  llvm::ConstantArray::get(ATy, UsedArray), Name);
2475 
2476  GV->setSection("llvm.metadata");
2477 }
2478 
2479 void CodeGenModule::emitLLVMUsed() {
2480  emitUsed(*this, "llvm.used", LLVMUsed);
2481  emitUsed(*this, "llvm.compiler.used", LLVMCompilerUsed);
2482 }

2498 void CodeGenModule::AddDependentLib(StringRef Lib) {
2499  auto &C = getLLVMContext();
2500  if (getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {

2502  llvm::MDNode::get(C, llvm::MDString::get(C, Lib)));
2503  return;
2504  }

2507  getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDependentLibraryOption(Lib, Opt);

2511 
2512 /// Add link options implied by the given module, including modules
2513 /// it depends on, using a postorder walk.
2514 static void addLinkOptionsPostorder(CodeGenModule &CGM, Module *Mod,
2515  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::MDNode *> &Metadata,
2516  llvm::SmallPtrSet<Module *, 16> &Visited) {
2517  // Import this module's parent.
2518  if (Mod->Parent && Visited.insert(Mod->Parent).second) {
2519  addLinkOptionsPostorder(CGM, Mod->Parent, Metadata, Visited);
2520  }
2521 
2522  // Import this module's dependencies.
2523  for (Module *Import : llvm::reverse(Mod->Imports)) {
2524  if (Visited.insert(Import).second)
2525  addLinkOptionsPostorder(CGM, Import, Metadata, Visited);
2526  }
2527 
2528  // Add linker options to link against the libraries/frameworks
2529  // described by this module.
2530  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
2531  bool IsELF = CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF();
2532 
2533  // For modules that use export_as for linking, use that module
2534  // name instead.
2535  if (Mod->UseExportAsModuleLinkName)
2536  return;
2537 
2538  for (const Module::LinkLibrary &LL : llvm::reverse(Mod->LinkLibraries)) {
2539  // Link against a framework. Frameworks are currently Darwin only, so we
2540  // don't to ask TargetCodeGenInfo for the spelling of the linker option.
2541  if (LL.IsFramework) {
2542  llvm::Metadata *Args[2] = {llvm::MDString::get(Context, "-framework"),
2543  llvm::MDString::get(Context, LL.Library)};
2544 
2545  Metadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args));
2546  continue;
2547  }
2548 
2549  // Link against a library.
2550  if (IsELF) {
2551  llvm::Metadata *Args[2] = {
2552  llvm::MDString::get(Context, "lib"),
2553  llvm::MDString::get(Context, LL.Library),
2554  };
2555  Metadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args));
2556  } else {
2557  llvm::SmallString<24> Opt;
2558  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDependentLibraryOption(LL.Library, Opt);
2559  auto *OptString = llvm::MDString::get(Context, Opt);
2560  Metadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, OptString));
2561  }
2562  }
2563 }
2564 
2565 void CodeGenModule::EmitModuleLinkOptions() {
2566  // Collect the set of all of the modules we want to visit to emit link
2567  // options, which is essentially the imported modules and all of their
2568  // non-explicit child modules.
2569  llvm::SetVector<clang::Module *> LinkModules;
2570  llvm::SmallPtrSet<clang::Module *, 16> Visited;
2571  SmallVector<clang::Module *, 16> Stack;
2572 
2573  // Seed the stack with imported modules.
2574  for (Module *M : ImportedModules) {
2575  // Do not add any link flags when an implementation TU of a module imports
2576  // a header of that same module.
2577  if (M->getTopLevelModuleName() == getLangOpts().CurrentModule &&
2578  !getLangOpts().isCompilingModule())
2579  continue;
2580  if (Visited.insert(M).second)
2581  Stack.push_back(M);
2582  }
2583 
2584  // Find all of the modules to import, making a little effort to prune
2585  // non-leaf modules.
2586  while (!Stack.empty()) {
2587  clang::Module *Mod = Stack.pop_back_val();
2588 
2589  bool AnyChildren = false;
2590 
2591  // Visit the submodules of this module.
2592  for (const auto &SM : Mod->submodules()) {
2593  // Skip explicit children; they need to be explicitly imported to be
2594  // linked against.
2595  if (SM->IsExplicit)
2596  continue;
2597 
2598  if (Visited.insert(SM).second) {
2599  Stack.push_back(SM);
2600  AnyChildren = true;
2601  }
2602  }
2603 
2604  // We didn't find any children, so add this module to the list of
2605  // modules to link against.
2606  if (!AnyChildren) {
2607  LinkModules.insert(Mod);
2608  }
2609  }
2610 
2611  // Add link options for all of the imported modules in reverse topological
2612  // order. We don't do anything to try to order import link flags with respect
2613  // to linker options inserted by things like #pragma comment().
2614  SmallVector<llvm::MDNode *, 16> MetadataArgs;
2615  Visited.clear();
2616  for (Module *M : LinkModules)
2617  if (Visited.insert(M).second)
2618  addLinkOptionsPostorder(*this, M, MetadataArgs, Visited);
2619  std::reverse(MetadataArgs.begin(), MetadataArgs.end());
2620  LinkerOptionsMetadata.append(MetadataArgs.begin(), MetadataArgs.end());
2621 
2622  // Add the linker options metadata flag.
2623  auto *NMD = getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.linker.options");
2624  for (auto *MD : LinkerOptionsMetadata)
2625  NMD->addOperand(MD);
2626 }
2627 
2628 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeferred() {
2629  // Emit deferred declare target declarations.
2630  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd)
2631  getOpenMPRuntime().emitDeferredTargetDecls();
2632 
2633  // Emit code for any potentially referenced deferred decls. Since a
2634  // previously unused static decl may become used during the generation of code
2635  // for a static function, iterate until no changes are made.
2636 
2637  if (!DeferredVTables.empty()) {
2638  EmitDeferredVTables();
2639 
2640  // Emitting a vtable doesn't directly cause more vtables to
2641  // become deferred, although it can cause functions to be
2642  // emitted that then need those vtables.
2643  assert(DeferredVTables.empty());
2644  }
2645 
2646  // Emit CUDA/HIP static device variables referenced by host code only.
2647  // Note we should not clear CUDADeviceVarODRUsedByHost since it is still
2648  // needed for further handling.
2649  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
2650  llvm::append_range(DeferredDeclsToEmit,
2651  getContext().CUDADeviceVarODRUsedByHost);
2652 
2653  // Stop if we're out of both deferred vtables and deferred declarations.
2654  if (DeferredDeclsToEmit.empty())
2655  return;
2656 
2657  // Grab the list of decls to emit. If EmitGlobalDefinition schedules more
2658  // work, it will not interfere with this.
2659  std::vector<GlobalDecl> CurDeclsToEmit;
2660  CurDeclsToEmit.swap(DeferredDeclsToEmit);
2661 
2662  for (GlobalDecl &D : CurDeclsToEmit) {
2663  const ValueDecl *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D.getDecl());
2664  // If emitting for SYCL device, emit the deferred alias
2665  // as well as what it aliases.
2666  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
2667  if (AliasAttr *Attr = VD->getAttr<AliasAttr>()) {
2668  StringRef AliaseeName = Attr->getAliasee();
2669  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(AliaseeName);
2670  // Emit what is aliased first.
2671  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end()) {
2672  GlobalDecl GD = DDI->second;
2673  llvm::GlobalValue *AliaseeGV =
2674  dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetAddrOfGlobal(GD, ForDefinition));
2675  if (!AliaseeGV)
2676  AliaseeGV = GetGlobalValue(getMangledName(GD));
2677  assert(AliaseeGV);
2678  EmitGlobalDefinition(GD, AliaseeGV);
2679  // Remove the entry just added to the DeferredDeclsToEmit
2680  // since we have emitted it.
2681  DeferredDeclsToEmit.pop_back();
2682  }
2683  // Now emit the alias itself.
2684  EmitAliasDefinition(D);
2685  continue;
2686  }
2687  }
2688  // We should call GetAddrOfGlobal with IsForDefinition set to true in order
2689  // to get GlobalValue with exactly the type we need, not something that
2690  // might had been created for another decl with the same mangled name but
2691  // different type.
2692  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(
2693  GetAddrOfGlobal(D, ForDefinition));
2694 
2695  // In case of different address spaces, we may still get a cast, even with
2696  // IsForDefinition equal to true. Query mangled names table to get
2697  // GlobalValue.
2698  if (!GV)
2699  GV = GetGlobalValue(getMangledName(D));
2700 
2701  // Make sure GetGlobalValue returned non-null.
2702  assert(GV);
2703 
2704  // Check to see if we've already emitted this. This is necessary
2705  // for a couple of reasons: first, decls can end up in the
2706  // deferred-decls queue multiple times, and second, decls can end
2707  // up with definitions in unusual ways (e.g. by an extern inline
2708  // function acquiring a strong function redefinition). Just
2709  // ignore these cases.
2710  if (!GV->isDeclaration())
2711  continue;
2712 
2713  // If this is OpenMP, check if it is legal to emit this global normally.
2714  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && OpenMPRuntime && OpenMPRuntime->emitTargetGlobal(D))
2715  continue;
2716 
2717  // Otherwise, emit the definition and move on to the next one.
2718  EmitGlobalDefinition(D, GV);
2719 
2720  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
2721  // If there are any aliases deferred for this, emit those now.
2722  for (auto It = DeferredAliases.begin(); It != DeferredAliases.end();
2723  /*no increment*/) {
2724  const ValueDecl *Global = cast<ValueDecl>(It->second.getDecl());
2725  if (It->first == getMangledName(D)) {
2726  EmitAliasDefinition(Global);
2727  It = DeferredAliases.erase(It);
2728  } else {
2729  ++It;
2730  }
2731  }
2732  }
2733 
2734  // If we found out that we need to emit more decls, do that recursively.
2735  // This has the advantage that the decls are emitted in a DFS and related
2736  // ones are close together, which is convenient for testing.
2737  if (!DeferredVTables.empty() || !DeferredDeclsToEmit.empty()) {
2738  EmitDeferred();
2739  assert(DeferredVTables.empty() && DeferredDeclsToEmit.empty());
2740  }
2741  }
2742 }
2743 
2744 void CodeGenModule::EmitVTablesOpportunistically() {
2745  // Try to emit external vtables as available_externally if they have emitted
2746  // all inlined virtual functions. It runs after EmitDeferred() and therefore
2747  // is not allowed to create new references to things that need to be emitted
2748  // lazily. Note that it also uses fact that we eagerly emitting RTTI.
2749 
2750  assert((OpportunisticVTables.empty() || shouldOpportunisticallyEmitVTables())
2751  && "Only emit opportunistic vtables with optimizations");
2752 
2753  for (const CXXRecordDecl *RD : OpportunisticVTables) {
2754  assert(getVTables().isVTableExternal(RD) &&
2755  "This queue should only contain external vtables");
2756  if (getCXXABI().canSpeculativelyEmitVTable(RD))
2757  VTables.GenerateClassData(RD);
2758  }
2759  OpportunisticVTables.clear();
2760 }
2761 
2762 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalAnnotations() {
2763  if (Annotations.empty())
2764  return;
2765 
2766  // Create a new global variable for the ConstantStruct in the Module.
2767  llvm::Constant *Array = llvm::ConstantArray::get(llvm::ArrayType::get(
2768  Annotations[0]->getType(), Annotations.size()), Annotations);
2769  auto *gv = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Array->getType(), false,
2770  llvm::GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage,
2771  Array, "llvm.global.annotations");
2772  gv->setSection(AnnotationSection);
2773 }

2775 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitAnnotationString(StringRef Str) {
2776  llvm::Constant *&AStr = AnnotationStrings[Str];
2777  if (AStr)
2778  return AStr;
2779 
2780  // Not found yet, create a new global.
2781  llvm::Constant *s = llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), Str);
2782  auto *gv =
2783  new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), s->getType(), true,
2784  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, s, ".str");
2785  gv->setSection(AnnotationSection);
2786  gv->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
2787  AStr = gv;
2788  return gv;
2789 }

2800  SourceManager &SM = getContext().getSourceManager();
2801  PresumedLoc PLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(L);
2802  unsigned LineNo = PLoc.isValid() ? PLoc.getLine() :

2806 
2807 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitAnnotationArgs(const AnnotateAttr *Attr) {
2808  ArrayRef<Expr *> Exprs = {Attr->args_begin(), Attr->args_size()};
2809  if (Exprs.empty())
2810  return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(GlobalsInt8PtrTy);
2811 
2812  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2813  for (Expr *E : Exprs) {
2814  ID.Add(cast<clang::ConstantExpr>(E)->getAPValueResult());
2815  }
2816  llvm::Constant *&Lookup = AnnotationArgs[ID.ComputeHash()];
2817  if (Lookup)
2818  return Lookup;
2819 
2820  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> LLVMArgs;
2821  LLVMArgs.reserve(Exprs.size());
2822  ConstantEmitter ConstEmiter(*this);
2823  llvm::transform(Exprs, std::back_inserter(LLVMArgs), [&](const Expr *E) {
2824  const auto *CE = cast<clang::ConstantExpr>(E);
2825  return ConstEmiter.emitAbstract(CE->getBeginLoc(), CE->getAPValueResult(),
2826  CE->getType());
2827  });
2828  auto *Struct = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(LLVMArgs);
2829  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Struct->getType(), true,
2830  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Struct,
2831  ".args");
2832  GV->setSection(AnnotationSection);
2833  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
2834  auto *Bitcasted = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, GlobalsInt8PtrTy);
2835 
2836  Lookup = Bitcasted;
2837  return Bitcasted;
2838 }
2839 
2840 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitAnnotateAttr(llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
2841  const AnnotateAttr *AA,
2842  SourceLocation L) {
2843  // Get the globals for file name, annotation, and the line number.
2844  llvm::Constant *AnnoGV = EmitAnnotationString(AA->getAnnotation()),
2845  *UnitGV = EmitAnnotationUnit(L),
2846  *LineNoCst = EmitAnnotationLineNo(L),
2847  *Args = EmitAnnotationArgs(AA);
2848 
2849  llvm::Constant *GVInGlobalsAS = GV;
2850  if (GV->getAddressSpace() !=
2851  getDataLayout().getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace()) {
2852  GVInGlobalsAS = llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
2853  GV, GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(
2854  getDataLayout().getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace()));
2855  }
2856 
2857  // Create the ConstantStruct for the global annotation.
2858  llvm::Constant *Fields[] = {
2859  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GVInGlobalsAS, GlobalsInt8PtrTy),
2860  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(AnnoGV, GlobalsInt8PtrTy),
2861  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(UnitGV, GlobalsInt8PtrTy),
2862  LineNoCst,
2863  Args,
2864  };
2865  return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields);
2866 }
