2896 bool CodeGenModule::isInNoSanitizeList(SanitizerMask Kind, llvm::Function *Fn,
2897  SourceLocation Loc) const {
2898  const auto &NoSanitizeL = getContext().getNoSanitizeList();
2899  // NoSanitize by function name.
2900  if (NoSanitizeL.containsFunction(Kind, Fn->getName()))
2901  return true;
2902  // NoSanitize by location.
2903  if (Loc.isValid())
2904  return NoSanitizeL.containsLocation(Kind, Loc);
2905  // If location is unknown, this may be a compiler-generated function. Assume
2906  // it's located in the main file.
2907  auto &SM = Context.getSourceManager();
2908  if (const auto *MainFile = SM.getFileEntryForID(SM.getMainFileID())) {
2909  return NoSanitizeL.containsFile(Kind, MainFile->getName());
2910  }
2911  return false;
2912 }
2913 
2914 bool CodeGenModule::isInNoSanitizeList(llvm::GlobalVariable *GV,
2915  SourceLocation Loc, QualType Ty,
2916  StringRef Category) const {
2917  // For now globals can be ignored only in ASan and KASan.
2918  const SanitizerMask EnabledAsanMask =
2919  LangOpts.Sanitize.Mask &
2920  (SanitizerKind::Address | SanitizerKind::KernelAddress |
2921  SanitizerKind::HWAddress | SanitizerKind::KernelHWAddress |
2922  SanitizerKind::MemTag);
2923  if (!EnabledAsanMask)
2924  return false;
2925  const auto &NoSanitizeL = getContext().getNoSanitizeList();
2926  if (NoSanitizeL.containsGlobal(EnabledAsanMask, GV->getName(), Category))
2927  return true;
2928  if (NoSanitizeL.containsLocation(EnabledAsanMask, Loc, Category))
2929  return true;
2930  // Check global type.
2931  if (!Ty.isNull()) {
2932  // Drill down the array types: if global variable of a fixed type is
2933  // not sanitized, we also don't instrument arrays of them.
2934  while (auto AT = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(Ty.getTypePtr()))
2935  Ty = AT->getElementType();
2936  Ty = Ty.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
2937  // Only record types (classes, structs etc.) are ignored.
2938  if (Ty->isRecordType()) {
2939  std::string TypeStr = Ty.getAsString(getContext().getPrintingPolicy());
2940  if (NoSanitizeL.containsType(EnabledAsanMask, TypeStr, Category))
2941  return true;
2942  }
2943  }
2944  return false;
2945 }
2946 
2947 bool CodeGenModule::imbueXRayAttrs(llvm::Function *Fn, SourceLocation Loc,
2948  StringRef Category) const {
2949  const auto &XRayFilter = getContext().getXRayFilter();
2950  using ImbueAttr = XRayFunctionFilter::ImbueAttribute;
2951  auto Attr = ImbueAttr::NONE;
2952  if (Loc.isValid())
2953  Attr = XRayFilter.shouldImbueLocation(Loc, Category);
2954  if (Attr == ImbueAttr::NONE)
2955  Attr = XRayFilter.shouldImbueFunction(Fn->getName());
2956  switch (Attr) {
2957  case ImbueAttr::NONE:
2958  return false;
2959  case ImbueAttr::ALWAYS:
2960  Fn->addFnAttr("function-instrument", "xray-always");
2961  break;
2962  case ImbueAttr::ALWAYS_ARG1:
2963  Fn->addFnAttr("function-instrument", "xray-always");
2964  Fn->addFnAttr("xray-log-args", "1");
2965  break;
2966  case ImbueAttr::NEVER:
2967  Fn->addFnAttr("function-instrument", "xray-never");
2968  break;
2969  }
2970  return true;
2971 }
2972 
2973 bool CodeGenModule::isProfileInstrExcluded(llvm::Function *Fn,
2974  SourceLocation Loc) const {
2975  const auto &ProfileList = getContext().getProfileList();
2976  // If the profile list is empty, then instrument everything.
2977  if (ProfileList.isEmpty())
2978  return false;
2979  CodeGenOptions::ProfileInstrKind Kind = getCodeGenOpts().getProfileInstr();
2980  // First, check the function name.
2981  Optional<bool> V = ProfileList.isFunctionExcluded(Fn->getName(), Kind);
2982  if (V.hasValue())
2983  return *V;
2984  // Next, check the source location.
2985  if (Loc.isValid()) {
2986  Optional<bool> V = ProfileList.isLocationExcluded(Loc, Kind);
2987  if (V.hasValue())
2988  return *V;
2989  }
2990  // If location is unknown, this may be a compiler-generated function. Assume
2991  // it's located in the main file.
2992  auto &SM = Context.getSourceManager();
2993  if (const auto *MainFile = SM.getFileEntryForID(SM.getMainFileID())) {
2994  Optional<bool> V = ProfileList.isFileExcluded(MainFile->getName(), Kind);
2995  if (V.hasValue())
2996  return *V;
2997  }
2998  return ProfileList.getDefault();
2999 }
3000 
3001 bool CodeGenModule::MustBeEmitted(const ValueDecl *Global) {
3002  // Never defer when EmitAllDecls is specified.
3003  if (LangOpts.EmitAllDecls)
3004  return true;
3005 
3006  if (CodeGenOpts.KeepStaticConsts) {
3007  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Global);
3008  if (VD && VD->getType().isConstQualified() &&
3009  VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static)
3010  return true;
3011  }
3012 
3013  return getContext().DeclMustBeEmitted(Global);
3014 }
3015 
3016 bool CodeGenModule::MayBeEmittedEagerly(const ValueDecl *Global) {
3017  // In OpenMP 5.0 variables and function may be marked as
3018  // device_type(host/nohost) and we should not emit them eagerly unless we sure
3019  // that they must be emitted on the host/device. To be sure we need to have
3020  // seen a declare target with an explicit mentioning of the function, we know
3021  // we have if the level of the declare target attribute is -1. Note that we
3022  // check somewhere else if we should emit this at all.
3023  if (LangOpts.OpenMP >= 50 && !LangOpts.OpenMPSimd) {
3024  llvm::Optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr *> ActiveAttr =
3025  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::getActiveAttr(Global);
3026  if (!ActiveAttr || (*ActiveAttr)->getLevel() != (unsigned)-1)
3027  return false;
3028  }
3029 
3030  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Global)) {
3031  if (FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
3032  // Implicit template instantiations may change linkage if they are later
3033  // explicitly instantiated, so they should not be emitted eagerly.
3034  return false;
3035  }
3036  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Global))
3037  if (Context.getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(VD) ==
3038  ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::WeakUnknown)
3039  // A definition of an inline constexpr static data member may change
3040  // linkage later if it's redeclared outside the class.
3041  return false;
3042  // If OpenMP is enabled and threadprivates must be generated like TLS, delay
3043  // codegen for global variables, because they may be marked as threadprivate.
3044  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && LangOpts.OpenMPUseTLS &&
3045  getContext().getTargetInfo().isTLSSupported() && isa<VarDecl>(Global) &&
3046  !isTypeConstant(Global->getType(), false) &&
3047  !OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(Global))
3048  return false;
3049 
3050  return true;
3051 }
3052 
3053 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfMSGuidDecl(const MSGuidDecl *GD) {
3054  StringRef Name = getMangledName(GD);
3055 
3056  // The UUID descriptor should be pointer aligned.
3057  CharUnits Alignment = CharUnits::fromQuantity(PointerAlignInBytes);
3058 
3059  // Look for an existing global.
3060  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name))
3061  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3062 
3063  ConstantEmitter Emitter(*this);
3064  llvm::Constant *Init;
3065 
3066  APValue &V = GD->getAsAPValue();
3067  if (!V.isAbsent()) {
3068  // If possible, emit the APValue version of the initializer. In particular,
3069  // this gets the type of the constant right.
3070  Init = Emitter.emitForInitializer(
3071  GD->getAsAPValue(), GD->getType().getAddressSpace(), GD->getType());
3072  } else {
3073  // As a fallback, directly construct the constant.
3074  // FIXME: This may get padding wrong under esoteric struct layout rules.
3075  // MSVC appears to create a complete type 'struct __s_GUID' that it
3076  // presumably uses to represent these constants.
3077  MSGuidDecl::Parts Parts = GD->getParts();
3078  llvm::Constant *Fields[4] = {
3079  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Parts.Part1),
3080  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int16Ty, Parts.Part2),
3081  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int16Ty, Parts.Part3),
3082  llvm::ConstantDataArray::getRaw(
3083  StringRef(reinterpret_cast<char *>(Parts.Part4And5), 8), 8,
3084  Int8Ty)};
3085  Init = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields);
3086  }
3087 
3088  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3089  getModule(), Init->getType(),
3090  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage, Init, Name);
3091  if (supportsCOMDAT())
3092  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
3093  setDSOLocal(GV);
3094 
3095  if (!V.isAbsent()) {
3096  Emitter.finalize(GV);
3097  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3098  }
3099 
3100  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(GD->getType());
3101  llvm::Constant *Addr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
3102  GV, Ty->getPointerTo(GV->getAddressSpace()));
3103  return ConstantAddress(Addr, Ty, Alignment);
3104 }
3105 
3106 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfTemplateParamObject(
3107  const TemplateParamObjectDecl *TPO) {
3108  StringRef Name = getMangledName(TPO);
3109  CharUnits Alignment = getNaturalTypeAlignment(TPO->getType());
3110 
3111  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name))
3112  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3113 
3114  ConstantEmitter Emitter(*this);
3115  llvm::Constant *Init = Emitter.emitForInitializer(
3116  TPO->getValue(), TPO->getType().getAddressSpace(), TPO->getType());
3117 
3118  if (!Init) {
3119  ErrorUnsupported(TPO, "template parameter object");
3120  return ConstantAddress::invalid();
3121  }
3122 
3123  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3124  getModule(), Init->getType(),
3125  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage, Init, Name);
3126  if (supportsCOMDAT())
3127  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
3128  Emitter.finalize(GV);
3129 
3130  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3131 }
3132 
3133 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetWeakRefReference(const ValueDecl *VD) {
3134  const AliasAttr *AA = VD->getAttr<AliasAttr>();
3135  assert(AA && "No alias?");
3136 
3137  CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
3138  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
3139 
3140  // See if there is already something with the target's name in the module.
3141  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(AA->getAliasee());
3142  if (Entry) {
3143  unsigned AS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(VD->getType());
3144  auto Ptr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Entry, DeclTy->getPointerTo(AS));
3145  return ConstantAddress(Ptr, DeclTy, Alignment);
3146  }
3147 
3148  llvm::Constant *Aliasee;
3149  if (isa<llvm::FunctionType>(DeclTy))
3150  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy,
3151  GlobalDecl(cast<FunctionDecl>(VD)),
3152  /*ForVTable=*/false);
3153  else
3154  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy, LangAS::Default,
3155  nullptr);
3156 
3157  auto *F = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Aliasee);
3158  F->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalWeakLinkage);
3159  WeakRefReferences.insert(F);
3160 
3161  return ConstantAddress(Aliasee, DeclTy, Alignment);
3162 }
3163 
3164 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl GD) {
3165  const auto *Global = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3166 
3167  // Weak references don't produce any output by themselves.
3168  if (Global->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>())
3169  return;
3170 
3171  // If this is an alias definition (which otherwise looks like a declaration)
3172  // handle it now.
3173  if (AliasAttr *Attr = Global->getAttr<AliasAttr>()) {
3174  // Emit the alias here if it is not SYCL device compilation.
3175  if (!LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
3176  return EmitAliasDefinition(GD);
3177  // Defer for SYCL devices, until either the alias or what it aliases
3178  // is used.
3179  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
3180  DeferredDecls[MangledName] = GD;
3181  StringRef AliaseeName = Attr->getAliasee();
3182  DeferredAliases[AliaseeName] = GD;
3183  return;
3184  }
3185 
3186  // IFunc like an alias whose value is resolved at runtime by calling resolver.
3187  if (Global->hasAttr<IFuncAttr>())
3188  return emitIFuncDefinition(GD);
3189 
3190  // If this is a cpu_dispatch multiversion function, emit the resolver.
3191  if (Global->hasAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>())
3192  return emitCPUDispatchDefinition(GD);
3193 
3194  // If this is CUDA, be selective about which declarations we emit.
3195  if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
3196  if (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
3197  if (!Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() &&
3198  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() &&
3199  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() &&
3200  !Global->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>() &&
3201  !Global->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() &&
3202  !Global->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType())
3203  return;
3204  } else {
3205  // We need to emit host-side 'shadows' for all global
3206  // device-side variables because the CUDA runtime needs their
3207  // size and host-side address in order to provide access to
3208  // their device-side incarnations.
3209 
3210  // So device-only functions are the only things we skip.
3211  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) && !Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() &&
3212  Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
3213  return;
3214 
3215  assert((isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) || isa<VarDecl>(Global)) &&
3216  "Expected Variable or Function");
3217  }
3218  }
3219 
3220  if (LangOpts.OpenMP) {
3221  // If this is OpenMP, check if it is legal to emit this global normally.
3222  if (OpenMPRuntime && OpenMPRuntime->emitTargetGlobal(GD))
3223  return;
3224  if (auto *DRD = dyn_cast<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(Global)) {
3225  if (MustBeEmitted(Global))
3226  EmitOMPDeclareReduction(DRD);
3227  return;
3228  } else if (auto *DMD = dyn_cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(Global)) {
3229  if (MustBeEmitted(Global))
3230  EmitOMPDeclareMapper(DMD);
3231  return;
3232  }
3233  }
3234 
3235  // Ignore declarations, they will be emitted on their first use.
3236  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Global)) {
3237  // Forward declarations are emitted lazily on first use.
3238  if (!FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody()) {
3239  if (!FD->doesDeclarationForceExternallyVisibleDefinition())
3240  return;
3241 
3242  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
3243 
3244  // Compute the function info and LLVM type.
3245  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
3246  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
3247 
3248  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(MangledName, Ty, GD, /*ForVTable=*/false,
3249  /*DontDefer=*/false);
3250  return;
3251  }
3252  } else {
3253  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(Global);
3254  assert(VD->isFileVarDecl() && "Cannot emit local var decl as global.");
3255  if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition() != VarDecl::Definition &&
3256  !Context.isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(VD)) {
3257  if (LangOpts.OpenMP) {
3258  // Emit declaration of the must-be-emitted declare target variable.
3259  if (llvm::Optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
3260  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD)) {
3261  bool UnifiedMemoryEnabled =
3262  getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory();
3263  if (*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To &&
3264  !UnifiedMemoryEnabled) {
3265  (void)GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
3266  } else {
3267  assert(((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link) ||
3268  (*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To &&
3269  UnifiedMemoryEnabled)) &&
3270  "Link clause or to clause with unified memory expected.");
3271  (void)getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfDeclareTargetVar(VD);
3272  }
3273 
3274  return;
3275  }
3276  }
3277  // If this declaration may have caused an inline variable definition to
3278  // change linkage, make sure that it's emitted.
3279  if (Context.getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(VD) ==
3280  ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Strong)
3281  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
3282  return;
3283  }
3284  }
3285 
3286  // clang::ParseAST ensures that we emit the SYCL devices at the end, so
3287  // anything that is a device (or indirectly called) will be handled later.
3288  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && MustBeEmitted(Global)) {
3289  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
3290  return;
3291  }
3292 
3293  // Defer code generation to first use when possible, e.g. if this is an inline
3294  // function. If the global must always be emitted, do it eagerly if possible
3295  // to benefit from cache locality.
3296  if (MustBeEmitted(Global) && MayBeEmittedEagerly(Global)) {
3297  // Emit the definition if it can't be deferred.
3298  EmitGlobalDefinition(GD);
3299  return;
3300  }
3301 
3302  // If we're deferring emission of a C++ variable with an
3303  // initializer, remember the order in which it appeared in the file.
3304  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && isa<VarDecl>(Global) &&
3305  cast<VarDecl>(Global)->hasInit()) {
3306  DelayedCXXInitPosition[Global] = CXXGlobalInits.size();
3307  CXXGlobalInits.push_back(nullptr);
3308  }
3309 
3310  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
3311  if (GetGlobalValue(MangledName) != nullptr) {
3312  // The value has already been used and should therefore be emitted.
3313  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
3314  } else if (MustBeEmitted(Global)) {
3315  // The value must be emitted, but cannot be emitted eagerly.
3316  assert(!MayBeEmittedEagerly(Global));
3317  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
3318  } else {
3319  // Otherwise, remember that we saw a deferred decl with this name. The
3320  // first use of the mangled name will cause it to move into
3321  // DeferredDeclsToEmit.
3322  DeferredDecls[MangledName] = GD;
3323  }
3324 }
3325 
3326 // Check if T is a class type with a destructor that's not dllimport.
3327 static bool HasNonDllImportDtor(QualType T) {
3328  if (const auto *RT = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>())
3329  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
3330  if (RD->getDestructor() && !RD->getDestructor()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
3331  return true;
3332 
3333  return false;
3334 }
3335 
3336 namespace {
3337  struct FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive
3338  : public ConstStmtVisitor<FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive, bool> {
3339  const StringRef Name;
3340  const Builtin::Context &BI;
3341  FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive(StringRef N, const Builtin::Context &C)
3342  : Name(N), BI(C) {}
3343 
3344  bool VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
3345  const FunctionDecl *FD = E->getDirectCallee();
3346  if (!FD)
3347  return false;
3348  AsmLabelAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
3349  if (Attr && Name == Attr->getLabel())
3350  return true;
3351  unsigned BuiltinID = FD->getBuiltinID();
3352  if (!BuiltinID || !BI.isLibFunction(BuiltinID))
3353  return false;
3354  StringRef BuiltinName = BI.getName(BuiltinID);
3355  if (BuiltinName.startswith("__builtin_") &&
3356  Name == BuiltinName.slice(strlen("__builtin_"), StringRef::npos)) {
3357  return true;
3358  }
3359  return false;
3360  }
3361 
3362  bool VisitStmt(const Stmt *S) {
3363  for (const Stmt *Child : S->children())
3364  if (Child && this->Visit(Child))
3365  return true;
3366  return false;
3367  }
3368  };
3369 
3370  // Make sure we're not referencing non-imported vars or functions.
3371  struct DLLImportFunctionVisitor
3372  : public RecursiveASTVisitor<DLLImportFunctionVisitor> {
3373  bool SafeToInline = true;
3374 
3375  bool shouldVisitImplicitCode() const { return true; }
3376 
3377  bool VisitVarDecl(VarDecl *VD) {
3378  if (VD->getTLSKind()) {
3379  // A thread-local variable cannot be imported.
3380  SafeToInline = false;
3381  return SafeToInline;
3382  }
3383 
3384  // A variable definition might imply a destructor call.
3385  if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
3386  SafeToInline = !HasNonDllImportDtor(VD->getType());
3387 
3388  return SafeToInline;
3389  }
3390 
3391  bool VisitCXXBindTemporaryExpr(CXXBindTemporaryExpr *E) {
3392  if (const auto *D = E->getTemporary()->getDestructor())
3393  SafeToInline = D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3394  return SafeToInline;
3395  }
3396 
3397  bool VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
3398  ValueDecl *VD = E->getDecl();
3399  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(VD))
3400  SafeToInline = VD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3401  else if (VarDecl *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(VD))
3402  SafeToInline = !V->hasGlobalStorage() || V->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3403  return SafeToInline;
3404  }
3405 
3406  bool VisitCXXConstructExpr(CXXConstructExpr *E) {
3407  SafeToInline = E->getConstructor()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3408  return SafeToInline;
3409  }
3410 
3411  bool VisitCXXMemberCallExpr(CXXMemberCallExpr *E) {
3412  CXXMethodDecl *M = E->getMethodDecl();
3413  if (!M) {
3414  // Call through a pointer to member function. This is safe to inline.
3415  SafeToInline = true;
3416  } else {
3417  SafeToInline = M->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3418  }
3419  return SafeToInline;
3420  }
3421 
3422  bool VisitCXXDeleteExpr(CXXDeleteExpr *E) {
3423  SafeToInline = E->getOperatorDelete()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3424  return SafeToInline;
3425  }
3426 
3427  bool VisitCXXNewExpr(CXXNewExpr *E) {
3428  SafeToInline = E->getOperatorNew()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3429  return SafeToInline;
3430  }
3431  };
3432 }
3433 
3434 // isTriviallyRecursive - Check if this function calls another
3435 // decl that, because of the asm attribute or the other decl being a builtin,
3436 // ends up pointing to itself.
3437 bool
3438 CodeGenModule::isTriviallyRecursive(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3439  StringRef Name;
3440  if (getCXXABI().getMangleContext().shouldMangleDeclName(FD)) {
3441  // asm labels are a special kind of mangling we have to support.
3442  AsmLabelAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
3443  if (!Attr)
3444  return false;
3445  Name = Attr->getLabel();
3446  } else {
3447  Name = FD->getName();
3448  }
3449 
3450  FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive Walker(Name, Context.BuiltinInfo);
3451  const Stmt *Body = FD->getBody();
3452  return Body ? Walker.Visit(Body) : false;
3453 }
3454 
3455 bool CodeGenModule::shouldEmitFunction(GlobalDecl GD) {
3456  if (getFunctionLinkage(GD) != llvm::Function::AvailableExternallyLinkage)
3457  return true;
3458  const auto *F = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3459  if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel == 0 && !F->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>())
3460  return false;
3461 
3462  if (F->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() && !F->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>()) {
3463  // Check whether it would be safe to inline this dllimport function.
3464  DLLImportFunctionVisitor Visitor;
3465  Visitor.TraverseFunctionDecl(const_cast<FunctionDecl*>(F));
3466  if (!Visitor.SafeToInline)
3467  return false;
3468 
3469  if (const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(F)) {
3470  // Implicit destructor invocations aren't captured in the AST, so the
3471  // check above can't see them. Check for them manually here.
3472  for (const Decl *Member : Dtor->getParent()->decls())
3473  if (isa<FieldDecl>(Member))
3474  if (HasNonDllImportDtor(cast<FieldDecl>(Member)->getType()))
3475  return false;
3476  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &B : Dtor->getParent()->bases())
3477  if (HasNonDllImportDtor(B.getType()))
3478  return false;
3479  }
3480  }
3481 
3482  // Inline builtins declaration must be emitted. They often are fortified
3483  // functions.
3484  if (F->isInlineBuiltinDeclaration())
3485  return true;
3486 
3487  // PR9614. Avoid cases where the source code is lying to us. An available
3488  // externally function should have an equivalent function somewhere else,
3489  // but a function that calls itself through asm label/`__builtin_` trickery is
3490  // clearly not equivalent to the real implementation.
3491  // This happens in glibc's btowc and in some configure checks.
3492  return !isTriviallyRecursive(F);
3493 }
3494 
3495 bool CodeGenModule::shouldOpportunisticallyEmitVTables() {
3496  return CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel > 0;
3497 }
3498 
3499 void CodeGenModule::EmitMultiVersionFunctionDefinition(GlobalDecl GD,
3500  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
3501  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3502 
3503  if (FD->isCPUSpecificMultiVersion()) {
3504  auto *Spec = FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>();
3505  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Spec->cpus_size(); ++I)
3506  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(I), nullptr);
3507  // Requires multiple emits.
3508  } else if (FD->isTargetClonesMultiVersion()) {
3509  auto *Clone = FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>();
3510  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Clone->featuresStrs_size(); ++I)
3511  if (Clone->isFirstOfVersion(I))
3512  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(I), nullptr);
3513  EmitTargetClonesResolver(GD);
3514  } else
3515  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
3516 }
3517 
3518 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalDefinition(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
3519  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3520 
3521  PrettyStackTraceDecl CrashInfo(const_cast<ValueDecl *>(D), D->getLocation(),
3522  Context.getSourceManager(),
3523  "Generating code for declaration");
3524 
3525  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3526  // At -O0, don't generate IR for functions with available_externally
3527  // linkage.
3528  if (!shouldEmitFunction(GD))
3529  return;
3530 
3531  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("CodeGen Function", [&]() {
3532  std::string Name;
3533  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
3534  FD->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, getContext().getPrintingPolicy(),
3535  /*Qualified=*/true);
3536  return Name;
3537  });
3538 
3539  if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
3540  // Make sure to emit the definition(s) before we emit the thunks.
3541  // This is necessary for the generation of certain thunks.
3542  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method))
3543  ABI->emitCXXStructor(GD);
3544  else if (FD->isMultiVersion())
3545  EmitMultiVersionFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
3546  else
3547  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
3548 
3549  if (Method->isVirtual())
3550  getVTables().EmitThunks(GD);
3551 
3552  return;
3553  }
3554 
3555  if (FD->isMultiVersion())
3556  return EmitMultiVersionFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
3557  return EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
3558  }
3559 
3560  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
3561  return EmitGlobalVarDefinition(VD, !VD->hasDefinition());
3562 
3563  llvm_unreachable("Invalid argument to EmitGlobalDefinition()");
3564 }
3565 
3566 static void ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction(llvm::GlobalValue *Old,
3567  llvm::Function *NewFn);
3568 
3569 static unsigned
3570 TargetMVPriority(const TargetInfo &TI,
3571  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RO) {
3572  unsigned Priority = 0;
3573  for (StringRef Feat : RO.Conditions.Features)
3574  Priority = std::max(Priority, TI.multiVersionSortPriority(Feat));
3575 
3576  if (!RO.Conditions.Architecture.empty())
3577  Priority = std::max(
3578  Priority, TI.multiVersionSortPriority(RO.Conditions.Architecture));
3579  return Priority;
3580 }
3581 
3582 // Multiversion functions should be at most 'WeakODRLinkage' so that a different
3583 // TU can forward declare the function without causing problems. Particularly
3584 // in the cases of CPUDispatch, this causes issues. This also makes sure we
3585 // work with internal linkage functions, so that the same function name can be
3586 // used with internal linkage in multiple TUs.
3587 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes getMultiversionLinkage(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3588  GlobalDecl GD) {
3589  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3590  if (FD->getFormalLinkage() == InternalLinkage)
3591  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3592  return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
3593 }
3594 
3595 void CodeGenModule::EmitTargetClonesResolver(GlobalDecl GD) {
3596  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3597  assert(FD && "Not a FunctionDecl?");
3598  const auto *TC = FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>();
3599  assert(TC && "Not a target_clones Function?");
3600 
3601  QualType CanonTy = Context.getCanonicalType(FD->getType());
3602  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertType(CanonTy);
3603 
3604  if (const auto *CXXFD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
3605  const CGFunctionInfo &FInfo = getTypes().arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(CXXFD);
3606  DeclTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FInfo);
3607  }
3608 
3609  llvm::Function *ResolverFunc;
3610  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc()) {
3611  auto *IFunc = cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(
3612  GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD, DeclTy, FD));
3613  ResolverFunc = cast<llvm::Function>(IFunc->getResolver());
3614  } else
3615  ResolverFunc =
3616  cast<llvm::Function>(GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD, DeclTy, FD));
3617 
3618  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption, 10> Options;
3619  for (unsigned VersionIndex = 0; VersionIndex < TC->featuresStrs_size();
3620  ++VersionIndex) {
3621  if (!TC->isFirstOfVersion(VersionIndex))
3622  continue;
3623  StringRef Version = TC->getFeatureStr(VersionIndex);
3624  StringRef MangledName =
3625  getMangledName(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(VersionIndex));
3626  llvm::Constant *Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3627  assert(Func &&
3628  "Should have already been created before calling resolver emit");
3629 
3630  StringRef Architecture;
3631  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 1> Feature;
3632 
3633  if (Version.startswith("arch="))
3634  Architecture = Version.drop_front(sizeof("arch=") - 1);
3635  else if (Version != "default")
3636  Feature.push_back(Version);
3637 
3638  Options.emplace_back(cast<llvm::Function>(Func), Architecture, Feature);
3639  }
3640 
3641  const TargetInfo &TI = getTarget();
3642  std::stable_sort(
3643  Options.begin(), Options.end(),
3644  [&TI](const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &LHS,
3645  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RHS) {
3646  return TargetMVPriority(TI, LHS) > TargetMVPriority(TI, RHS);
3647  });
3648  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
3649  CGF.EmitMultiVersionResolver(ResolverFunc, Options);
3650 }
3651 
3652 void CodeGenModule::emitMultiVersionFunctions() {
3653  std::vector<GlobalDecl> MVFuncsToEmit;
3654  MultiVersionFuncs.swap(MVFuncsToEmit);
3655  for (GlobalDecl GD : MVFuncsToEmit) {
3656  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption, 10> Options;
3657  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3658  getContext().forEachMultiversionedFunctionVersion(
3659  FD, [this, &GD, &Options](const FunctionDecl *CurFD) {
3660  GlobalDecl CurGD{
3661  (CurFD->isDefined() ? CurFD->getDefinition() : CurFD)};
3662  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(CurGD);
3663  llvm::Constant *Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3664  if (!Func) {
3665  if (CurFD->isDefined()) {
3666  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(CurGD, nullptr);
3667  Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3668  } else {
3669  const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
3670  getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
3671  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
3672  Func = GetAddrOfFunction(CurGD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false,
3673  /*DontDefer=*/false, ForDefinition);
3674  }
3675  assert(Func && "This should have just been created");
3676  }
3677 
3678  const auto *TA = CurFD->getAttr<TargetAttr>();
3679  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 8> Feats;
3680  TA->getAddedFeatures(Feats);
3681 
3682  Options.emplace_back(cast<llvm::Function>(Func),
3683  TA->getArchitecture(), Feats);
3684  });
3685 
3686  llvm::Function *ResolverFunc;
3687  const TargetInfo &TI = getTarget();
3688 
3689  if (TI.supportsIFunc() || FD->isTargetMultiVersion()) {
3690  ResolverFunc = cast<llvm::Function>(
3691  GetGlobalValue((getMangledName(GD) + ".resolver").str()));
3692  ResolverFunc->setLinkage(getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD));
3693  } else {
3694  ResolverFunc = cast<llvm::Function>(GetGlobalValue(getMangledName(GD)));
3695  }
3696 
3697  if (supportsCOMDAT())
3698  ResolverFunc->setComdat(
3699  getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ResolverFunc->getName()));
3700 
3701  llvm::stable_sort(
3702  Options, [&TI](const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &LHS,
3703  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RHS) {
3704  return TargetMVPriority(TI, LHS) > TargetMVPriority(TI, RHS);
3705  });
3706  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
3707  CGF.EmitMultiVersionResolver(ResolverFunc, Options);
3708  }
3709 
3710  // Ensure that any additions to the deferred decls list caused by emitting a
3711  // variant are emitted. This can happen when the variant itself is inline and
3712  // calls a function without linkage.
3713  if (!MVFuncsToEmit.empty())
3714  EmitDeferred();
3715 
3716  // Ensure that any additions to the multiversion funcs list from either the
3717  // deferred decls or the multiversion functions themselves are emitted.
3718  if (!MultiVersionFuncs.empty())
3719  emitMultiVersionFunctions();
3720 }
3721 
3722 void CodeGenModule::emitCPUDispatchDefinition(GlobalDecl GD) {
3723  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3724  assert(FD && "Not a FunctionDecl?");
3725  assert(FD->isCPUDispatchMultiVersion() && "Not a multiversion function?");
3726  const auto *DD = FD->getAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>();
3727  assert(DD && "Not a cpu_dispatch Function?");
3728  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertType(FD->getType());
3729 
3730  if (const auto *CXXFD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
3731  const CGFunctionInfo &FInfo = getTypes().arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(CXXFD);
3732  DeclTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FInfo);
3733  }
3734 
3735  StringRef ResolverName = getMangledName(GD);
3736  UpdateMultiVersionNames(GD, FD, ResolverName);
3737 
3738  llvm::Type *ResolverType;
3739  GlobalDecl ResolverGD;
3740  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc()) {
3741  ResolverType = llvm::FunctionType::get(
3742  llvm::PointerType::get(DeclTy,
3743  Context.getTargetAddressSpace(FD->getType())),
3744  false);
3745  }
3746  else {
3747  ResolverType = DeclTy;
3748  ResolverGD = GD;
3749  }
3750 
3751  auto *ResolverFunc = cast<llvm::Function>(GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
3752  ResolverName, ResolverType, ResolverGD, /*ForVTable=*/false));
3753  ResolverFunc->setLinkage(getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD));
3754  if (supportsCOMDAT())
3755  ResolverFunc->setComdat(
3756  getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ResolverFunc->getName()));
3757 
3758  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption, 10> Options;
3759  const TargetInfo &Target = getTarget();
3760  unsigned Index = 0;
3761  for (const IdentifierInfo *II : DD->cpus()) {
3762  // Get the name of the target function so we can look it up/create it.
3763  std::string MangledName = getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, true) +
3764  getCPUSpecificMangling(*this, II->getName());
3765 
3766  llvm::Constant *Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3767 
3768  if (!Func) {
3769  GlobalDecl ExistingDecl = Manglings.lookup(MangledName);
3770  if (ExistingDecl.getDecl() &&
3771  ExistingDecl.getDecl()->getAsFunction()->isDefined()) {
3772  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(ExistingDecl, nullptr);
3773  Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3774  } else {
3775  if (!ExistingDecl.getDecl())
3776  ExistingDecl = GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(Index);
3777 
3778  Func = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
3779  MangledName, DeclTy, ExistingDecl,
3780  /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/true,
3781  /*IsThunk=*/false, llvm::AttributeList(), ForDefinition);
3782  }
3783  }
3784 
3785  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 32> Features;
3786  Target.getCPUSpecificCPUDispatchFeatures(II->getName(), Features);
3787  llvm::transform(Features, Features.begin(),
3788  [](StringRef Str) { return Str.substr(1); });
3789  llvm::erase_if(Features, [&Target](StringRef Feat) {
3790  return !Target.validateCpuSupports(Feat);
3791  });
3792  Options.emplace_back(cast<llvm::Function>(Func), StringRef{}, Features);
3793  ++Index;
3794  }
3795 
3796  llvm::stable_sort(
3797  Options, [](const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &LHS,
3798  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RHS) {
3799  return llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(LHS.Conditions.Features) >
3800  llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(RHS.Conditions.Features);
3801  });
3802 
3803  // If the list contains multiple 'default' versions, such as when it contains
3804  // 'pentium' and 'generic', don't emit the call to the generic one (since we
3805  // always run on at least a 'pentium'). We do this by deleting the 'least
3806  // advanced' (read, lowest mangling letter).
3807  while (Options.size() > 1 &&
3808  llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(
3809  (Options.end() - 2)->Conditions.Features) == 0) {
3810  StringRef LHSName = (Options.end() - 2)->Function->getName();
3811  StringRef RHSName = (Options.end() - 1)->Function->getName();
3812  if (LHSName.compare(RHSName) < 0)
3813  Options.erase(Options.end() - 2);
3814  else
3815  Options.erase(Options.end() - 1);
3816  }
3817 
3818  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
3819  CGF.EmitMultiVersionResolver(ResolverFunc, Options);
3820 
3821  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc()) {
3822  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD);
3823  auto *IFunc = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(
3824  GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD, DeclTy, FD));
3825 
3826  // Fix up function declarations that were created for cpu_specific before
3827  // cpu_dispatch was known
3828  if (!dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(IFunc)) {
3829  assert(cast<llvm::Function>(IFunc)->isDeclaration());
3830  auto *GI = llvm::GlobalIFunc::create(DeclTy, 0, Linkage, "", ResolverFunc,
3831  &getModule());
3832  GI->takeName(IFunc);
3833  IFunc->replaceAllUsesWith(GI);
3834  IFunc->eraseFromParent();
3835  IFunc = GI;
3836  }
3837 
3838  std::string AliasName = getMangledNameImpl(
3839  *this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
3840  llvm::Constant *AliasFunc = GetGlobalValue(AliasName);
3841  if (!AliasFunc) {
3842  auto *GA = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(DeclTy, 0, Linkage, AliasName, IFunc,
3843  &getModule());
3844  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GA);
3845  }
3846  }
3847 }
3848 
3849 /// If a dispatcher for the specified mangled name is not in the module, create
3850 /// and return an llvm Function with the specified type.
3851 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(
3852  GlobalDecl GD, llvm::Type *DeclTy, const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3853  std::string MangledName =
3854  getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
3855 
3856  // Holds the name of the resolver, in ifunc mode this is the ifunc (which has
3857  // a separate resolver).
3858  std::string ResolverName = MangledName;
3859  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc())
3860  ResolverName += ".ifunc";
3861  else if (FD->isTargetMultiVersion())
3862  ResolverName += ".resolver";
3863 
3864  // If this already exists, just return that one.
3865  if (llvm::GlobalValue *ResolverGV = GetGlobalValue(ResolverName))
3866  return ResolverGV;
3867 
3868  // Since this is the first time we've created this IFunc, make sure
3869  // that we put this multiversioned function into the list to be
3870  // replaced later if necessary (target multiversioning only).
3871  if (FD->isTargetMultiVersion())
3872  MultiVersionFuncs.push_back(GD);
3873  else if (FD->isTargetClonesMultiVersion()) {
3874  // In target_clones multiversioning, make sure we emit this if used.
3875  auto DDI =
3876  DeferredDecls.find(getMangledName(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(0)));
3877  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end()) {
3878  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
3879  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
3880  } else {
3881  // Emit the symbol of the 1st variant, so that the deferred decls know we
3882  // need it, otherwise the only global value will be the resolver/ifunc,
3883  // which end up getting broken if we search for them with GetGlobalValue'.
3884  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
3885  getMangledName(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(0)), DeclTy, FD,
3886  /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/true,
3887  /*IsThunk=*/false, llvm::AttributeList(), ForDefinition);
3888  }
3889  }
3890 
3891  // For cpu_specific, don't create an ifunc yet because we don't know if the
3892  // cpu_dispatch will be emitted in this translation unit.
3893  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc() && !FD->isCPUSpecificMultiVersion()) {
3894  llvm::Type *ResolverType = llvm::FunctionType::get(
3895  llvm::PointerType::get(
3896  DeclTy, getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(FD->getType())),
3897  false);
3898  llvm::Constant *Resolver = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
3899  MangledName + ".resolver", ResolverType, GlobalDecl{},
3900  /*ForVTable=*/false);
3901  llvm::GlobalIFunc *GIF =
3902  llvm::GlobalIFunc::create(DeclTy, 0, getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD),
3903  "", Resolver, &getModule());
3904  GIF->setName(ResolverName);
3905  SetCommonAttributes(FD, GIF);
3906 
3907  return GIF;
3908  }
3909 
3910  llvm::Constant *Resolver = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
3911  ResolverName, DeclTy, GlobalDecl{}, /*ForVTable=*/false);
3912  assert(isa<llvm::GlobalValue>(Resolver) &&
3913  "Resolver should be created for the first time");
3914  SetCommonAttributes(FD, cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Resolver));
3915  return Resolver;
3916 }
3917 
3918 /// GetOrCreateLLVMFunction - If the specified mangled name is not in the
3919 /// module, create and return an llvm Function with the specified type. If there
3920 /// is something in the module with the specified name, return it potentially
3921 /// bitcasted to the right type.
3922 ///
3923 /// If D is non-null, it specifies a decl that correspond to this. This is used
3924 /// to set the attributes on the function when it is first created.
3925 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
3926  StringRef MangledName, llvm::Type *Ty, GlobalDecl GD, bool ForVTable,
3927  bool DontDefer, bool IsThunk, llvm::AttributeList ExtraAttrs,
3928  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
3929  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
3930 
3931  // Any attempts to use a MultiVersion function should result in retrieving
3932  // the iFunc instead. Name Mangling will handle the rest of the changes.
3933  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3934  // For the device mark the function as one that should be emitted.
3935  if (getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice && OpenMPRuntime &&
3936  !OpenMPRuntime->markAsGlobalTarget(GD) && FD->isDefined() &&
3937  !DontDefer && !IsForDefinition) {
3938  if (const FunctionDecl *FDDef = FD->getDefinition()) {
3939  GlobalDecl GDDef;
3940  if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(FDDef))
3941  GDDef = GlobalDecl(CD, GD.getCtorType());
3942  else if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(FDDef))
3943  GDDef = GlobalDecl(DD, GD.getDtorType());
3944  else
3945  GDDef = GlobalDecl(FDDef);
3946  EmitGlobal(GDDef);
3947  }
3948  }
3949 
3950  if (FD->isMultiVersion()) {
3951  UpdateMultiVersionNames(GD, FD, MangledName);
3952  if (!IsForDefinition)
3953  return GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD, Ty, FD);
3954  }
3955  }
3956 
3957  // Lookup the entry, lazily creating it if necessary.
3958  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3959  if (Entry) {
3960  if (WeakRefReferences.erase(Entry)) {
3961  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
3962  if (FD && !FD->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
3963  Entry->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage);
3964  }
3965 
3966  // Handle dropped DLL attributes.
3967  if (D && !D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() && !D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) {
3968  Entry->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
3969  setDSOLocal(Entry);
3970  }
3971 
3972  // If there are two attempts to define the same mangled name, issue an
3973  // error.
3974  if (IsForDefinition && !Entry->isDeclaration()) {
3975  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
3976  // Check that GD is not yet in DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions is required
3977  // to make sure that we issue an error only once.
3978  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(MangledName, OtherGD) &&
3979  (GD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl() !=
3980  OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()) &&
3981  DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions.insert(GD).second) {
3982  getDiags().Report(D->getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_mangled_name)
3983  << MangledName;
3984  getDiags().Report(OtherGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
3985  diag::note_previous_definition);
3986  }
3987  }
3988 
3989  if ((isa<llvm::Function>(Entry) || isa<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Entry)) &&
3990  (Entry->getValueType() == Ty)) {
3991  return Entry;
3992  }
3993 
3994  // Make sure the result is of the correct type.
3995  // (If function is requested for a definition, we always need to create a new
3996  // function, not just return a bitcast.)
3997  if (!IsForDefinition)
3998  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Entry, Ty->getPointerTo());
3999  }
4000 
4001  // This function doesn't have a complete type (for example, the return
4002  // type is an incomplete struct). Use a fake type instead, and make
4003  // sure not to try to set attributes.
4004  bool IsIncompleteFunction = false;
4005 
4006  llvm::FunctionType *FTy;
4007  if (isa<llvm::FunctionType>(Ty)) {
4008  FTy = cast<llvm::FunctionType>(Ty);
4009  } else {
4010  FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, false);
4011  IsIncompleteFunction = true;
4012  }
4013 
4014  llvm::Function *F =
4015  llvm::Function::Create(FTy, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
4016  Entry ? StringRef() : MangledName, &getModule());
4017 
4018  // If we already created a function with the same mangled name (but different
4019  // type) before, take its name and add it to the list of functions to be
4020  // replaced with F at the end of CodeGen.
4021  //
4022  // This happens if there is a prototype for a function (e.g. "int f()") and
4023  // then a definition of a different type (e.g. "int f(int x)").
4024  if (Entry) {
4025  F->takeName(Entry);
4026 
4027  // This might be an implementation of a function without a prototype, in
4028  // which case, try to do special replacement of calls which match the new
4029  // prototype. The really key thing here is that we also potentially drop
4030  // arguments from the call site so as to make a direct call, which makes the
4031  // inliner happier and suppresses a number of optimizer warnings (!) about
4032  // dropping arguments.
4033  if (!Entry->use_empty()) {
4034  ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction(Entry, F);
4035  Entry->removeDeadConstantUsers();
4036  }
4037 
4038  llvm::Constant *BC = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
4039  F, Entry->getValueType()->getPointerTo());
4040  addGlobalValReplacement(Entry, BC);
4041  }
4042 
4043  assert(F->getName() == MangledName && "name was uniqued!");
4044  if (D)
4045  SetFunctionAttributes(GD, F, IsIncompleteFunction, IsThunk);
4046  if (ExtraAttrs.hasFnAttrs()) {
4047  llvm::AttrBuilder B(F->getContext(), ExtraAttrs.getFnAttrs());
4048  F->addFnAttrs(B);
4049  }
4050 
4051  if (!DontDefer) {
4052  // All MSVC dtors other than the base dtor are linkonce_odr and delegate to
4053  // each other bottoming out with the base dtor. Therefore we emit non-base
4054  // dtors on usage, even if there is no dtor definition in the TU.
4055  if (D && isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(D) &&
4056  getCXXABI().useThunkForDtorVariant(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D),
4057  GD.getDtorType()))
4058  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
4059 
4060  // This is the first use or definition of a mangled name. If there is a
4061  // deferred decl with this name, remember that we need to emit it at the end
4062  // of the file.
4063  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
4064  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end()) {
4065  // Move the potentially referenced deferred decl to the
4066  // DeferredDeclsToEmit list, and remove it from DeferredDecls (since we
4067  // don't need it anymore).
4068  addDeferredDeclToEmit(DDI->second);
4069  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
4070 
4071  // Otherwise, there are cases we have to worry about where we're
4072  // using a declaration for which we must emit a definition but where
4073  // we might not find a top-level definition:
4074  // - member functions defined inline in their classes
4075  // - friend functions defined inline in some class
4076  // - special member functions with implicit definitions
4077  // If we ever change our AST traversal to walk into class methods,
4078  // this will be unnecessary.
4079  //
4080  // We also don't emit a definition for a function if it's going to be an
4081  // entry in a vtable, unless it's already marked as used.
4082  } else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && D) {
4083  // Look for a declaration that's lexically in a record.
4084  for (const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getMostRecentDecl(); FD;
4085  FD = FD->getPreviousDecl()) {
4086  if (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getLexicalDeclContext())) {
4087  if (FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody()) {
4088  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD.getWithDecl(FD));
4089  break;
4090  }
4091  }
4092  }
4093  }
4094  }
4095 
4096  // Make sure the result is of the requested type.
4097  if (!IsIncompleteFunction) {
4098  assert(F->getFunctionType() == Ty);
4099  return F;
4100  }
4101 
4102  llvm::Type *PTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Ty);
4103  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(F, PTy);
4104 }
4105 
4106 /// GetAddrOfFunction - Return the address of the given function. If Ty is
4107 /// non-null, then this function will use the specified type if it has to
4108 /// create it (this occurs when we see a definition of the function).
4109 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfFunction(GlobalDecl GD,
4110  llvm::Type *Ty,
4111  bool ForVTable,
4112  bool DontDefer,
4113  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
4114  assert(!cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl())->isConsteval() &&
4115  "consteval function should never be emitted");
4116  // If there was no specific requested type, just convert it now.
4117  if (!Ty) {
4118  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4119  Ty = getTypes().ConvertType(FD->getType());
4120  }
4121 
4122  // Devirtualized destructor calls may come through here instead of via
4123  // getAddrOfCXXStructor. Make sure we use the MS ABI base destructor instead
4124  // of the complete destructor when necessary.
4125  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
4126  if (getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
4127  GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete &&
4128  DD->getParent()->getNumVBases() == 0)
4129  GD = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Base);
4130  }
4131 
4132  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
4133  auto *F = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(MangledName, Ty, GD, ForVTable, DontDefer,
4134  /*IsThunk=*/false, llvm::AttributeList(),
4135  IsForDefinition);
4136  // Returns kernel handle for HIP kernel stub function.
4137  if (LangOpts.CUDA && !LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice &&
4138  cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl())->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) {
4139  auto *Handle = getCUDARuntime().getKernelHandle(
4140  cast<llvm::Function>(F->stripPointerCasts()), GD);
4141  if (IsForDefinition)
4142  return F;
4143  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Handle, Ty->getPointerTo());
4144  }
4145  return F;
4146 }
4147 
4148 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetFunctionStart(const ValueDecl *Decl) {
4149  llvm::GlobalValue *F =
4150  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetAddrOfFunction(Decl)->stripPointerCasts());
4151 
4152  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(llvm::NoCFIValue::get(F),
4153  llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(VMContext));
4154 }
4155 
4156 static const FunctionDecl *
4157 GetRuntimeFunctionDecl(ASTContext &C, StringRef Name) {
4158  TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = C.getTranslationUnitDecl();
4159  DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
4160 
4161  IdentifierInfo &CII = C.Idents.get(Name);
4162  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&CII))
4163  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Result))
4164  return FD;
4165 
4166  if (!C.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4167  return nullptr;
4168 
4169  // Demangle the premangled name from getTerminateFn()
4170  IdentifierInfo &CXXII =
4171  (Name == "_ZSt9terminatev" || Name == "?terminate@@YAXXZ")
4172  ? C.Idents.get("terminate")
4173  : C.Idents.get(Name);
4174 
4175  for (const auto &N : {"__cxxabiv1", "std"}) {
4176  IdentifierInfo &NS = C.Idents.get(N);
4177  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&NS)) {
4178  const NamespaceDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(Result);
4179  if (auto *LSD = dyn_cast<LinkageSpecDecl>(Result))
4180  for (const auto *Result : LSD->lookup(&NS))
4181  if ((ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(Result)))
4182  break;
4183 
4184  if (ND)
4185  for (const auto *Result : ND->lookup(&CXXII))
4186  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Result))
4187  return FD;
4188  }
4189  }
4190 
4191  return nullptr;
4192 }
4193 
4194 /// CreateRuntimeFunction - Create a new runtime function with the specified
4195 /// type and name.
4196 llvm::FunctionCallee
4197 CodeGenModule::CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType *FTy, StringRef Name,
4198  llvm::AttributeList ExtraAttrs, bool Local,
4199  bool AssumeConvergent) {
4200  if (AssumeConvergent) {
4201  ExtraAttrs =
4202  ExtraAttrs.addFnAttribute(VMContext, llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
4203  }
4204 
4205  llvm::Constant *C =
4206  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(Name, FTy, GlobalDecl(), /*ForVTable=*/false,
4207  /*DontDefer=*/false, /*IsThunk=*/false,
4208  ExtraAttrs);
4209 
4210  if (auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(C)) {
4211  if (F->empty()) {
4212  F->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
4213 
4214  // In Windows Itanium environments, try to mark runtime functions
4215  // dllimport. For Mingw and MSVC, don't. We don't really know if the user
4216  // will link their standard library statically or dynamically. Marking
4217  // functions imported when they are not imported can cause linker errors
4218  // and warnings.
4219  if (!Local && getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment() &&
4220  !getCodeGenOpts().LTOVisibilityPublicStd) {
4221  const FunctionDecl *FD = GetRuntimeFunctionDecl(Context, Name);
4222  if (!FD || FD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
4223  F->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
4224  F->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
4225  }
4226  }
4227  setDSOLocal(F);
4228  }
4229  }
4230 
4231  return {FTy, C};
4232 }
4233 
4234 /// isTypeConstant - Determine whether an object of this type can be emitted
4235 /// as a constant.
4236 ///
4237 /// If ExcludeCtor is true, the duration when the object's constructor runs
4238 /// will not be considered. The caller will need to verify that the object is
4239 /// not written to during its construction.
4240 bool CodeGenModule::isTypeConstant(QualType Ty, bool ExcludeCtor) {
4241  if (!Ty.isConstant(Context) && !Ty->isReferenceType())
4242  return false;
4243 
4244  if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4245  if (const CXXRecordDecl *Record
4246  = Context.getBaseElementType(Ty)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4247  return ExcludeCtor && !Record->hasMutableFields() &&
4248  Record->hasTrivialDestructor();
4249  }
4250 
4251  return true;
4252 }
4253 
4254 static void maybeEmitPipeStorageMetadata(const VarDecl *D,
4255  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV,
4256  CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4257  // TODO: Applicable only on pipe storages. Currently they are defined
4258  // as structures inside of SYCL headers. Add a check for pipe_storage_t
4259  // when it ready.
4260  QualType PipeTy = D->getType();
4261  if (!PipeTy->isStructureType())
4262  return;
4263 
4264  if (const auto *IOAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr>()) {
4265  const auto *CE = cast<ConstantExpr>(IOAttr->getID());
4266  Optional<llvm::APSInt> ID = CE->getResultAsAPSInt();
4267  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
4268 
4269  llvm::Metadata *AttrMDArgs[] = {
4270  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
4271  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(Context), ID->getSExtValue()))};
4272  GV->setMetadata(IOAttr->getSpelling(),
4273  llvm::MDNode::get(Context, AttrMDArgs));
4274  }
4275 }
4276 
4277 /// GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal - If the specified mangled name is not in the module,
4278 /// create and return an llvm GlobalVariable with the specified type and address
4279 /// space. If there is something in the module with the specified name, return
4280 /// it potentially bitcasted to the right type.
4281 ///
4282 /// If D is non-null, it specifies a decl that correspond to this. This is used
4283 /// to set the attributes on the global when it is first created.
4284 ///
4285 /// If IsForDefinition is true, it is guaranteed that an actual global with
4286 /// type Ty will be returned, not conversion of a variable with the same
4287 /// mangled name but some other type.
4288 llvm::Constant *
4289 CodeGenModule::GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(StringRef MangledName, llvm::Type *Ty,
4290  LangAS AddrSpace, const VarDecl *D,
4291  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
4292  // Lookup the entry, lazily creating it if necessary.
4293  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4294  unsigned TargetAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AddrSpace);
4295  if (Entry) {
4296  if (WeakRefReferences.erase(Entry)) {
4297  if (D && !D->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
4298  Entry->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage);
4299  }
4300 
4301  // Handle dropped DLL attributes.
4302  if (D && !D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() && !D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
4303  Entry->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
4304 
4305  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && !LangOpts.OpenMPSimd && D)
4306  getOpenMPRuntime().registerTargetGlobalVariable(D, Entry);
4307 
4308  if (Entry->getValueType() == Ty && Entry->getAddressSpace() == TargetAS)
4309  return Entry;
4310 
4311  // If there are two attempts to define the same mangled name, issue an
4312  // error.
4313  if (IsForDefinition && !Entry->isDeclaration()) {
4314  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
4315  const VarDecl *OtherD;
4316 
4317  // Check that D is not yet in DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions is required
4318  // to make sure that we issue an error only once.
4319  if (D && lookupRepresentativeDecl(MangledName, OtherGD) &&
4320  (D->getCanonicalDecl() != OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()) &&
4321  (OtherD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(OtherGD.getDecl())) &&
4322  OtherD->hasInit() &&
4323  DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions.insert(D).second) {
4324  getDiags().Report(D->getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_mangled_name)
4325  << MangledName;
4326  getDiags().Report(OtherGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
4327  diag::note_previous_definition);
4328  }
4329  }
4330 
4331  // Make sure the result is of the correct type.
4332  if (Entry->getType()->getAddressSpace() != TargetAS) {
4333  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(Entry,
4334  Ty->getPointerTo(TargetAS));
4335  }
4336 
4337  // (If global is requested for a definition, we always need to create a new
4338  // global, not just return a bitcast.)
4339  if (!IsForDefinition)
4340  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Entry, Ty->getPointerTo(TargetAS));
4341  }
4342 
4343  auto DAddrSpace = GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(D);
4344 
4345  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
4346  getModule(), Ty, false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
4347  MangledName, nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
4348  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(DAddrSpace));
4349 
4350  // If we already created a global with the same mangled name (but different
4351  // type) before, take its name and remove it from its parent.
4352  if (Entry) {
4353  GV->takeName(Entry);
4354 
4355  if (!Entry->use_empty()) {
4356  llvm::Constant *NewPtrForOldDecl =
4357  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, Entry->getType());
4358  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(NewPtrForOldDecl);
4359  }
4360 
4361  Entry->eraseFromParent();
4362  }
4363 
4364  // This is the first use or definition of a mangled name. If there is a
4365  // deferred decl with this name, remember that we need to emit it at the end
4366  // of the file.
4367  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
4368  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end()) {
4369  // Move the potentially referenced deferred decl to the DeferredDeclsToEmit
4370  // list, and remove it from DeferredDecls (since we don't need it anymore).
4371  addDeferredDeclToEmit(DDI->second);
4372  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
4373  }
4374 
4375  // Handle things which are present even on external declarations.
4376  if (D) {
4377  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && !LangOpts.OpenMPSimd)
4378  getOpenMPRuntime().registerTargetGlobalVariable(D, GV);
4379 
4380  // FIXME: This code is overly simple and should be merged with other global
4381  // handling.
4382  GV->setConstant(isTypeConstant(D->getType(), false));
4383 
4384  GV->setAlignment(getContext().getDeclAlign(D).getAsAlign());
4385 
4386  setLinkageForGV(GV, D);
4387 
4388  if (D->getTLSKind()) {
4389  if (D->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic)
4390  CXXThreadLocals.push_back(D);
4391  setTLSMode(GV, *D);
4392  }
4393 
4394  setGVProperties(GV, D);
4395 
4396  // If required by the ABI, treat declarations of static data members with
4397  // inline initializers as definitions.
4398  if (getContext().isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(D)) {
4399  EmitGlobalVarDefinition(D);
4400  }
4401 
4402  // Emit section information for extern variables.
4403  if (D->hasExternalStorage()) {
4404  if (const SectionAttr *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
4405  GV->setSection(SA->getName());
4406  }
4407 
4408  // Handle XCore specific ABI requirements.
4409  if (getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::xcore &&
4410  D->getLanguageLinkage() == CLanguageLinkage &&
4411  D->getType().isConstant(Context) &&
4412  isExternallyVisible(D->getLinkageAndVisibility().getLinkage()))
4413  GV->setSection(".cp.rodata");
4414 
4415  // Check if we a have a const declaration with an initializer, we may be
4416  // able to emit it as available_externally to expose it's value to the
4417  // optimizer.
4418  if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && GV->hasExternalLinkage() &&
4419  D->getType().isConstQualified() && !GV->hasInitializer() &&
4420  !D->hasDefinition() && D->hasInit() && !D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
4421  const auto *Record =
4422  Context.getBaseElementType(D->getType())->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4423  bool HasMutableFields = Record && Record->hasMutableFields();
4424  if (!HasMutableFields) {
4425  const VarDecl *InitDecl;
4426  const Expr *InitExpr = D->getAnyInitializer(InitDecl);
4427  if (InitExpr) {
4428  ConstantEmitter emitter(*this);
4429  llvm::Constant *Init = emitter.tryEmitForInitializer(*InitDecl);
4430  if (Init) {
4431  auto *InitType = Init->getType();
4432  if (GV->getValueType() != InitType) {
4433  // The type of the initializer does not match the definition.
4434  // This happens when an initializer has a different type from
4435  // the type of the global (because of padding at the end of a
4436  // structure for instance).
4437  GV->setName(StringRef());
4438  // Make a new global with the correct type, this is now guaranteed
4439  // to work.
4440  auto *NewGV = cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
4441  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(D, InitType, IsForDefinition)
4442  ->stripPointerCasts());
4443 
4444  // Erase the old global, since it is no longer used.
4445  GV->eraseFromParent();
4446  GV = NewGV;
4447  } else {
4448  GV->setInitializer(Init);
4449  GV->setConstant(true);
4450  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
4451  }
4452  emitter.finalize(GV);
4453  }
4454  }
4455  }
4456  }
4457 
4458  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
4459  maybeEmitPipeStorageMetadata(D, GV, *this);
4460  }
4461 
4462  if (GV->isDeclaration()) {
4463  getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(D, GV, *this);
4464  // External HIP managed variables needed to be recorded for transformation
4465  // in both device and host compilations.
4466  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && D && D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() &&
4467  D->hasExternalStorage())
4468  getCUDARuntime().handleVarRegistration(D, *GV);
4469  }
4470 
4471  LangAS ExpectedAS =
4472  D ? D->getType().getAddressSpace()
4473  : (LangOpts.OpenCL ? LangAS::opencl_global : LangAS::Default);
4474  assert(getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(ExpectedAS) == TargetAS);
4475  if (DAddrSpace != ExpectedAS) {
4476  return getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
4477  *this, GV, DAddrSpace, ExpectedAS, Ty->getPointerTo(TargetAS));
4478  }
4479 
4480  return GV;
4481 }
4482 
4483 llvm::Constant *
4484 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobal(GlobalDecl GD, ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
4485  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
4486 
4487  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(D) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(D))
4488  return getAddrOfCXXStructor(GD, /*FnInfo=*/nullptr, /*FnType=*/nullptr,
4489  /*DontDefer=*/false, IsForDefinition);
4490 
4491  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
4492  auto FInfo =
4493  &getTypes().arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D));
4494  auto Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(*FInfo);
4495  return GetAddrOfFunction(GD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/false,
4496  IsForDefinition);
4497  }
4498 
4499  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4500  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
4501  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4502  return GetAddrOfFunction(GD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/false,
4503  IsForDefinition);
4504  }
4505 
4506  return GetAddrOfGlobalVar(cast<VarDecl>(D), /*Ty=*/nullptr, IsForDefinition);
4507 }
4508 
4509 llvm::GlobalVariable *CodeGenModule::CreateOrReplaceCXXRuntimeVariable(
4510  StringRef Name, llvm::Type *Ty, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage,
4511  unsigned Alignment) {
4512  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name);
4513  llvm::GlobalVariable *OldGV = nullptr;
4514 
4515  if (GV) {
4516  // Check if the variable has the right type.
4517  if (GV->getValueType() == Ty)
4518  return GV;
4519 
4520  // Because C++ name mangling, the only way we can end up with an already
4521  // existing global with the same name is if it has been declared extern "C".
4522  assert(GV->isDeclaration() && "Declaration has wrong type!");
4523  OldGV = GV;
4524  }
4525 
4526  // Create a new variable.
4527  GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Ty, /*isConstant=*/true,
4528  Linkage, nullptr, Name);
4529 
4530  if (OldGV) {
4531  // Replace occurrences of the old variable if needed.
4532  GV->takeName(OldGV);
4533 
4534  if (!OldGV->use_empty()) {
4535  llvm::Constant *NewPtrForOldDecl =
4536  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, OldGV->getType());
4537  OldGV->replaceAllUsesWith(NewPtrForOldDecl);
4538  }
4539 
4540  OldGV->eraseFromParent();
4541  }
4542 
4543  if (supportsCOMDAT() && GV->isWeakForLinker() &&
4544  !GV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage())
4545  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
4546 
4547  GV->setAlignment(llvm::MaybeAlign(Alignment));
4548 
4549  return GV;
4550 }
4551 
4552 /// GetAddrOfGlobalVar - Return the llvm::Constant for the address of the
4553 /// given global variable. If Ty is non-null and if the global doesn't exist,
4554 /// then it will be created with the specified type instead of whatever the
4555 /// normal requested type would be. If IsForDefinition is true, it is guaranteed
4556 /// that an actual global with type Ty will be returned, not conversion of a
4557 /// variable with the same mangled name but some other type.
4558 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobalVar(const VarDecl *D,
4559  llvm::Type *Ty,
4560  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
4561  assert(D->hasGlobalStorage() && "Not a global variable");
4562  QualType ASTTy = D->getType();
4563  if (!Ty)
4564  Ty = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ASTTy);
4565 
4566  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(D);
4567  return GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(MangledName, Ty, ASTTy.getAddressSpace(), D,
4568  IsForDefinition);
4569 }
4570 
4571 /// CreateRuntimeVariable - Create a new runtime global variable with the
4572 /// specified type and name.
4573 llvm::Constant *
4574 CodeGenModule::CreateRuntimeVariable(llvm::Type *Ty,
4575  StringRef Name) {
4576  LangAS AddrSpace = getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL ? LangAS::opencl_global
4577  : LangAS::Default;
4578  auto *Ret = GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(Name, Ty, AddrSpace, nullptr);
4579  setDSOLocal(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Ret->stripPointerCasts()));
4580  return Ret;
4581 }
4582 
4583 void CodeGenModule::EmitTentativeDefinition(const VarDecl *D) {
4584  assert(!D->getInit() && "Cannot emit definite definitions here!");
4585 
4586  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(D);
4587  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4588 
4589  // We already have a definition, not declaration, with the same mangled name.
4590  // Emitting of declaration is not required (and actually overwrites emitted
4591  // definition).
4592  if (GV && !GV->isDeclaration())
4593  return;
4594 
4595  // If we have not seen a reference to this variable yet, place it into the
4596  // deferred declarations table to be emitted if needed later.
4597  if (!MustBeEmitted(D) && !GV) {
4598  DeferredDecls[MangledName] = D;
4599  return;
4600  }
4601 
4602  // The tentative definition is the only definition.
4603  EmitGlobalVarDefinition(D);
4604 }
4605 
4606 void CodeGenModule::EmitExternalDeclaration(const VarDecl *D) {
4607  EmitExternalVarDeclaration(D);
4608 }
