4610 CharUnits CodeGenModule::GetTargetTypeStoreSize(llvm::Type *Ty) const {
4611  return Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(
4612  getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSizeInBits(Ty));
4613 }
4614 
4615 LangAS CodeGenModule::GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(const VarDecl *D) {
4616  if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
4617  LangAS AS = D ? D->getType().getAddressSpace() : LangAS::opencl_global;
4618  assert(AS == LangAS::opencl_global ||
4619  AS == LangAS::opencl_global_device ||
4620  AS == LangAS::opencl_global_host ||
4621  AS == LangAS::opencl_constant ||
4622  AS == LangAS::opencl_local ||
4623  AS >= LangAS::FirstTargetAddressSpace);
4624  return AS;
4625  }
4626 
4627  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && D) {
4628  auto *Scope = D->getAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>();
4629  if (Scope && Scope->isWorkGroup())
4630  return LangAS::sycl_local;
4631  }
4632 
4633  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice &&
4634  (!D || D->getType().getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default))
4635  return LangAS::sycl_global;
4636 
4637  if (LangOpts.CUDA && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
4638  if (D && D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>())
4639  return LangAS::cuda_constant;
4640  else if (D && D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>())
4641  return LangAS::cuda_shared;
4642  else if (D && D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
4643  return LangAS::cuda_device;
4644  else if (D && D->getType().isConstQualified())
4645  return LangAS::cuda_constant;
4646  else
4647  return LangAS::cuda_device;
4648  }
4649 
4650  if (LangOpts.OpenMP) {
4651  LangAS AS;
4652  if (OpenMPRuntime->hasAllocateAttributeForGlobalVar(D, AS))
4653  return AS;
4654  }
4655  return getTargetCodeGenInfo().getGlobalVarAddressSpace(*this, D);
4656 }
4657 
4658 LangAS CodeGenModule::GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace() const {
4659  // OpenCL v1.2 s6.5.3: a string literal is in the constant address space.
4660  if (LangOpts.OpenCL)
4661  return LangAS::opencl_constant;
4662  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
4663  return LangAS::sycl_global;
4664  if (LangOpts.HIP && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice && getTriple().isSPIRV())
4665  // For HIPSPV map literals to cuda_device (maps to CrossWorkGroup in SPIR-V)
4666  // instead of default AS (maps to Generic in SPIR-V). Otherwise, we end up
4667  // with OpVariable instructions with Generic storage class which is not
4668  // allowed (SPIR-V V1.6 s3.42.8). Also, mapping literals to SPIR-V
4669  // UniformConstant storage class is not viable as pointers to it may not be
4670  // casted to Generic pointers which are used to model HIP's "flat" pointers.
4671  return LangAS::cuda_device;
4672  if (auto AS = getTarget().getConstantAddressSpace())
4673  return AS.getValue();
4674  return LangAS::Default;
4675 }
4676 
4677 // In address space agnostic languages, string literals are in default address
4678 // space in AST. However, certain targets (e.g. amdgcn) request them to be
4679 // emitted in constant address space in LLVM IR. To be consistent with other
4680 // parts of AST, string literal global variables in constant address space
4681 // need to be casted to default address space before being put into address
4682 // map and referenced by other part of CodeGen.
4683 // In OpenCL, string literals are in constant address space in AST, therefore
4684 // they should not be casted to default address space.
4685 static llvm::Constant *
4686 castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(CodeGenModule &CGM,
4687  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV) {
4688  llvm::Constant *Cast = GV;
4689  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4690  auto AS = CGM.GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace();
4691  if (AS != LangAS::Default)
4692  Cast = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
4693  CGM, GV, AS, LangAS::Default,
4694  GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(
4695  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
4696  }
4697  return Cast;
4698 }
4699 
4700 template<typename SomeDecl>
4701 void CodeGenModule::MaybeHandleStaticInExternC(const SomeDecl *D,
4702  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
4703  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4704  return;
4705 
4706  // Must have 'used' attribute, or else inline assembly can't rely on
4707  // the name existing.
4708  if (!D->template hasAttr<UsedAttr>())
4709  return;
4710 
4711  // Must have internal linkage and an ordinary name.
4712  if (!D->getIdentifier() || D->getFormalLinkage() != InternalLinkage)
4713  return;
4714 
4715  // Must be in an extern "C" context. Entities declared directly within
4716  // a record are not extern "C" even if the record is in such a context.
4717  const SomeDecl *First = D->getFirstDecl();
4718  if (First->getDeclContext()->isRecord() || !First->isInExternCContext())
4719  return;
4720 
4721  // OK, this is an internal linkage entity inside an extern "C" linkage
4722  // specification. Make a note of that so we can give it the "expected"
4723  // mangled name if nothing else is using that name.
4724  std::pair<StaticExternCMap::iterator, bool> R =
4725  StaticExternCValues.insert(std::make_pair(D->getIdentifier(), GV));
4726 
4727  // If we have multiple internal linkage entities with the same name
4728  // in extern "C" regions, none of them gets that name.
4729  if (!R.second)
4730  R.first->second = nullptr;
4731 }
4732 
4733 static bool shouldBeInCOMDAT(CodeGenModule &CGM, const Decl &D) {
4734  if (!CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
4735  return false;
4736 
4737  if (D.hasAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
4738  return true;
4739 
4740  GVALinkage Linkage;
4741  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(&D))
4742  Linkage = CGM.getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD);
4743  else
4744  Linkage = CGM.getContext().GetGVALinkageForFunction(cast<FunctionDecl>(&D));
4745 
4746  switch (Linkage) {
4747  case GVA_Internal:
4748  case GVA_AvailableExternally:
4749  case GVA_StrongExternal:
4750  return false;
4751  case GVA_DiscardableODR:
4752  case GVA_StrongODR:
4753  return true;
4754  }
4755  llvm_unreachable("No such linkage");
4756 }
4757 
4758 void CodeGenModule::maybeSetTrivialComdat(const Decl &D,
4759  llvm::GlobalObject &GO) {
4760  if (!shouldBeInCOMDAT(*this, D))
4761  return;
4762  GO.setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GO.getName()));
4763 }
4764 
4765 void CodeGenModule::generateIntelFPGAAnnotation(
4766  const Decl *D, llvm::SmallString<256> &AnnotStr) {
4767  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(AnnotStr);
4768  if (D->hasAttr<IntelFPGARegisterAttr>())
4769  Out << "{register:1}";
4770  if (auto const *MA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGAMemoryAttr>()) {
4771  IntelFPGAMemoryAttr::MemoryKind Kind = MA->getKind();
4772  Out << "{memory:";
4773  switch (Kind) {
4774  case IntelFPGAMemoryAttr::MLAB:
4775  case IntelFPGAMemoryAttr::BlockRAM:
4776  Out << IntelFPGAMemoryAttr::ConvertMemoryKindToStr(Kind);
4777  break;
4778  case IntelFPGAMemoryAttr::Default:
4779  Out << "DEFAULT";
4780  break;
4781  }
4782  Out << '}';
4783  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(D)) {
4784  Out << "{sizeinfo:";
4785  // D can't be of type FunctionDecl (as no memory attribute can be applied
4786  // to a function)
4787  QualType ElementTy = DD->getType();
4788  QualType TmpTy = ElementTy->isArrayType()
4789  ? getContext().getBaseElementType(ElementTy)
4790  : ElementTy;
4791  Out << getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(TmpTy).getQuantity();
4792  // Add the dimension of the array to Out.
4793  while (const auto *AT = getContext().getAsArrayType(ElementTy)) {
4794  // Expecting only constant array types, assert otherwise.
4795  const auto *CAT = cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT);
4796  Out << "," << CAT->getSize();
4797  ElementTy = CAT->getElementType();
4798  }
4799  Out << '}';
4800  }
4801  }
4802  if (D->hasAttr<IntelFPGASinglePumpAttr>())
4803  Out << "{pump:1}";
4804  if (D->hasAttr<IntelFPGADoublePumpAttr>())
4805  Out << "{pump:2}";
4806  if (const auto *BWA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGABankWidthAttr>()) {
4807  llvm::APSInt BWAInt = BWA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
4808  Out << '{' << BWA->getSpelling() << ':' << BWAInt << '}';
4809  }
4810  if (const auto *PCA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGAPrivateCopiesAttr>()) {
4811  llvm::APSInt PCAInt = PCA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
4812  Out << '{' << PCA->getSpelling() << ':' << PCAInt << '}';
4813  }
4814  if (const auto *NBA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGANumBanksAttr>()) {
4815  llvm::APSInt NBAInt = NBA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
4816  Out << '{' << NBA->getSpelling() << ':' << NBAInt << '}';
4817  }
4818  if (const auto *BBA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGABankBitsAttr>()) {
4819  Out << '{' << BBA->getSpelling() << ':';
4820  for (IntelFPGABankBitsAttr::args_iterator I = BBA->args_begin(),
4821  E = BBA->args_end();
4822  I != E; ++I) {
4823  if (I != BBA->args_begin())
4824  Out << ',';
4825  llvm::APSInt BBAInt = (*I)->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
4826  Out << BBAInt;
4827  }
4828  Out << '}';
4829  }
4830  if (const auto *MRA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGAMaxReplicatesAttr>()) {
4831  llvm::APSInt MRAInt = MRA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
4832  Out << '{' << MRA->getSpelling() << ':' << MRAInt << '}';
4833  }
4834  if (const auto *MA = D->getAttr<IntelFPGAMergeAttr>()) {
4835  Out << '{' << MA->getSpelling() << ':' << MA->getName() << ':'
4836  << MA->getDirection() << '}';
4837  }
4838  if (D->hasAttr<IntelFPGASimpleDualPortAttr>())
4839  Out << "{simple_dual_port:1}";
4840  if (const auto *FP2D = D->getAttr<IntelFPGAForcePow2DepthAttr>()) {
4841  llvm::APSInt FP2DInt =
4842  FP2D->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
4843  Out << '{' << FP2D->getSpelling() << ':' << FP2DInt << '}';
4844  }
4845 }
4846 
4847 void CodeGenModule::addGlobalIntelFPGAAnnotation(const VarDecl *VD,
4848  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
4849  SmallString<256> AnnotStr;
4850  generateIntelFPGAAnnotation(VD, AnnotStr);
4851  if (!AnnotStr.empty()) {
4852  // Get the globals for file name, annotation, and the line number.
4853  llvm::Constant *AnnoGV = EmitAnnotationString(AnnotStr),
4854  *UnitGV = EmitAnnotationUnit(VD->getLocation()),
4855  *LineNoCst = EmitAnnotationLineNo(VD->getLocation());
4856 
4857  llvm::Constant *ASZeroGV = GV;
4858  if (GV->getAddressSpace() != 0)
4859  ASZeroGV = llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
4860  GV, GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(0));
4861 
4862  // Create the ConstantStruct for the global annotation.
4863  llvm::Constant *Fields[5] = {
4864  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(ASZeroGV, Int8PtrTy),
4865  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(AnnoGV, Int8PtrTy),
4866  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(UnitGV, Int8PtrTy), LineNoCst,
4867  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(Int8PtrTy)};
4868  Annotations.push_back(llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields));
4869  }
4870 }
4871 
4872 /// Pass IsTentative as true if you want to create a tentative definition.
4873 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalVarDefinition(const VarDecl *D,
4874  bool IsTentative) {
4875  // OpenCL global variables of sampler type are translated to function calls,
4876  // therefore no need to be translated.
4877  QualType ASTTy = D->getType();
4878  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL && ASTTy->isSamplerT())
4879  return;
4880 
4881  // If this is OpenMP device, check if it is legal to emit this global
4882  // normally.
4883  if (LangOpts.OpenMPIsDevice && OpenMPRuntime &&
4884  OpenMPRuntime->emitTargetGlobalVariable(D))
4885  return;
4886 
4887  llvm::TrackingVH<llvm::Constant> Init;
4888  bool NeedsGlobalCtor = false;
4889  bool NeedsGlobalDtor =
4890  D->needsDestruction(getContext()) == QualType::DK_cxx_destructor;
4891 
4892  const VarDecl *InitDecl;
4893  const Expr *InitExpr = D->getAnyInitializer(InitDecl);
4894 
4895  Optional<ConstantEmitter> emitter;
4896 
4897  // CUDA E.2.4.1 "__shared__ variables cannot have an initialization
4898  // as part of their declaration." Sema has already checked for
4899  // error cases, so we just need to set Init to UndefValue.
4900  bool IsCUDASharedVar =
4901  getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>();
4902  // Shadows of initialized device-side global variables are also left
4903  // undefined.
4904  // Managed Variables should be initialized on both host side and device side.
4905  bool IsCUDAShadowVar =
4906  !getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && !D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() &&
4907  (D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() ||
4908  D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>());
4909  bool IsCUDADeviceShadowVar =
4910  getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && !D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() &&
4911  (D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() ||
4912  D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType());
4913  if (getLangOpts().CUDA &&
4914  (IsCUDASharedVar || IsCUDAShadowVar || IsCUDADeviceShadowVar))
4915  Init = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ASTTy));
4916  else if (D->hasAttr<LoaderUninitializedAttr>())
4917  Init = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ASTTy));
4918  else if (!InitExpr) {
4919  // This is a tentative definition; tentative definitions are
4920  // implicitly initialized with { 0 }.
4921  //
4922  // Note that tentative definitions are only emitted at the end of
4923  // a translation unit, so they should never have incomplete
4924  // type. In addition, EmitTentativeDefinition makes sure that we
4925  // never attempt to emit a tentative definition if a real one
4926  // exists. A use may still exists, however, so we still may need
4927  // to do a RAUW.
4928  assert(!ASTTy->isIncompleteType() && "Unexpected incomplete type");
4929  Init = EmitNullConstant(D->getType());
4930  } else {
4931  initializedGlobalDecl = GlobalDecl(D);
4932  emitter.emplace(*this);
4933  llvm::Constant *Initializer = emitter->tryEmitForInitializer(*InitDecl);
4934  if (!Initializer) {
4935  QualType T = InitExpr->getType();
4936  if (D->getType()->isReferenceType())
4937  T = D->getType();
4938 
4939  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4940  Init = EmitNullConstant(T);
4941  NeedsGlobalCtor = true;
4942  } else {
4943  ErrorUnsupported(D, "static initializer");
4944  Init = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertType(T));
4945  }
4946  } else {
4947  Init = Initializer;
4948  // We don't need an initializer, so remove the entry for the delayed
4949  // initializer position (just in case this entry was delayed) if we
4950  // also don't need to register a destructor.
4951  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !NeedsGlobalDtor)
4952  DelayedCXXInitPosition.erase(D);
4953  }
4954  }
4955 
4956  llvm::Type* InitType = Init->getType();
4957  llvm::Constant *Entry =
4958  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(D, InitType, ForDefinition_t(!IsTentative));
4959 
4960  // Strip off pointer casts if we got them.
4961  Entry = Entry->stripPointerCasts();
4962 
4963  // Entry is now either a Function or GlobalVariable.
4964  auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Entry);
4965 
4966  // We have a definition after a declaration with the wrong type.
4967  // We must make a new GlobalVariable* and update everything that used OldGV
4968  // (a declaration or tentative definition) with the new GlobalVariable*
4969  // (which will be a definition).
4970  //
4971  // This happens if there is a prototype for a global (e.g.
4972  // "extern int x[];") and then a definition of a different type (e.g.
4973  // "int x[10];"). This also happens when an initializer has a different type
4974  // from the type of the global (this happens with unions).
4975  if (!GV || GV->getValueType() != InitType ||
4976  GV->getType()->getAddressSpace() !=
4977  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(D))) {
4978 
4979  // Move the old entry aside so that we'll create a new one.
4980  Entry->setName(StringRef());
4981 
4982  // Make a new global with the correct type, this is now guaranteed to work.
4983  GV = cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
4984  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(D, InitType, ForDefinition_t(!IsTentative))
4985  ->stripPointerCasts());
4986 
4987  // Replace all uses of the old global with the new global
4988  llvm::Constant *NewPtrForOldDecl =
4989  llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(GV,
4990  Entry->getType());
4991  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(NewPtrForOldDecl);
4992 
4993  // Erase the old global, since it is no longer used.
4994  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Entry)->eraseFromParent();
4995  }
4996 
4997  MaybeHandleStaticInExternC(D, GV);
4998 
4999  if (D->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
5000  AddGlobalAnnotations(D, GV);
5001 
5002  // Emit Intel FPGA attribute annotation for a file-scope static variable.
5003  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
5004  addGlobalIntelFPGAAnnotation(D, GV);
5005 
5006  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
5007  const RecordDecl *RD = D->getType()->getAsRecordDecl();
5008  // Add IR attributes if add_ir_attribute_global_variable is attached to
5009  // type.
5010  if (RD && RD->hasAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesGlobalVariableAttr>())
5011  AddGlobalSYCLIRAttributes(GV, RD);
5012  // If VarDecl has a type decorated with SYCL device_global attribute, emit
5013  // IR attribute 'sycl-unique-id'.
5014  if (RD && RD->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>())
5015  addSYCLUniqueID(GV, D, Context);
5016  }
5017 
5018  if (D->getType().isRestrictQualified()) {
5019  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = getLLVMContext();
5020 
5021  // Common metadata nodes.
5022  llvm::NamedMDNode *GlobalsRestrict =
5023  getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("globals.restrict");
5024  llvm::Metadata *Args[] = {llvm::ValueAsMetadata::get(GV)};
5025  llvm::MDNode *Node = llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args);
5026  GlobalsRestrict->addOperand(Node);
5027  }
5028 
5029  // Set the llvm linkage type as appropriate.
5030  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage =
5031  getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(D, GV->isConstant());
5032 
5033  // CUDA B.2.1 "The __device__ qualifier declares a variable that resides on
5034  // the device. [...]"
5035  // CUDA B.2.2 "The __constant__ qualifier, optionally used together with
5036  // __device__, declares a variable that: [...]
5037  // Is accessible from all the threads within the grid and from the host
5038  // through the runtime library (cudaGetSymbolAddress() / cudaGetSymbolSize()
5039  // / cudaMemcpyToSymbol() / cudaMemcpyFromSymbol())."
5040  if (GV && LangOpts.CUDA) {
5041  if (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
5042  if (Linkage != llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage &&
5043  (D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() ||
5044  D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() ||
5045  D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType()))
5046  GV->setExternallyInitialized(true);
5047  } else {
5048  getCUDARuntime().internalizeDeviceSideVar(D, Linkage);
5049  }
5050  getCUDARuntime().handleVarRegistration(D, *GV);
5051  }
5052 
5053  GV->setInitializer(Init);
5054  if (emitter)
5055  emitter->finalize(GV);
5056 
5057  // If it is safe to mark the global 'constant', do so now.
5058  GV->setConstant(!NeedsGlobalCtor && !NeedsGlobalDtor &&
5059  isTypeConstant(D->getType(), true));
5060 
5061  // If it is in a read-only section, mark it 'constant'.
5062  if (const SectionAttr *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>()) {
5063  const ASTContext::SectionInfo &SI = Context.SectionInfos[SA->getName()];
5064  if ((SI.SectionFlags & ASTContext::PSF_Write) == 0)
5065  GV->setConstant(true);
5066  }
5067 
5068  GV->setAlignment(getContext().getDeclAlign(D).getAsAlign());
5069 
5070  // On Darwin, unlike other Itanium C++ ABI platforms, the thread-wrapper
5071  // function is only defined alongside the variable, not also alongside
5072  // callers. Normally, all accesses to a thread_local go through the
5073  // thread-wrapper in order to ensure initialization has occurred, underlying
5074  // variable will never be used other than the thread-wrapper, so it can be
5075  // converted to internal linkage.
5076  //
5077  // However, if the variable has the 'constinit' attribute, it _can_ be
5078  // referenced directly, without calling the thread-wrapper, so the linkage
5079  // must not be changed.
5080  //
5081  // Additionally, if the variable isn't plain external linkage, e.g. if it's
5082  // weak or linkonce, the de-duplication semantics are important to preserve,
5083  // so we don't change the linkage.
5084  if (D->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
5085  Linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage &&
5086  Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin() &&
5087  !D->hasAttr<ConstInitAttr>())
5088  Linkage = llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
5089 
5090  GV->setLinkage(Linkage);
5091  if (D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
5092  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLImportStorageClass);
5093  else if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
5094  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLExportStorageClass);
5095  else
5096  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DefaultStorageClass);
5097 
5098  if (Linkage == llvm::GlobalVariable::CommonLinkage) {
5099  // common vars aren't constant even if declared const.
5100  GV->setConstant(false);
5101  // Tentative definition of global variables may be initialized with
5102  // non-zero null pointers. In this case they should have weak linkage
5103  // since common linkage must have zero initializer and must not have
5104  // explicit section therefore cannot have non-zero initial value.
5105  if (!GV->getInitializer()->isNullValue())
5106  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakAnyLinkage);
5107  }
5108 
5109  setNonAliasAttributes(D, GV);
5110 
5111  if (D->getTLSKind() && !GV->isThreadLocal()) {
5112  if (D->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic)
5113  CXXThreadLocals.push_back(D);
5114  setTLSMode(GV, *D);
5115  }
5116 
5117  maybeSetTrivialComdat(*D, *GV);
5118 
5119  // Emit the initializer function if necessary.
5120  if (NeedsGlobalCtor || NeedsGlobalDtor)
5121  EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInitFunc(D, GV, NeedsGlobalCtor);
5122 
5123  SanitizerMD->reportGlobalToASan(GV, *D, NeedsGlobalCtor);
5124 
5125  // Emit global variable debug information.
5126  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
5127  if (getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
5128  DI->EmitGlobalVariable(GV, D);
5129 
5130  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
5131  maybeEmitPipeStorageMetadata(D, GV, *this);
5132  // Notify SYCL code generation infrastructure that a global variable is
5133  // being generated.
5134  getSYCLRuntime().actOnGlobalVarEmit(*this, *D, GV);
5135  }
5136 }
5137 
5138 void CodeGenModule::EmitExternalVarDeclaration(const VarDecl *D) {
5139  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
5140  if (getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo()) {
5141  QualType ASTTy = D->getType();
5142  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(D->getType());
5143  llvm::Constant *GV =
5144  GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(D->getName(), Ty, ASTTy.getAddressSpace(), D);
5145  DI->EmitExternalVariable(
5146  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV->stripPointerCasts()), D);
5147  }
5148 }
5149 
5150 static bool isVarDeclStrongDefinition(const ASTContext &Context,
5151  CodeGenModule &CGM, const VarDecl *D,
5152  bool NoCommon) {
5153  // Don't give variables common linkage if -fno-common was specified unless it
5154  // was overridden by a NoCommon attribute.
5155  if ((NoCommon || D->hasAttr<NoCommonAttr>()) && !D->hasAttr<CommonAttr>())
5156  return true;
5157 
5158  // C11 6.9.2/2:
5159  // A declaration of an identifier for an object that has file scope without
5160  // an initializer, and without a storage-class specifier or with the
5161  // storage-class specifier static, constitutes a tentative definition.
5162  if (D->getInit() || D->hasExternalStorage())
5163  return true;
5164 
5165  // A variable cannot be both common and exist in a section.
5166  if (D->hasAttr<SectionAttr>())
5167  return true;
5168 
5169  // A variable cannot be both common and exist in a section.
5170  // We don't try to determine which is the right section in the front-end.
5171  // If no specialized section name is applicable, it will resort to default.
5172  if (D->hasAttr<PragmaClangBSSSectionAttr>() ||
5173  D->hasAttr<PragmaClangDataSectionAttr>() ||
5174  D->hasAttr<PragmaClangRelroSectionAttr>() ||
5175  D->hasAttr<PragmaClangRodataSectionAttr>())
5176  return true;
5177 
5178  // Thread local vars aren't considered common linkage.
5179  if (D->getTLSKind())
5180  return true;
5181 
5182  // Tentative definitions marked with WeakImportAttr are true definitions.
5183  if (D->hasAttr<WeakImportAttr>())
5184  return true;
5185 
5186  // A variable cannot be both common and exist in a comdat.
5187  if (shouldBeInCOMDAT(CGM, *D))
5188  return true;
5189 
5190  // Declarations with a required alignment do not have common linkage in MSVC
5191  // mode.
5192  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
5193  if (D->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>())
5194  return true;
5195  QualType VarType = D->getType();
5196  if (Context.isAlignmentRequired(VarType))
5197  return true;
5198 
5199  if (const auto *RT = VarType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5200  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
5201  for (const FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
5202  if (FD->isBitField())
5203  continue;
5204  if (FD->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>())
5205  return true;
5206  if (Context.isAlignmentRequired(FD->getType()))
5207  return true;
5208  }
5209  }
5210  }
5211 
5212  // Microsoft's link.exe doesn't support alignments greater than 32 bytes for
5213  // common symbols, so symbols with greater alignment requirements cannot be
5214  // common.
5215  // Other COFF linkers (ld.bfd and LLD) support arbitrary power-of-two
5216  // alignments for common symbols via the aligncomm directive, so this
5217  // restriction only applies to MSVC environments.
5218  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isKnownWindowsMSVCEnvironment() &&
5219  Context.getTypeAlignIfKnown(D->getType()) >
5220  Context.toBits(CharUnits::fromQuantity(32)))
5221  return true;
5222 
5223  return false;
5224 }
5225 
5226 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes CodeGenModule::getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(
5227  const DeclaratorDecl *D, GVALinkage Linkage, bool IsConstantVariable) {
5228  if (Linkage == GVA_Internal)
5229  return llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
5230 
5231  if (D->hasAttr<WeakAttr>()) {
5232  if (IsConstantVariable)
5233  return llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakODRLinkage;
5234  else
5235  return llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakAnyLinkage;
5236  }
5237 
5238  if (const auto *FD = D->getAsFunction())
5239  if (FD->isMultiVersion() && Linkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
5240  return llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkOnceAnyLinkage;
5241 
5242  // We are guaranteed to have a strong definition somewhere else,
5243  // so we can use available_externally linkage.
5244  if (Linkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
5245  return llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage;
5246 
5247  // Note that Apple's kernel linker doesn't support symbol
5248  // coalescing, so we need to avoid linkonce and weak linkages there.
5249  // Normally, this means we just map to internal, but for explicit
5250  // instantiations we'll map to external.
5251 
5252  // In C++, the compiler has to emit a definition in every translation unit
5253  // that references the function. We should use linkonce_odr because
5254  // a) if all references in this translation unit are optimized away, we
5255  // don't need to codegen it. b) if the function persists, it needs to be
5256  // merged with other definitions. c) C++ has the ODR, so we know the
5257  // definition is dependable.
5258  if (Linkage == GVA_DiscardableODR)
5259  return !Context.getLangOpts().AppleKext ? llvm::Function::LinkOnceODRLinkage
5260  : llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
5261 
5262  // An explicit instantiation of a template has weak linkage, since
5263  // explicit instantiations can occur in multiple translation units
5264  // and must all be equivalent. However, we are not allowed to
5265  // throw away these explicit instantiations.
5266  //
5267  // CUDA/HIP: For -fno-gpu-rdc case, device code is limited to one TU,
5268  // so say that CUDA templates are either external (for kernels) or internal.
5269  // This lets llvm perform aggressive inter-procedural optimizations. For
5270  // -fgpu-rdc case, device function calls across multiple TU's are allowed,
5271  // therefore we need to follow the normal linkage paradigm.
5272  if (Linkage == GVA_StrongODR) {
5273  if (getLangOpts().AppleKext)
5274  return llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage;
5275  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
5276  !getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode)
5277  return D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() ? llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage
5278  : llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
5279  return llvm::Function::WeakODRLinkage;
5280  }
5281 
5282  // C++ doesn't have tentative definitions and thus cannot have common
5283  // linkage.
5284  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
5285  !isVarDeclStrongDefinition(Context, *this, cast<VarDecl>(D),
5286  CodeGenOpts.NoCommon))
5287  return llvm::GlobalVariable::CommonLinkage;
5288 
5289  // selectany symbols are externally visible, so use weak instead of
5290  // linkonce. MSVC optimizes away references to const selectany globals, so
5291  // all definitions should be the same and ODR linkage should be used.
5292  // http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/5tkz6s71.aspx
5293  if (D->hasAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
5294  return llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakODRLinkage;
5295 
5296  // Otherwise, we have strong external linkage.
5297  assert(Linkage == GVA_StrongExternal);
5298  return llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage;
5299 }
5300 
5301 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes CodeGenModule::getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(
5302  const VarDecl *VD, bool IsConstant) {
5303  GVALinkage Linkage = getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD);
5304  return getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(VD, Linkage, IsConstant);
5305 }
5306 
5307 /// Replace the uses of a function that was declared with a non-proto type.
5308 /// We want to silently drop extra arguments from call sites
5309 static void replaceUsesOfNonProtoConstant(llvm::Constant *old,
5310  llvm::Function *newFn) {
5311  // Fast path.
5312  if (old->use_empty()) return;
5313 
5314  llvm::Type *newRetTy = newFn->getReturnType();
5315  SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 4> newArgs;
5316 
5317  for (llvm::Value::use_iterator ui = old->use_begin(), ue = old->use_end();
5318  ui != ue; ) {
5319  llvm::Value::use_iterator use = ui++; // Increment before the use is erased.
5320  llvm::User *user = use->getUser();
5321 
5322  // Recognize and replace uses of bitcasts. Most calls to
5323  // unprototyped functions will use bitcasts.
5324  if (auto *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(user)) {
5325  if (bitcast->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast)
5326  replaceUsesOfNonProtoConstant(bitcast, newFn);
5327  continue;
5328  }
5329 
5330  // Recognize calls to the function.
5331  llvm::CallBase *callSite = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(user);
5332  if (!callSite) continue;
5333  if (!callSite->isCallee(&*use))
5334  continue;
5335 
5336  // If the return types don't match exactly, then we can't
5337  // transform this call unless it's dead.
5338  if (callSite->getType() != newRetTy && !callSite->use_empty())
5339  continue;
5340 
5341  // Get the call site's attribute list.
5342  SmallVector<llvm::AttributeSet, 8> newArgAttrs;
5343  llvm::AttributeList oldAttrs = callSite->getAttributes();
5344 
5345  // If the function was passed too few arguments, don't transform.
5346  unsigned newNumArgs = newFn->arg_size();
5347  if (callSite->arg_size() < newNumArgs)
5348  continue;
5349 
5350  // If extra arguments were passed, we silently drop them.
5351  // If any of the types mismatch, we don't transform.
5352  unsigned argNo = 0;
5353  bool dontTransform = false;
5354  for (llvm::Argument &A : newFn->args()) {
5355  if (callSite->getArgOperand(argNo)->getType() != A.getType()) {
5356  dontTransform = true;
5357  break;
5358  }
5359 
5360  // Add any parameter attributes.
5361  newArgAttrs.push_back(oldAttrs.getParamAttrs(argNo));
5362  argNo++;
5363  }
5364  if (dontTransform)
5365  continue;
5366 
5367  // Okay, we can transform this. Create the new call instruction and copy
5368  // over the required information.
5369  newArgs.append(callSite->arg_begin(), callSite->arg_begin() + argNo);
5370 
5371  // Copy over any operand bundles.
5372  SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> newBundles;
5373  callSite->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(newBundles);
5374 
5375  llvm::CallBase *newCall;
5376  if (isa<llvm::CallInst>(callSite)) {
5377  newCall =
5378  llvm::CallInst::Create(newFn, newArgs, newBundles, "", callSite);
5379  } else {
5380  auto *oldInvoke = cast<llvm::InvokeInst>(callSite);
5381  newCall = llvm::InvokeInst::Create(newFn, oldInvoke->getNormalDest(),
5382  oldInvoke->getUnwindDest(), newArgs,
5383  newBundles, "", callSite);
5384  }
5385  newArgs.clear(); // for the next iteration
5386 
5387  if (!newCall->getType()->isVoidTy())
5388  newCall->takeName(callSite);
5389  newCall->setAttributes(
5390  llvm::AttributeList::get(newFn->getContext(), oldAttrs.getFnAttrs(),
5391  oldAttrs.getRetAttrs(), newArgAttrs));
5392  newCall->setCallingConv(callSite->getCallingConv());
5393 
5394  // Finally, remove the old call, replacing any uses with the new one.
5395  if (!callSite->use_empty())
5396  callSite->replaceAllUsesWith(newCall);
5397 
5398  // Copy debug location attached to CI.
5399  if (callSite->getDebugLoc())
5400  newCall->setDebugLoc(callSite->getDebugLoc());
5401 
5402  callSite->eraseFromParent();
5403  }
5404 }
5405 
5406 /// ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction - This function is called when we
5407 /// implement a function with no prototype, e.g. "int foo() {}". If there are
5408 /// existing call uses of the old function in the module, this adjusts them to
5409 /// call the new function directly.
5410 ///
5411 /// This is not just a cleanup: the always_inline pass requires direct calls to
5412 /// functions to be able to inline them. If there is a bitcast in the way, it
5413 /// won't inline them. Instcombine normally deletes these calls, but it isn't
5414 /// run at -O0.
5415 static void ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction(llvm::GlobalValue *Old,
5416  llvm::Function *NewFn) {
5417  // If we're redefining a global as a function, don't transform it.
5418  if (!isa<llvm::Function>(Old)) return;
5419 
5420  replaceUsesOfNonProtoConstant(Old, NewFn);
5421 }
5422 
5423 void CodeGenModule::HandleCXXStaticMemberVarInstantiation(VarDecl *VD) {
5424  auto DK = VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition();
5425  if (DK == VarDecl::Definition && VD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
5426  return;
5427 
5428  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK = VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
5429  // If we have a definition, this might be a deferred decl. If the
5430  // instantiation is explicit, make sure we emit it at the end.
5431  if (VD->getDefinition() && TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition)
5432  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
5433 
5434  EmitTopLevelDecl(VD);
5435 }
5436 
5437 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GlobalDecl GD,
5438  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
5439  const auto *D = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
5440 
5441  // Compute the function info and LLVM type.
5442  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
5443  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
5444 
5445  // Get or create the prototype for the function.
5446  if (!GV || (GV->getValueType() != Ty))
5447  GV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetAddrOfFunction(GD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false,
5448  /*DontDefer=*/true,
5449  ForDefinition));
5450 
5451  // Already emitted.
5452  if (!GV->isDeclaration())
5453  return;
5454 
5455  // We need to set linkage and visibility on the function before
5456  // generating code for it because various parts of IR generation
5457  // want to propagate this information down (e.g. to local static
5458  // declarations).
5459  auto *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
5460  setFunctionLinkage(GD, Fn);
5461 
5462  // FIXME: this is redundant with part of setFunctionDefinitionAttributes
5463  setGVProperties(Fn, GD);
5464 
5465  MaybeHandleStaticInExternC(D, Fn);
5466 
5467  maybeSetTrivialComdat(*D, *Fn);
5468 
5469  // Set CodeGen attributes that represent floating point environment.
5470  setLLVMFunctionFEnvAttributes(D, Fn);
5471 
5472  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateCode(GD, Fn, FI);
5473 
5474  setNonAliasAttributes(GD, Fn);
5475  SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(D, Fn);
5476 
5477  if (const ConstructorAttr *CA = D->getAttr<ConstructorAttr>())
5478  AddGlobalCtor(Fn, CA->getPriority());
5479  if (const DestructorAttr *DA = D->getAttr<DestructorAttr>())
5480  AddGlobalDtor(Fn, DA->getPriority(), true);
5481  if (D->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
5482  AddGlobalAnnotations(D, Fn);
5483 }
5484 
5485 void CodeGenModule::EmitAliasDefinition(GlobalDecl GD) {
5486  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
5487  const AliasAttr *AA = D->getAttr<AliasAttr>();
5488  assert(AA && "Not an alias?");
5489 
5490  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
5491 
5492  if (AA->getAliasee() == MangledName) {
5493  Diags.Report(AA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 0;
5494  return;
5495  }
5496 
5497  // If there is a definition in the module, then it wins over the alias.
5498  // This is dubious, but allow it to be safe. Just ignore the alias.
5499  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
5500  if (Entry && !Entry->isDeclaration())
5501  return;
5502 
5503  Aliases.push_back(GD);
5504 
5505  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(D->getType());
5506 
5507  // Create a reference to the named value. This ensures that it is emitted
5508  // if a deferred decl.
5509  llvm::Constant *Aliasee;
5510  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT;
5511  unsigned AS;
5512  if (isa<llvm::FunctionType>(DeclTy)) {
5513  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy, GD,
5514  /*ForVTable=*/false);
5515  LT = getFunctionLinkage(GD);
5516  AS = Aliasee->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
5517  } else {
5518  LangAS LAS = GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(dyn_cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl()));
5519  AS = ArgInfoAddressSpace(LAS);
5520  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy, LAS,
5521  /*D=*/nullptr);
5522  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl()))
5523  LT = getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, D->getType().isConstQualified());
5524  else
5525  LT = getFunctionLinkage(GD);
5526  }
5527 
5528  // Create the new alias itself, but don't set a name yet.
5529  auto *GA =
5530  llvm::GlobalAlias::create(DeclTy, AS, LT, "", Aliasee, &getModule());
5531 
5532  if (Entry) {
5533  if (GA->getAliasee() == Entry) {
5534  Diags.Report(AA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 0;
5535  return;
5536  }
5537 
5538  assert(Entry->isDeclaration());
5539 
5540  // If there is a declaration in the module, then we had an extern followed
5541  // by the alias, as in:
5542  // extern int test6();
5543  // ...
5544  // int test6() __attribute__((alias("test7")));
5545  //
5546  // Remove it and replace uses of it with the alias.
5547  GA->takeName(Entry);
5548 
5549  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(
5550  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GA, Entry->getType()));
5551  Entry->eraseFromParent();
5552  } else {
5553  GA->setName(MangledName);
5554  }
5555 
5556  // Set attributes which are particular to an alias; this is a
5557  // specialization of the attributes which may be set on a global
5558  // variable/function.
5559  if (D->hasAttr<WeakAttr>() || D->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>() ||
5560  D->isWeakImported()) {
5561  GA->setLinkage(llvm::Function::WeakAnyLinkage);
5562  }
5563 
5564  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
5565  if (VD->getTLSKind())
5566  setTLSMode(GA, *VD);
5567 
5568  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GA);
5569 }
5570 
5571 void CodeGenModule::emitIFuncDefinition(GlobalDecl GD) {
5572  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
5573  const IFuncAttr *IFA = D->getAttr<IFuncAttr>();
5574  assert(IFA && "Not an ifunc?");
5575 
5576  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
5577 
5578  if (IFA->getResolver() == MangledName) {
5579  Diags.Report(IFA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 1;
5580  return;
5581  }
5582 
5583  // Report an error if some definition overrides ifunc.
5584  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
5585  if (Entry && !Entry->isDeclaration()) {
5586  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
5587  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(MangledName, OtherGD) &&
5588  DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions.insert(GD).second) {
5589  Diags.Report(D->getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_mangled_name)
5590  << MangledName;
5591  Diags.Report(OtherGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
5592  diag::note_previous_definition);
5593  }
5594  return;
5595  }
5596 
5597  Aliases.push_back(GD);
5598 
5599  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(D->getType());
5600  llvm::Type *ResolverTy = llvm::GlobalIFunc::getResolverFunctionType(DeclTy);
5601  llvm::Constant *Resolver =
5602  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(IFA->getResolver(), ResolverTy, {},
5603  /*ForVTable=*/false);
5604  llvm::GlobalIFunc *GIF =
5605  llvm::GlobalIFunc::create(DeclTy, 0, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
5606  "", Resolver, &getModule());
5607  if (Entry) {
5608  if (GIF->getResolver() == Entry) {
5609  Diags.Report(IFA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 1;
5610  return;
5611  }
5612  assert(Entry->isDeclaration());
5613 
5614  // If there is a declaration in the module, then we had an extern followed
5615  // by the ifunc, as in:
5616  // extern int test();
5617  // ...
5618  // int test() __attribute__((ifunc("resolver")));
5619  //
5620  // Remove it and replace uses of it with the ifunc.
5621  GIF->takeName(Entry);
5622 
5623  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GIF,
5624  Entry->getType()));
5625  Entry->eraseFromParent();
5626  } else
5627  GIF->setName(MangledName);
5628 
5629  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GIF);
5630 }
5631 
5632 llvm::Function *CodeGenModule::getIntrinsic(unsigned IID,
5633  ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> Tys) {
5634  return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(&getModule(), (llvm::Intrinsic::ID)IID,
5635  Tys);
5636 }
5637 
5638 static llvm::StringMapEntry<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &
5639 GetConstantCFStringEntry(llvm::StringMap<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &Map,
5640  const StringLiteral *Literal, bool TargetIsLSB,
5641  bool &IsUTF16, unsigned &StringLength) {
5642  StringRef String = Literal->getString();
5643  unsigned NumBytes = String.size();
5644 
5645  // Check for simple case.
5646  if (!Literal->containsNonAsciiOrNull()) {
5647  StringLength = NumBytes;
5648  return *Map.insert(std::make_pair(String, nullptr)).first;
5649  }
5650 
5651  // Otherwise, convert the UTF8 literals into a string of shorts.
5652  IsUTF16 = true;
5653 
5654  SmallVector<llvm::UTF16, 128> ToBuf(NumBytes + 1); // +1 for ending nulls.
5655  const llvm::UTF8 *FromPtr = (const llvm::UTF8 *)String.data();
5656  llvm::UTF16 *ToPtr = &ToBuf[0];
5657 
5658  (void)llvm::ConvertUTF8toUTF16(&FromPtr, FromPtr + NumBytes, &ToPtr,
5659  ToPtr + NumBytes, llvm::strictConversion);
5660 
5661  // ConvertUTF8toUTF16 returns the length in ToPtr.
5662  StringLength = ToPtr - &ToBuf[0];
5663 
5664  // Add an explicit null.
5665  *ToPtr = 0;
5666  return *Map.insert(std::make_pair(
5667  StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(ToBuf.data()),
5668  (StringLength + 1) * 2),
5669  nullptr)).first;
5670 }
5671 
5672 ConstantAddress
5673 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantCFString(const StringLiteral *Literal) {
5674  unsigned StringLength = 0;
5675  bool isUTF16 = false;
5676  llvm::StringMapEntry<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &Entry =
5677  GetConstantCFStringEntry(CFConstantStringMap, Literal,
5678  getDataLayout().isLittleEndian(), isUTF16,
5679  StringLength);
5680 
5681  if (auto *C = Entry.second)
5682  return ConstantAddress(
5683  C, C->getValueType(), CharUnits::fromQuantity(C->getAlignment()));
5684 
5685  llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int32Ty);
5686  llvm::Constant *Zeros[] = { Zero, Zero };
5687 
5688  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
5689  const llvm::Triple &Triple = getTriple();
5690 
5691  const auto CFRuntime = getLangOpts().CFRuntime;
5692  const bool IsSwiftABI =
5693  static_cast<unsigned>(CFRuntime) >=
5694  static_cast<unsigned>(LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift);
5695  const bool IsSwift4_1 = CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1;
5696 
5697  // If we don't already have it, get __CFConstantStringClassReference.
5698  if (!CFConstantStringClassRef) {
5699  const char *CFConstantStringClassName = "__CFConstantStringClassReference";
5700  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().ConvertType(getContext().IntTy);
5701  Ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(Ty, 0);
5702 
5703  switch (CFRuntime) {
5704  default: break;
5705  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift: LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5706  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift5_0:
5707  CFConstantStringClassName =
5708  Triple.isOSDarwin() ? "$s15SwiftFoundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN"
5709  : "$s10Foundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN";
5710  Ty = IntPtrTy;
5711  break;
5712  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_2:
5713  CFConstantStringClassName =
5714  Triple.isOSDarwin() ? "$S15SwiftFoundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN"
5715  : "$S10Foundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN";
5716  Ty = IntPtrTy;
5717  break;
5718  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1:
5719  CFConstantStringClassName =
5720  Triple.isOSDarwin() ? "__T015SwiftFoundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN"
5721  : "__T010Foundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN";
5722  Ty = IntPtrTy;
5723  break;
5724  }
5725 
5726  llvm::Constant *C = CreateRuntimeVariable(Ty, CFConstantStringClassName);
5727 
5728  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF() || Triple.isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
5729  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
5730 
5731  if ((GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(C))) {
5732  IdentifierInfo &II = Context.Idents.get(GV->getName());
5733  TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
5734  DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
5735 
5736  const VarDecl *VD = nullptr;
5737  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&II))
5738  if ((VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Result)))
5739  break;
5740 
5741  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
5742  if (!VD)
5743  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
5744  } else {
5745  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
5746  if (!VD || !VD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
5747  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
5748  else
5749  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
5750  }
5751 
5752  setDSOLocal(GV);
5753  }
5754  }
5755 
5756  // Decay array -> ptr
5757  CFConstantStringClassRef =
5758  IsSwiftABI ? llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(C, Ty)
5759  : llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(Ty, C, Zeros);
5760  }
5761 
5762  QualType CFTy = Context.getCFConstantStringType();
5763 
5764  auto *STy = cast<llvm::StructType>(getTypes().ConvertType(CFTy));
5765 
5766  ConstantInitBuilder Builder(*this);
5767  auto Fields = Builder.beginStruct(STy);
5768 
5769  // Class pointer.
5770  Fields.add(cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(CFConstantStringClassRef));
5771 
5772  // Flags.
5773  if (IsSwiftABI) {
5774  Fields.addInt(IntPtrTy, IsSwift4_1 ? 0x05 : 0x01);
5775  Fields.addInt(Int64Ty, isUTF16 ? 0x07d0 : 0x07c8);
5776  } else {
5777  Fields.addInt(IntTy, isUTF16 ? 0x07d0 : 0x07C8);
5778  }
5779 
5780  // String pointer.
5781  llvm::Constant *C = nullptr;
5782  if (isUTF16) {
5783  auto Arr = llvm::makeArrayRef(
5784  reinterpret_cast<uint16_t *>(const_cast<char *>(Entry.first().data())),
5785  Entry.first().size() / 2);
5786  C = llvm::ConstantDataArray::get(VMContext, Arr);
5787  } else {
5788  C = llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext, Entry.first());
5789  }
5790 
5791  // Note: -fwritable-strings doesn't make the backing store strings of
5792  // CFStrings writable. (See <rdar://problem/10657500>)
5793  auto *GV =
5794  new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), C->getType(), /*isConstant=*/true,
5795  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, C, ".str");
5796  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
5797  // Don't enforce the target's minimum global alignment, since the only use
5798  // of the string is via this class initializer.
5799  CharUnits Align = isUTF16 ? Context.getTypeAlignInChars(Context.ShortTy)
5800  : Context.getTypeAlignInChars(Context.CharTy);
5801  GV->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
5802 
5803  // FIXME: We set the section explicitly to avoid a bug in ld64 224.1.
5804  // Without it LLVM can merge the string with a non unnamed_addr one during
5805  // LTO. Doing that changes the section it ends in, which surprises ld64.
5806  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatMachO())
5807  GV->setSection(isUTF16 ? "__TEXT,__ustring"
5808  : "__TEXT,__cstring,cstring_literals");
5809  // Make sure the literal ends up in .rodata to allow for safe ICF and for
5810  // the static linker to adjust permissions to read-only later on.
5811  else if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF())
5812  GV->setSection(".rodata");
5813 
5814  // String.
5815  llvm::Constant *Str =
5816  llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(GV->getValueType(), GV, Zeros);
5817 
5818  if (isUTF16)
5819  // Cast the UTF16 string to the correct type.
5820  Str = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Str, Int8PtrTy);
5821  Fields.add(Str);
5822 
5823  // String length.
5824  llvm::IntegerType *LengthTy =
5825  llvm::IntegerType::get(getModule().getContext(),
5826  Context.getTargetInfo().getLongWidth());
5827  if (IsSwiftABI) {
5828  if (CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1 ||
5829  CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_2)
5830  LengthTy = Int32Ty;
5831  else
5832  LengthTy = IntPtrTy;
5833  }
5834  Fields.addInt(LengthTy, StringLength);
5835 
5836  // Swift ABI requires 8-byte alignment to ensure that the _Atomic(uint64_t) is
5837  // properly aligned on 32-bit platforms.
5838  CharUnits Alignment =
5839  IsSwiftABI ? Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(64) : getPointerAlign();
5840 
5841  // The struct.
5842  GV = Fields.finishAndCreateGlobal("_unnamed_cfstring_", Alignment,
5843  /*isConstant=*/false,
5844  llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage);
5845  GV->addAttribute("objc_arc_inert");
5846  switch (Triple.getObjectFormat()) {
5847  case llvm::Triple::UnknownObjectFormat:
5848  llvm_unreachable("unknown file format");
5849  case llvm::Triple::GOFF:
5850  llvm_unreachable("GOFF is not yet implemented");
5851  case llvm::Triple::XCOFF:
5852  llvm_unreachable("XCOFF is not yet implemented");
5853  case llvm::Triple::COFF:
5854  case llvm::Triple::ELF:
5855  case llvm::Triple::Wasm:
5856  GV->setSection("cfstring");
5857  break;
5858  case llvm::Triple::MachO:
5859  GV->setSection("__DATA,__cfstring");
5860  break;
5861  }
5862  Entry.second = GV;
5863 
5864  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
5865 }
5866 
5867 bool CodeGenModule::getExpressionLocationsEnabled() const {
5868  return !CodeGenOpts.EmitCodeView || CodeGenOpts.DebugColumnInfo;
5869 }
5870 
5871 QualType CodeGenModule::getObjCFastEnumerationStateType() {
5872  if (ObjCFastEnumerationStateType.isNull()) {
5873  RecordDecl *D = Context.buildImplicitRecord("__objcFastEnumerationState");
5874  D->startDefinition();
5875 
5876  QualType FieldTypes[] = {
5877  Context.UnsignedLongTy,
5878  Context.getPointerType(Context.getObjCIdType()),
5879  Context.getPointerType(Context.UnsignedLongTy),
5880  Context.getConstantArrayType(Context.UnsignedLongTy,
5881  llvm::APInt(32, 5), nullptr, ArrayType::Normal, 0)
5882  };
5883 
5884  for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
5885  FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(Context,
5886  D,
5887  SourceLocation(),
5888  SourceLocation(), nullptr,
5889  FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
5890  /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
5891  /*Mutable=*/false,
5892  ICIS_NoInit);
5893  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
5894  D->addDecl(Field);
5895  }
5896 
5897  D->completeDefinition();
5898  ObjCFastEnumerationStateType = Context.getTagDeclType(D);
5899  }
5900 
5901  return ObjCFastEnumerationStateType;
5902 }
5903 
5904 llvm::Constant *
5905 CodeGenModule::GetConstantArrayFromStringLiteral(const StringLiteral *E) {
5906  assert(!E->getType()->isPointerType() && "Strings are always arrays");
5907 
5908  // Don't emit it as the address of the string, emit the string data itself
5909  // as an inline array.
5910  if (E->getCharByteWidth() == 1) {
5911  SmallString<64> Str(E->getString());
5912 
5913  // Resize the string to the right size, which is indicated by its type.
5914  const ConstantArrayType *CAT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(E->getType());
5915  Str.resize(CAT->getSize().getZExtValue());
5916  return llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext, Str, false);
5917  }
5918 
5919  auto *AType = cast<llvm::ArrayType>(getTypes().ConvertType(E->getType()));
5920  llvm::Type *ElemTy = AType->getElementType();
5921  unsigned NumElements = AType->getNumElements();
5922 
5923  // Wide strings have either 2-byte or 4-byte elements.
5924  if (ElemTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 16) {
5925  SmallVector<uint16_t, 32> Elements;
5926  Elements.reserve(NumElements);
5927 
5928  for(unsigned i = 0, e = E->getLength(); i != e; ++i)
5929  Elements.push_back(E->getCodeUnit(i));
5930  Elements.resize(NumElements);
5931  return llvm::ConstantDataArray::get(VMContext, Elements);
5932  }
5933 
5934  assert(ElemTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 32);
5935  SmallVector<uint32_t, 32> Elements;
5936  Elements.reserve(NumElements);
5937 
5938  for(unsigned i = 0, e = E->getLength(); i != e; ++i)
5939  Elements.push_back(E->getCodeUnit(i));
5940  Elements.resize(NumElements);
5941  return llvm::ConstantDataArray::get(VMContext, Elements);
5942 }
5943 
5944 static llvm::GlobalVariable *
5945 GenerateStringLiteral(llvm::Constant *C, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT,
5946  CodeGenModule &CGM, StringRef GlobalName,
5947  CharUnits Alignment) {
5948  unsigned AddrSpace = CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(
5949  CGM.GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace());
5950 
5951  llvm::Module &M = CGM.getModule();
5952  // Create a global variable for this string
5953  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
5954  M, C->getType(), !CGM.getLangOpts().WritableStrings, LT, C, GlobalName,
5955  nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AddrSpace);
5956  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
5957  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
5958  if (GV->isWeakForLinker()) {
5959  assert(CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && "Only COFF uses weak string literals");
5960  GV->setComdat(M.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
5961  }
5962  CGM.setDSOLocal(GV);
5963 
5964  return GV;
5965 }

5967 /// GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral - Return a pointer to a
5968 /// constant array for the given string literal.
5969 ConstantAddress
5970 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral(const StringLiteral *S,
5971  StringRef Name) {
5972  CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getAlignOfGlobalVarInChars(S->getType());
5973 
5974  llvm::Constant *C = GetConstantArrayFromStringLiteral(S);
5975  llvm::GlobalVariable **Entry = nullptr;
5976  if (!LangOpts.WritableStrings) {
5977  Entry = &ConstantStringMap[C];
5978  if (auto GV = *Entry) {
5979  if (uint64_t(Alignment.getQuantity()) > GV->getAlignment())
5980  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
5981  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
5982  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
5983  }
5984  }
5985 
5986  SmallString<256> MangledNameBuffer;
5987  StringRef GlobalVariableName;
5988  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT;
5989 
5990  // Mangle the string literal if that's how the ABI merges duplicate strings.
5991  // Don't do it if they are writable, since we don't want writes in one TU to
5992  // affect strings in another.
5993  if (getCXXABI().getMangleContext().shouldMangleStringLiteral(S) &&
5994  !LangOpts.WritableStrings) {
5995  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledNameBuffer);
5996  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleStringLiteral(S, Out);
5997  LT = llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
5998  GlobalVariableName = MangledNameBuffer;
5999  } else {
6000  LT = llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage;
6001  GlobalVariableName = Name;
6002  }
6003 
6004  auto GV = GenerateStringLiteral(C, LT, *this, GlobalVariableName, Alignment);
6005  if (Entry)
6006  *Entry = GV;
6007 
6008  SanitizerMD->reportGlobalToASan(GV, S->getStrTokenLoc(0), "<string literal>",
6009  QualType());
6010 
6011  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
6012  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
6013 }

6015 /// GetAddrOfConstantStringFromObjCEncode - Return a pointer to a constant
6016 /// array for the given ObjCEncodeExpr node.
6017 ConstantAddress
6018 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantStringFromObjCEncode(const ObjCEncodeExpr *E) {
6019  std::string Str;
6020  getContext().getObjCEncodingForType(E->getEncodedType(), Str);
6021 
6022  return GetAddrOfConstantCString(Str);
6023 }
