6025 /// GetAddrOfConstantCString - Returns a pointer to a character array containing
6026 /// the literal and a terminating '\0' character.
6027 /// The result has pointer to array type.
6028 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantCString(
6029  const std::string &Str, const char *GlobalName) {
6030  StringRef StrWithNull(Str.c_str(), Str.size() + 1);
6031  CharUnits Alignment =
6032  getContext().getAlignOfGlobalVarInChars(getContext().CharTy);
6033 
6034  llvm::Constant *C =
6035  llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), StrWithNull, false);
6036 
6037  // Don't share any string literals if strings aren't constant.
6038  llvm::GlobalVariable **Entry = nullptr;
6039  if (!LangOpts.WritableStrings) {
6040  Entry = &ConstantStringMap[C];
6041  if (auto GV = *Entry) {
6042  if (uint64_t(Alignment.getQuantity()) > GV->getAlignment())
6043  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
6044  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
6045  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
6046  }
6047  }
6048 
6049  // Get the default prefix if a name wasn't specified.
6050  if (!GlobalName)
6051  GlobalName = ".str";
6052  // Create a global variable for this.
6053  auto GV = GenerateStringLiteral(C, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, *this,
6054  GlobalName, Alignment);
6055  if (Entry)
6056  *Entry = GV;
6057 
6058  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
6059  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
6060 }
6061 
6062 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobalTemporary(
6063  const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *E, const Expr *Init) {
6064  assert((E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static ||
6065  E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Thread) && "not a global temporary");
6066  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(E->getExtendingDecl());
6067 
6068  // If we're not materializing a subobject of the temporary, keep the
6069  // cv-qualifiers from the type of the MaterializeTemporaryExpr.
6070  QualType MaterializedType = Init->getType();
6071  if (Init == E->getSubExpr())
6072  MaterializedType = E->getType();
6073 
6074  CharUnits Align = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(MaterializedType);
6075 
6076  auto InsertResult = MaterializedGlobalTemporaryMap.insert({E, nullptr});
6077  if (!InsertResult.second) {
6078  // We've seen this before: either we already created it or we're in the
6079  // process of doing so.
6080  if (!InsertResult.first->second) {
6081  // We recursively re-entered this function, probably during emission of
6082  // the initializer. Create a placeholder. We'll clean this up in the
6083  // outer call, at the end of this function.
6084  llvm::Type *Type = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(MaterializedType);
6085  InsertResult.first->second = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
6086  getModule(), Type, false, llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage,
6087  nullptr);
6088  }
6089  return ConstantAddress(InsertResult.first->second,
6090  llvm::cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
6091  InsertResult.first->second->stripPointerCasts())
6092  ->getValueType(),
6093  Align);
6094  }
6095 
6096  // FIXME: If an externally-visible declaration extends multiple temporaries,
6097  // we need to give each temporary the same name in every translation unit (and
6098  // we also need to make the temporaries externally-visible).
6099  SmallString<256> Name;
6100  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
6101  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleReferenceTemporary(
6102  VD, E->getManglingNumber(), Out);
6103 
6104  APValue *Value = nullptr;
6105  if (E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static && VD && VD->evaluateValue()) {
6106  // If the initializer of the extending declaration is a constant
6107  // initializer, we should have a cached constant initializer for this
6108  // temporary. Note that this might have a different value from the value
6109  // computed by evaluating the initializer if the surrounding constant
6110  // expression modifies the temporary.
6111  Value = E->getOrCreateValue(false);
6112  }
6113 
6114  // Try evaluating it now, it might have a constant initializer.
6115  Expr::EvalResult EvalResult;
6116  if (!Value && Init->EvaluateAsRValue(EvalResult, getContext()) &&
6117  !EvalResult.hasSideEffects())
6118  Value = &EvalResult.Val;
6119 
6120  LangAS AddrSpace =
6121  VD ? GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(VD) : MaterializedType.getAddressSpace();
6122 
6123  Optional<ConstantEmitter> emitter;
6124  llvm::Constant *InitialValue = nullptr;
6125  bool Constant = false;
6126  llvm::Type *Type;
6127  if (Value) {
6128  // The temporary has a constant initializer, use it.
6129  emitter.emplace(*this);
6130  InitialValue = emitter->emitForInitializer(*Value, AddrSpace,
6131  MaterializedType);
6132  Constant = isTypeConstant(MaterializedType, /*ExcludeCtor*/Value);
6133  Type = InitialValue->getType();
6134  } else {
6135  // No initializer, the initialization will be provided when we
6136  // initialize the declaration which performed lifetime extension.
6137  Type = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(MaterializedType);
6138  }
6139 
6140  // Create a global variable for this lifetime-extended temporary.
6141  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage =
6142  getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, Constant);
6143  if (Linkage == llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage) {
6144  const VarDecl *InitVD;
6145  if (VD->isStaticDataMember() && VD->getAnyInitializer(InitVD) &&
6146  isa<CXXRecordDecl>(InitVD->getLexicalDeclContext())) {
6147  // Temporaries defined inside a class get linkonce_odr linkage because the
6148  // class can be defined in multiple translation units.
6149  Linkage = llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
6150  } else {
6151  // There is no need for this temporary to have external linkage if the
6152  // VarDecl has external linkage.
6153  Linkage = llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage;
6154  }
6155  }
6156  auto TargetAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AddrSpace);
6157  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
6158  getModule(), Type, Constant, Linkage, InitialValue, Name.c_str(),
6159  /*InsertBefore=*/nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, TargetAS);
6160  if (emitter) emitter->finalize(GV);
6161  setGVProperties(GV, VD);
6162  if (GV->getDLLStorageClass() == llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLExportStorageClass)
6163  // The reference temporary should never be dllexport.
6164  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DefaultStorageClass);
6165  GV->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
6166  if (supportsCOMDAT() && GV->isWeakForLinker())
6167  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
6168  if (VD->getTLSKind())
6169  setTLSMode(GV, *VD);
6170  llvm::Constant *CV = GV;
6171  if (AddrSpace != LangAS::Default)
6172  CV = getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
6173  *this, GV, AddrSpace, LangAS::Default,
6174  Type->getPointerTo(
6175  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
6176 
6177  // Update the map with the new temporary. If we created a placeholder above,
6178  // replace it with the new global now.
6179  llvm::Constant *&Entry = MaterializedGlobalTemporaryMap[E];
6180  if (Entry) {
6181  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(
6182  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(CV, Entry->getType()));
6183  llvm::cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Entry)->eraseFromParent();
6184  }
6185  Entry = CV;
6186 
6187  return ConstantAddress(CV, Type, Align);
6188 }
6189 
6190 /// EmitObjCPropertyImplementations - Emit information for synthesized
6191 /// properties for an implementation.
6192 void CodeGenModule::EmitObjCPropertyImplementations(const
6193  ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
6194  for (const auto *PID : D->property_impls()) {
6195  // Dynamic is just for type-checking.
6196  if (PID->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize) {
6197  ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PID->getPropertyDecl();
6198 
6199  // Determine which methods need to be implemented, some may have
6200  // been overridden. Note that ::isPropertyAccessor is not the method
6201  // we want, that just indicates if the decl came from a
6202  // property. What we want to know is if the method is defined in
6203  // this implementation.
6204  auto *Getter = PID->getGetterMethodDecl();
6205  if (!Getter || Getter->isSynthesizedAccessorStub())
6206  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCGetter(
6207  const_cast<ObjCImplementationDecl *>(D), PID);
6208  auto *Setter = PID->getSetterMethodDecl();
6209  if (!PD->isReadOnly() && (!Setter || Setter->isSynthesizedAccessorStub()))
6210  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCSetter(
6211  const_cast<ObjCImplementationDecl *>(D), PID);
6212  }
6213  }
6214 }
6215 
6216 static bool needsDestructMethod(ObjCImplementationDecl *impl) {
6217  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *iface = impl->getClassInterface();
6218  for (const ObjCIvarDecl *ivar = iface->all_declared_ivar_begin();
6219  ivar; ivar = ivar->getNextIvar())
6220  if (ivar->getType().isDestructedType())
6221  return true;
6222 
6223  return false;
6224 }
6225 
6226 static bool AllTrivialInitializers(CodeGenModule &CGM,
6227  ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
6228  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
6229  for (ObjCImplementationDecl::init_iterator B = D->init_begin(),
6230  E = D->init_end(); B != E; ++B) {
6231  CXXCtorInitializer *CtorInitExp = *B;
6232  Expr *Init = CtorInitExp->getInit();
6233  if (!CGF.isTrivialInitializer(Init))
6234  return false;
6235  }
6236  return true;
6237 }
6238 
6239 /// EmitObjCIvarInitializations - Emit information for ivar initialization
6240 /// for an implementation.
6241 void CodeGenModule::EmitObjCIvarInitializations(ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
6242  // We might need a .cxx_destruct even if we don't have any ivar initializers.
6243  if (needsDestructMethod(D)) {
6244  IdentifierInfo *II = &getContext().Idents.get(".cxx_destruct");
6245  Selector cxxSelector = getContext().Selectors.getSelector(0, &II);
6246  ObjCMethodDecl *DTORMethod = ObjCMethodDecl::Create(
6247  getContext(), D->getLocation(), D->getLocation(), cxxSelector,
6248  getContext().VoidTy, nullptr, D,
6249  /*isInstance=*/true, /*isVariadic=*/false,
6250  /*isPropertyAccessor=*/true, /*isSynthesizedAccessorStub=*/false,
6251  /*isImplicitlyDeclared=*/true,
6252  /*isDefined=*/false, ObjCMethodDecl::Required);
6253  D->addInstanceMethod(DTORMethod);
6254  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCCtorDtorMethod(D, DTORMethod, false);
6255  D->setHasDestructors(true);
6256  }
6257 
6258  // If the implementation doesn't have any ivar initializers, we don't need
6259  // a .cxx_construct.
6260  if (D->getNumIvarInitializers() == 0 ||
6261  AllTrivialInitializers(*this, D))
6262  return;
6263 
6264  IdentifierInfo *II = &getContext().Idents.get(".cxx_construct");
6265  Selector cxxSelector = getContext().Selectors.getSelector(0, &II);
6266  // The constructor returns 'self'.
6267  ObjCMethodDecl *CTORMethod = ObjCMethodDecl::Create(
6268  getContext(), D->getLocation(), D->getLocation(), cxxSelector,
6269  getContext().getObjCIdType(), nullptr, D, /*isInstance=*/true,
6270  /*isVariadic=*/false,
6271  /*isPropertyAccessor=*/true, /*isSynthesizedAccessorStub=*/false,
6272  /*isImplicitlyDeclared=*/true,
6273  /*isDefined=*/false, ObjCMethodDecl::Required);
6274  D->addInstanceMethod(CTORMethod);
6275  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCCtorDtorMethod(D, CTORMethod, true);
6276  D->setHasNonZeroConstructors(true);
6277 }
6278 
6279 // EmitLinkageSpec - Emit all declarations in a linkage spec.
6280 void CodeGenModule::EmitLinkageSpec(const LinkageSpecDecl *LSD) {
6281  if (LSD->getLanguage() != LinkageSpecDecl::lang_c &&
6282  LSD->getLanguage() != LinkageSpecDecl::lang_cxx) {
6283  ErrorUnsupported(LSD, "linkage spec");
6284  return;
6285  }
6286 
6287  EmitDeclContext(LSD);
6288 }
6289 
6290 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeclContext(const DeclContext *DC) {
6291  for (auto *I : DC->decls()) {
6292  // Unlike other DeclContexts, the contents of an ObjCImplDecl at TU scope
6293  // are themselves considered "top-level", so EmitTopLevelDecl on an
6294  // ObjCImplDecl does not recursively visit them. We need to do that in
6295  // case they're nested inside another construct (LinkageSpecDecl /
6296  // ExportDecl) that does stop them from being considered "top-level".
6297  if (auto *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(I)) {
6298  for (auto *M : OID->methods())
6299  EmitTopLevelDecl(M);
6300  }
6301 
6302  EmitTopLevelDecl(I);
6303  }
6304 }
6305 
6306 /// EmitTopLevelDecl - Emit code for a single top level declaration.
6307 void CodeGenModule::EmitTopLevelDecl(Decl *D) {
6308  // Ignore dependent declarations.
6309  if (D->isTemplated())
6310  return;
6311 
6312  // Consteval function shouldn't be emitted.
6313  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
6314  if (FD->isConsteval())
6315  return;
6316 
6317  switch (D->getKind()) {
6318  case Decl::CXXConversion:
6319  case Decl::CXXMethod:
6320  case Decl::Function:
6321  EmitGlobal(cast<FunctionDecl>(D));
6322  // Always provide some coverage mapping
6323  // even for the functions that aren't emitted.
6324  AddDeferredUnusedCoverageMapping(D);
6325  break;
6326 
6327  case Decl::CXXDeductionGuide:
6328  // Function-like, but does not result in code emission.
6329  break;
6330 
6331  case Decl::Var:
6332  case Decl::Decomposition:
6333  case Decl::VarTemplateSpecialization:
6334  EmitGlobal(cast<VarDecl>(D));
6335  if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<DecompositionDecl>(D))
6336  for (auto *B : DD->bindings())
6337  if (auto *HD = B->getHoldingVar())
6338  EmitGlobal(HD);
6339  break;
6340 
6341  // Indirect fields from global anonymous structs and unions can be
6342  // ignored; only the actual variable requires IR gen support.
6343  case Decl::IndirectField:
6344  break;
6345 
6346  // C++ Decls
6347  case Decl::Namespace:
6348  EmitDeclContext(cast<NamespaceDecl>(D));
6349  break;
6350  case Decl::ClassTemplateSpecialization: {
6351  const auto *Spec = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D);
6352  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6353  if (Spec->getSpecializationKind() ==
6354  TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition &&
6355  Spec->hasDefinition())
6356  DI->completeTemplateDefinition(*Spec);
6357  } LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
6358  case Decl::CXXRecord: {
6359  CXXRecordDecl *CRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
6360  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo()) {
6361  if (CRD->hasDefinition())
6362  DI->EmitAndRetainType(getContext().getRecordType(cast<RecordDecl>(D)));
6363  if (auto *ES = D->getASTContext().getExternalSource())
6364  if (ES->hasExternalDefinitions(D) == ExternalASTSource::EK_Never)
6365  DI->completeUnusedClass(*CRD);
6366  }
6367  // Emit any static data members, they may be definitions.
6368  for (auto *I : CRD->decls())
6369  if (isa<VarDecl>(I) || isa<CXXRecordDecl>(I))
6370  EmitTopLevelDecl(I);
6371  break;
6372  }
6373  // No code generation needed.
6374  case Decl::UsingShadow:
6375  case Decl::ClassTemplate:
6376  case Decl::VarTemplate:
6377  case Decl::Concept:
6378  case Decl::VarTemplatePartialSpecialization:
6379  case Decl::FunctionTemplate:
6380  case Decl::TypeAliasTemplate:
6381  case Decl::Block:
6382  case Decl::Empty:
6383  case Decl::Binding:
6384  break;
6385  case Decl::Using: // using X; [C++]
6386  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6387  DI->EmitUsingDecl(cast<UsingDecl>(*D));
6388  break;
6389  case Decl::UsingEnum: // using enum X; [C++]
6390  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6391  DI->EmitUsingEnumDecl(cast<UsingEnumDecl>(*D));
6392  break;
6393  case Decl::NamespaceAlias:
6394  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6395  DI->EmitNamespaceAlias(cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(*D));
6396  break;
6397  case Decl::UsingDirective: // using namespace X; [C++]
6398  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6399  DI->EmitUsingDirective(cast<UsingDirectiveDecl>(*D));
6400  break;
6401  case Decl::CXXConstructor:
6402  getCXXABI().EmitCXXConstructors(cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D));
6403  break;
6404  case Decl::CXXDestructor:
6405  getCXXABI().EmitCXXDestructors(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D));
6406  break;
6407 
6408  case Decl::StaticAssert:
6409  // Nothing to do.
6410  break;
6411 
6412  // Objective-C Decls
6413 
6414  // Forward declarations, no (immediate) code generation.
6415  case Decl::ObjCInterface:
6416  case Decl::ObjCCategory:
6417  break;
6418 
6419  case Decl::ObjCProtocol: {
6420  auto *Proto = cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D);
6421  if (Proto->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6422  ObjCRuntime->GenerateProtocol(Proto);
6423  break;
6424  }
6425 
6426  case Decl::ObjCCategoryImpl:
6427  // Categories have properties but don't support synthesize so we
6428  // can ignore them here.
6429  ObjCRuntime->GenerateCategory(cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(D));
6430  break;
6431 
6432  case Decl::ObjCImplementation: {
6433  auto *OMD = cast<ObjCImplementationDecl>(D);
6434  EmitObjCPropertyImplementations(OMD);
6435  EmitObjCIvarInitializations(OMD);
6436  ObjCRuntime->GenerateClass(OMD);
6437  // Emit global variable debug information.
6438  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6439  if (getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
6440  DI->getOrCreateInterfaceType(getContext().getObjCInterfaceType(
6441  OMD->getClassInterface()), OMD->getLocation());
6442  break;
6443  }
6444  case Decl::ObjCMethod: {
6445  auto *OMD = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
6446  // If this is not a prototype, emit the body.
6447  if (OMD->getBody())
6448  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCMethod(OMD);
6449  break;
6450  }
6451  case Decl::ObjCCompatibleAlias:
6452  ObjCRuntime->RegisterAlias(cast<ObjCCompatibleAliasDecl>(D));
6453  break;
6454 
6455  case Decl::PragmaComment: {
6456  const auto *PCD = cast<PragmaCommentDecl>(D);
6457  switch (PCD->getCommentKind()) {
6458  case PCK_Unknown:
6459  llvm_unreachable("unexpected pragma comment kind");
6460  case PCK_Linker:
6461  AppendLinkerOptions(PCD->getArg());
6462  break;
6463  case PCK_Lib:
6464  AddDependentLib(PCD->getArg());
6465  break;
6466  case PCK_Compiler:
6467  case PCK_ExeStr:
6468  case PCK_User:
6469  break; // We ignore all of these.
6470  }
6471  break;
6472  }
6473 
6474  case Decl::PragmaDetectMismatch: {
6475  const auto *PDMD = cast<PragmaDetectMismatchDecl>(D);
6476  AddDetectMismatch(PDMD->getName(), PDMD->getValue());
6477  break;
6478  }
6479 
6480  case Decl::LinkageSpec:
6481  EmitLinkageSpec(cast<LinkageSpecDecl>(D));
6482  break;
6483 
6484  case Decl::FileScopeAsm: {
6485  // File-scope asm is ignored during device-side CUDA compilation.
6486  if (LangOpts.CUDA && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice)
6487  break;
6488  // File-scope asm is ignored during device-side OpenMP compilation.
6489  if (LangOpts.OpenMPIsDevice)
6490  break;
6491  // File-scope asm is ignored during device-side SYCL compilation.
6492  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
6493  break;
6494  auto *AD = cast<FileScopeAsmDecl>(D);
6495  getModule().appendModuleInlineAsm(AD->getAsmString()->getString());
6496  break;
6497  }
6498 
6499  case Decl::Import: {
6500  auto *Import = cast<ImportDecl>(D);
6501 
6502  // If we've already imported this module, we're done.
6503  if (!ImportedModules.insert(Import->getImportedModule()))
6504  break;
6505 
6506  // Emit debug information for direct imports.
6507  if (!Import->getImportedOwningModule()) {
6508  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6509  DI->EmitImportDecl(*Import);
6510  }
6511 
6512  // Find all of the submodules and emit the module initializers.
6513  llvm::SmallPtrSet<clang::Module *, 16> Visited;
6514  SmallVector<clang::Module *, 16> Stack;
6515  Visited.insert(Import->getImportedModule());
6516  Stack.push_back(Import->getImportedModule());
6517 
6518  while (!Stack.empty()) {
6519  clang::Module *Mod = Stack.pop_back_val();
6520  if (!EmittedModuleInitializers.insert(Mod).second)
6521  continue;
6522 
6523  for (auto *D : Context.getModuleInitializers(Mod))
6524  EmitTopLevelDecl(D);
6525 
6526  // Visit the submodules of this module.
6527  for (clang::Module::submodule_iterator Sub = Mod->submodule_begin(),
6528  SubEnd = Mod->submodule_end();
6529  Sub != SubEnd; ++Sub) {
6530  // Skip explicit children; they need to be explicitly imported to emit
6531  // the initializers.
6532  if ((*Sub)->IsExplicit)
6533  continue;
6534 
6535  if (Visited.insert(*Sub).second)
6536  Stack.push_back(*Sub);
6537  }
6538  }
6539  break;
6540  }
6541 
6542  case Decl::Export:
6543  EmitDeclContext(cast<ExportDecl>(D));
6544  break;
6545 
6546  case Decl::OMPThreadPrivate:
6547  EmitOMPThreadPrivateDecl(cast<OMPThreadPrivateDecl>(D));
6548  break;
6549 
6550  case Decl::OMPAllocate:
6551  EmitOMPAllocateDecl(cast<OMPAllocateDecl>(D));
6552  break;
6553 
6554  case Decl::OMPDeclareReduction:
6555  EmitOMPDeclareReduction(cast<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(D));
6556  break;
6557 
6558  case Decl::OMPDeclareMapper:
6559  EmitOMPDeclareMapper(cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(D));
6560  break;
6561 
6562  case Decl::OMPRequires:
6563  EmitOMPRequiresDecl(cast<OMPRequiresDecl>(D));
6564  break;
6565 
6566  case Decl::Typedef:
6567  case Decl::TypeAlias: // using foo = bar; [C++11]
6568  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6569  DI->EmitAndRetainType(
6570  getContext().getTypedefType(cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)));
6571  break;
6572 
6573  case Decl::Record:
6574  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6575  if (cast<RecordDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
6576  DI->EmitAndRetainType(getContext().getRecordType(cast<RecordDecl>(D)));
6577  break;
6578 
6579  case Decl::Enum:
6580  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6581  if (cast<EnumDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
6582  DI->EmitAndRetainType(getContext().getEnumType(cast<EnumDecl>(D)));
6583  break;
6584 
6585  default:
6586  // Make sure we handled everything we should, every other kind is a
6587  // non-top-level decl. FIXME: Would be nice to have an isTopLevelDeclKind
6588  // function. Need to recode Decl::Kind to do that easily.
6589  assert(isa<TypeDecl>(D) && "Unsupported decl kind");
6590  break;
6591  }
6592 }
6593 
6594 void CodeGenModule::AddDeferredUnusedCoverageMapping(Decl *D) {
6595  // Do we need to generate coverage mapping?
6596  if (!CodeGenOpts.CoverageMapping)
6597  return;
6598  switch (D->getKind()) {
6599  case Decl::CXXConversion:
6600  case Decl::CXXMethod:
6601  case Decl::Function:
6602  case Decl::ObjCMethod:
6603  case Decl::CXXConstructor:
6604  case Decl::CXXDestructor: {
6605  if (!cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody())
6606  break;
6607  SourceManager &SM = getContext().getSourceManager();
6608  if (LimitedCoverage && SM.getMainFileID() != SM.getFileID(D->getBeginLoc()))
6609  break;
6610  auto I = DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.find(D);
6611  if (I == DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.end())
6612  DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls[D] = true;
6613  break;
6614  }
6615  default:
6616  break;
6617  };
6618 }
6619 
6620 void CodeGenModule::ClearUnusedCoverageMapping(const Decl *D) {
6621  // Do we need to generate coverage mapping?
6622  if (!CodeGenOpts.CoverageMapping)
6623  return;
6624  if (const auto *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
6625  if (Fn->isTemplateInstantiation())
6626  ClearUnusedCoverageMapping(Fn->getTemplateInstantiationPattern());
6627  }
6628  auto I = DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.find(D);
6629  if (I == DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.end())
6630  DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls[D] = false;
6631  else
6632  I->second = false;
6633 }
6634 
6635 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeferredUnusedCoverageMappings() {
6636  // We call takeVector() here to avoid use-after-free.
6637  // FIXME: DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls is getting mutated because
6638  // we deserialize function bodies to emit coverage info for them, and that
6639  // deserializes more declarations. How should we handle that case?
6640  for (const auto &Entry : DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.takeVector()) {
6641  if (!Entry.second)
6642  continue;
6643  const Decl *D = Entry.first;
6644  switch (D->getKind()) {
6645  case Decl::CXXConversion:
6646  case Decl::CXXMethod:
6647  case Decl::Function:
6648  case Decl::ObjCMethod: {
6649  CodeGenPGO PGO(*this);
6650  GlobalDecl GD(cast<FunctionDecl>(D));
6651  PGO.emitEmptyCounterMapping(D, getMangledName(GD),
6652  getFunctionLinkage(GD));
6653  break;
6654  }
6655  case Decl::CXXConstructor: {
6656  CodeGenPGO PGO(*this);
6657  GlobalDecl GD(cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D), Ctor_Base);
6658  PGO.emitEmptyCounterMapping(D, getMangledName(GD),
6659  getFunctionLinkage(GD));
6660  break;
6661  }
6662  case Decl::CXXDestructor: {
6663  CodeGenPGO PGO(*this);
6664  GlobalDecl GD(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D), Dtor_Base);
6665  PGO.emitEmptyCounterMapping(D, getMangledName(GD),
6666  getFunctionLinkage(GD));
6667  break;
6668  }
6669  default:
6670  break;
6671  };
6672  }
6673 }
6674 
6675 void CodeGenModule::EmitMainVoidAlias() {
6676  // In order to transition away from "__original_main" gracefully, emit an
6677  // alias for "main" in the no-argument case so that libc can detect when
6678  // new-style no-argument main is in used.
6679  if (llvm::Function *F = getModule().getFunction("main")) {
6680  if (!F->isDeclaration() && F->arg_size() == 0 && !F->isVarArg() &&
6681  F->getReturnType()->isIntegerTy(Context.getTargetInfo().getIntWidth()))
6682  addUsedGlobal(llvm::GlobalAlias::create("__main_void", F));
6683  }
6684 }
6685 
6686 /// Turns the given pointer into a constant.
6687 static llvm::Constant *GetPointerConstant(llvm::LLVMContext &Context,
6688  const void *Ptr) {
6689  uintptr_t PtrInt = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Ptr);
6690  llvm::Type *i64 = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(Context);
6691  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(i64, PtrInt);
6692 }

6694 static void EmitGlobalDeclMetadata(CodeGenModule &CGM,
6695  llvm::NamedMDNode *&GlobalMetadata,
6696  GlobalDecl D,
6697  llvm::GlobalValue *Addr) {
6698  if (!GlobalMetadata)
6699  GlobalMetadata =
6700  CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("clang.global.decl.ptrs");
6701 
6702  // TODO: should we report variant information for ctors/dtors?
6703  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = {llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Addr),
6704  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(GetPointerConstant(
6705  CGM.getLLVMContext(), D.getDecl()))};
6706  GlobalMetadata->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Ops));
6707 }
6708 
6709 /// For each function which is declared within an extern "C" region and marked
6710 /// as 'used', but has internal linkage, create an alias from the unmangled
6711 /// name to the mangled name if possible. People expect to be able to refer
6712 /// to such functions with an unmangled name from inline assembly within the
6713 /// same translation unit.
6714 void CodeGenModule::EmitStaticExternCAliases() {
6715  if (!getTargetCodeGenInfo().shouldEmitStaticExternCAliases())
6716  return;
6717  for (auto &I : StaticExternCValues) {
6718  IdentifierInfo *Name = I.first;
6719  llvm::GlobalValue *Val = I.second;
6720  if (Val && !getModule().getNamedValue(Name->getName()))
6721  addCompilerUsedGlobal(llvm::GlobalAlias::create(Name->getName(), Val));
6722  }
6723 }
6724 
6725 bool CodeGenModule::lookupRepresentativeDecl(StringRef MangledName,
6726  GlobalDecl &Result) const {
6727  auto Res = Manglings.find(MangledName);
6728  if (Res == Manglings.end())
6729  return false;
6730  Result = Res->getValue();
6731  return true;
6732 }
6733 
6734 /// Emits metadata nodes associating all the global values in the
6735 /// current module with the Decls they came from. This is useful for
6736 /// projects using IR gen as a subroutine.
6737 ///
6738 /// Since there's currently no way to associate an MDNode directly
6739 /// with an llvm::GlobalValue, we create a global named metadata
6740 /// with the name 'clang.global.decl.ptrs'.
6741 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeclMetadata() {
6742  llvm::NamedMDNode *GlobalMetadata = nullptr;
6743 
6744  for (auto &I : MangledDeclNames) {
6745  llvm::GlobalValue *Addr = getModule().getNamedValue(I.second);
6746  // Some mangled names don't necessarily have an associated GlobalValue
6747  // in this module, e.g. if we mangled it for DebugInfo.
6748  if (Addr)
6749  EmitGlobalDeclMetadata(*this, GlobalMetadata, I.first, Addr);
6750  }
6751 }
6752 
6753 /// Emits metadata nodes for all the local variables in the current
6754 /// function.
6755 void CodeGenFunction::EmitDeclMetadata() {
6756  if (LocalDeclMap.empty()) return;
6757 
6758  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = getLLVMContext();
6759 
6760  // Find the unique metadata ID for this name.
6761  unsigned DeclPtrKind = Context.getMDKindID("clang.decl.ptr");
6762 
6763  llvm::NamedMDNode *GlobalMetadata = nullptr;
6764 
6765  for (auto &I : LocalDeclMap) {
6766  const Decl *D = I.first;
6767  llvm::Value *Addr = I.second.getPointer();
6768  if (auto *Alloca = dyn_cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(Addr)) {
6769  llvm::Value *DAddr = GetPointerConstant(getLLVMContext(), D);
6770  Alloca->setMetadata(
6771  DeclPtrKind, llvm::MDNode::get(
6772  Context, llvm::ValueAsMetadata::getConstant(DAddr)));
6773  } else if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Addr)) {
6774  GlobalDecl GD = GlobalDecl(cast<VarDecl>(D));
6775  EmitGlobalDeclMetadata(CGM, GlobalMetadata, GD, GV);
6776  }
6777  }
6778 }

6782  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.ident");
6783  std::string Version = getClangFullVersion();
6784  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
6785 
6786  llvm::Metadata *IdentNode[] = {llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, Version)};
6787  IdentMetadata->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, IdentNode));
6788 }

6800 void CodeGenModule::EmitCoverageFile() {
6801  if (getCodeGenOpts().CoverageDataFile.empty() &&
6802  getCodeGenOpts().CoverageNotesFile.empty())
6803  return;
6804 
6805  llvm::NamedMDNode *CUNode = TheModule.getNamedMetadata("llvm.dbg.cu");
6806  if (!CUNode)
6807  return;
6808 
6809  llvm::NamedMDNode *GCov = TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.gcov");
6810  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
6811  auto *CoverageDataFile =
6812  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, getCodeGenOpts().CoverageDataFile);
6813  auto *CoverageNotesFile =
6814  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, getCodeGenOpts().CoverageNotesFile);
6815  for (int i = 0, e = CUNode->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
6816  llvm::MDNode *CU = CUNode->getOperand(i);
6817  llvm::Metadata *Elts[] = {CoverageNotesFile, CoverageDataFile, CU};
6818  GCov->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, Elts));
6819  }
6820 }

6822 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(QualType Ty,
6823  bool ForEH) {
6824  // Return a bogus pointer if RTTI is disabled, unless it's for EH.
6825  // FIXME: should we even be calling this method if RTTI is disabled
6826  // and it's not for EH?
6827  if ((!ForEH && !getLangOpts().RTTI) || getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice ||
6828  (getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
6829  getTriple().isNVPTX()))
6830  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int8PtrTy);
6831 
6832  if (ForEH && Ty->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
6833  LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.isGNUFamily())
6834  return ObjCRuntime->GetEHType(Ty);
6835 
6836  return getCXXABI().getAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(Ty);
6837 }
6838 
6839 void CodeGenModule::EmitOMPThreadPrivateDecl(const OMPThreadPrivateDecl *D) {
6840  // Do not emit threadprivates in simd-only mode.
6841  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && LangOpts.OpenMPSimd)
6842  return;
6843  for (auto RefExpr : D->varlists()) {
6844  auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(RefExpr)->getDecl());
6845  bool PerformInit =
6846  VD->getAnyInitializer() &&
6847  !VD->getAnyInitializer()->isConstantInitializer(getContext(),
6848  /*ForRef=*/false);
6849 
6850  Address Addr(GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD),
6851  getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()),
6852  getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
6853  if (auto InitFunction = getOpenMPRuntime().emitThreadPrivateVarDefinition(
6854  VD, Addr, RefExpr->getBeginLoc(), PerformInit))
6855  CXXGlobalInits.push_back(InitFunction);
6856  }
6857 }

6859 llvm::Metadata *
6860 CodeGenModule::CreateMetadataIdentifierImpl(QualType T, MetadataTypeMap &Map,
6861  StringRef Suffix) {
6862  if (auto *FnType = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
6863  T = getContext().getFunctionType(
6864  FnType->getReturnType(), FnType->getParamTypes(),
6865  FnType->getExtProtoInfo().withExceptionSpec(EST_None));
6866 
6867  llvm::Metadata *&InternalId = Map[T.getCanonicalType()];
6868  if (InternalId)
6869  return InternalId;
6870 
6871  if (isExternallyVisible(T->getLinkage())) {
6872  std::string OutName;
6873  llvm::raw_string_ostream Out(OutName);
6874  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleTypeName(T, Out);
6875  Out << Suffix;
6876 
6877  InternalId = llvm::MDString::get(getLLVMContext(), Out.str());
6878  } else {
6879  InternalId = llvm::MDNode::getDistinct(getLLVMContext(),
6880  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Metadata *>());
6881  }
6882 
6883  return InternalId;
6884 }

6894 
6895 // Generalize pointer types to a void pointer with the qualifiers of the
6896 // originally pointed-to type, e.g. 'const char *' and 'char * const *'
6897 // generalize to 'const void *' while 'char *' and 'const char **' generalize to
6898 // 'void *'.
6899 static QualType GeneralizeType(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType Ty) {
6900  if (!Ty->isPointerType())
6901  return Ty;
6902 
6903  return Ctx.getPointerType(
6904  QualType(Ctx.VoidTy).withCVRQualifiers(
6905  Ty->getPointeeType().getCVRQualifiers()));
6906 }
6907 
6908 // Apply type generalization to a FunctionType's return and argument types
6909 static QualType GeneralizeFunctionType(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType Ty) {
6910  if (auto *FnType = Ty->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
6911  SmallVector<QualType, 8> GeneralizedParams;
6912  for (auto &Param : FnType->param_types())
6913  GeneralizedParams.push_back(GeneralizeType(Ctx, Param));
6914 
6915  return Ctx.getFunctionType(
6916  GeneralizeType(Ctx, FnType->getReturnType()),
6917  GeneralizedParams, FnType->getExtProtoInfo());
6918  }
6919 
6920  if (auto *FnType = Ty->getAs<FunctionNoProtoType>())
6921  return Ctx.getFunctionNoProtoType(
6922  GeneralizeType(Ctx, FnType->getReturnType()));
6923 
6924  llvm_unreachable("Encountered unknown FunctionType");
6925 }
6926 
6927 llvm::Metadata *CodeGenModule::CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(QualType T) {
6928  return CreateMetadataIdentifierImpl(GeneralizeFunctionType(getContext(), T),
6929  GeneralizedMetadataIdMap, ".generalized");
6930 }

6932 /// Returns whether this module needs the "all-vtables" type identifier.
6933 bool CodeGenModule::NeedAllVtablesTypeId() const {
6934  // Returns true if at least one of vtable-based CFI checkers is enabled and
6935  // is not in the trapping mode.
6936  return ((LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall) &&
6937  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall)) ||
6938  (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFINVCall) &&
6939  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFINVCall)) ||
6940  (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast) &&
6941  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast)) ||
6942  (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast) &&
6943  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast)));
6944 }

6946 void CodeGenModule::AddVTableTypeMetadata(llvm::GlobalVariable *VTable,
6947  CharUnits Offset,
6948  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
6949  llvm::Metadata *MD =
6950  CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
6951  VTable->addTypeMetadata(Offset.getQuantity(), MD);
6952 
6953  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso)
6954  if (auto CrossDsoTypeId = CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD))
6955  VTable->addTypeMetadata(Offset.getQuantity(),
6956  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CrossDsoTypeId));
6957 
6958  if (NeedAllVtablesTypeId()) {
6959  llvm::Metadata *MD = llvm::MDString::get(getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables");
6960  VTable->addTypeMetadata(Offset.getQuantity(), MD);
6961  }
6962 }

6983  QualType T, LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo, TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {

6987 
6988 CharUnits CodeGenModule::getNaturalTypeAlignment(QualType T,
6989  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
6990  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo,
6991  bool forPointeeType) {
6992  if (TBAAInfo)
6993  *TBAAInfo = getTBAAAccessInfo(T);
6994 
6995  // FIXME: This duplicates logic in ASTContext::getTypeAlignIfKnown. But
6996  // that doesn't return the information we need to compute BaseInfo.
6997 
6998  // Honor alignment typedef attributes even on incomplete types.
6999  // We also honor them straight for C++ class types, even as pointees;
7000  // there's an expressivity gap here.
7001  if (auto TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
7002  if (auto Align = TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment()) {
7003  if (BaseInfo)
7004  *BaseInfo = LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::AttributedType);
7005  return getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(Align);
7006  }
7007  }
7008 
7009  bool AlignForArray = T->isArrayType();
7010 
7011  // Analyze the base element type, so we don't get confused by incomplete
7012  // array types.
7013  T = getContext().getBaseElementType(T);
7014 
7015  if (T->isIncompleteType()) {
7016  // We could try to replicate the logic from
7017  // ASTContext::getTypeAlignIfKnown, but nothing uses the alignment if the
7018  // type is incomplete, so it's impossible to test. We could try to reuse
7019  // getTypeAlignIfKnown, but that doesn't return the information we need
7020  // to set BaseInfo. So just ignore the possibility that the alignment is
7021  // greater than one.
7022  if (BaseInfo)
7023  *BaseInfo = LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Type);
7024  return CharUnits::One();
7025  }
7026 
7027  if (BaseInfo)
7028  *BaseInfo = LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Type);
7029 
7030  CharUnits Alignment;
7031  const CXXRecordDecl *RD;
7032  if (T.getQualifiers().hasUnaligned()) {
7033  Alignment = CharUnits::One();
7034  } else if (forPointeeType && !AlignForArray &&
7035  (RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())) {
7036  // For C++ class pointees, we don't know whether we're pointing at a
7037  // base or a complete object, so we generally need to use the
7038  // non-virtual alignment.
7039  Alignment = getClassPointerAlignment(RD);
7040  } else {
7041  Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(T);
7042  }
7043 
7044  // Cap to the global maximum type alignment unless the alignment
7045  // was somehow explicit on the type.
7046  if (unsigned MaxAlign = getLangOpts().MaxTypeAlign) {
7047  if (Alignment.getQuantity() > MaxAlign &&
7048  !getContext().isAlignmentRequired(T))
7049  Alignment = CharUnits::fromQuantity(MaxAlign);
7050  }
7051  return Alignment;
7052 }
7053 
7054 bool CodeGenModule::stopAutoInit() {
7055  unsigned StopAfter = getContext().getLangOpts().TrivialAutoVarInitStopAfter;
7056  if (StopAfter) {
7057  // This number is positive only when -ftrivial-auto-var-init-stop-after=* is
7058  // used
7059  if (NumAutoVarInit >= StopAfter) {
7060  return true;
7061  }
7062  if (!NumAutoVarInit) {
7063  unsigned DiagID = getDiags().getCustomDiagID(
7064  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning,
7065  "-ftrivial-auto-var-init-stop-after=%0 has been enabled to limit the "
7066  "number of times ftrivial-auto-var-init=%1 gets applied.");
7067  getDiags().Report(DiagID)
7068  << StopAfter
7069  << (getContext().getLangOpts().getTrivialAutoVarInit() ==
7070  LangOptions::TrivialAutoVarInitKind::Zero
7071  ? "zero"
7072  : "pattern");
7073  }
7074  ++NumAutoVarInit;
7075  }
7076  return false;
7077 }
